title: lime pickles
directions: Dissolve
lime	in
gallons	cold
water. Put sliced cucumbers
into the mixture and let soak overnight.
Wash real good
with clear, clean water, then let soak in cold water for 3 hours.
Then drain.

title: "diabetic" chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl and beat just until blended.
Pour into well-greased and floured 13 x 9-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: five layer taco dip
directions: Beat cream cheese and powdered taco dip and spread on cookie sheet.
Top with salsa sauce.
Sprinkle with layer of shredded lettuce.
Top with tomatoes.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Unroll each half of crescent roll dough to make a rectangle.
Press dough into bottom and 1/2-inch up sides of greased 2-quart baking dish, pressing seams to seal. Sprinkle sausage over dough.
Top with cheese and sprinkle with green pepper.
Combine eggs, milk and herbs.
Pour over casserole. Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: french onion soup
directions: Put all ingredients in saucepan; cook until onions are tender. Put in crock-pot on low for 2 hours.
Serve with French bread, toasted and buttered.
Dip toast in soup.

title: louisiana creme fudge
directions: Use a large, heavy pan and cook very, very slow.
Cook sugar, syrup and cream, stirring until boiling, then cook to 234°, soft ball stage.
Let cool 5 minutes, then add butter and vanilla.
Then add flour and beat 15 minutes.
Add nuts and pour in dish.
Cut when cool.

title: baked beans with hamburger
directions: Brown meat with onions and bell pepper. Mix all other ingredients. Bake in buttered dish 30 minutes at 350°.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Melt slowly the chocolate chips with milk.
Cool mixture slightly.
Add nuts and marshmallows and mix.
Spread into greased 9-inch square pan.
Refrigerate and cut into squares.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into an unbaked pie crust. Bake in hot oven (425°) for 15 minutes, then lower temperature to 350°.
Bake 35 minutes longer.

title: mae laws relish
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions, cabbage, garlic, green pepper and salt.
Cover with ice; let stand for 3 hours.
Drain.
Bring mustard seed, celery seed, sugar, vinegar and turmeric to boil; pour over the drained vegetables and return to a boil.
Add corn and chopped carrots (2 cups total); put into sterilized jars. Process in water bath for 20 minutes.
Makes 9 pints.
A great favorite and delicious in egg or potato salad.

title: orange chicken
directions: Mix together oil, juice, honey, vinegar, Worcestershire and salt and pour over chicken.
Marinate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant; cut in cubes and boil in salted water until tender, approximately 20 minutes.
Drain and mash with fork. Brown ground chuck, onion and bell pepper; stir in eggplant and 2 cups cooked rice.
Pour into 2-quart baking dish.
Top with buttered cracker crumbs (I prefer Ritz).
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: hot seafood souffle
directions: Place half of the bread into a greased baking dish (9 x 12-inch).
Mix seafood, mayonnaise, onion, green pepper, celery, almonds, salt and pepper.
Spread over the bread.
Add remaining bread over mixture.
Mix eggs and milk and pour over.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Take from oven.
Pour mushroom soup over top (with a little cooking sherry). Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake 1 hour longer at 325°. Serves 12.

title: sausage-skillet supper
directions: Cut sausage into chunks or slices.
Combine with next 4 ingredients in large skillet.
Cover; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in frozen peas and mushrooms. Sprinkle cheese over the top.
Cover and simmer without lifting the lid for 20 minutes.

title: peppered ribeye steaks
directions: Brush steaks lightly with olive oil.
In a small bowl, combine all seasonings.
Sprinkle seasonings over steaks and press into both sides.
Cover and chill 1 hour.

title: "cheese" spread
directions: Mix and cook over low heat, stirring, then beat in margarine. Use with nachos, pasta, etc.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together until they resemble coarse cornmeal. Press into 8-inch square pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut while warm.
Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: cranberry-banana bread
directions: Combine cranberries, 1 cup sugar and water.
Cook over medium heat until berries pop (about 5 minutes); drain.
Cream shortening and 2/3 cup sugar, beat until light.
Add eggs and beat.
Combine dry ingredients, creamed mixture and bananas.
Mix well.
Add cranberries and walnuts.

title: pudding cake
directions: Mix margarine, cake mix and 1 beaten egg.
Pour in bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Beat eggs, cream cheese, powdered sugar and pecans.
Pour over first layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: capelli d'angelo with shrimp and herbs
directions: Combine the wine, oil, lemon juice, mustard, chopped basil and peppercorns and pour over the shrimp in a shallow bowl.
Marinate in the refrigerator at least 3 hours, turning the shrimp occasionally.
Prepare hot coals with a generous amount of mesquite for grilling the shrimp.

title: summer garden zucchini boats
directions: Microwave bacon 45 to 60 seconds until slightly underdone. Let stand 5 minutes, covered, to complete cooking.
Crumble bacon. Cut zucchini lengthwise in half.
Scoop out centers, leaving 1/4-inch shells.

title: potato casserole
directions: Chop potatoes and add all but last two ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole.
Top with crushed corn flakes and melted butter mixed together.
Sprinkle over potatoes.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apricot salad
directions: Bring apricot jello, water and sugar to boil.
Remove from heat and add cream cheese and 1 cup nuts.
Set aside to cool. Whip milk.
Pour all in milk and fold in well.
Pour in large mold and sprinkle 1/2 nuts on top.
Chill or freeze.

title: sausage stars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blot cooked ground pork dry with paper towels. Combine with cheeses, salad dressing, olives and red pepper.
Lightly grease a mini muffin tin and press 1 wrapper that has been cut in quarters in each cup. Brush with oil. Bake 5 minutes until golden.
Remove from tins and place on baking sheet. Fill each "star" with meat mixture. Bake 5 minutes until bubbly. Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: orange julius
directions: Put everything in blender.
Add ice cubes to level of liquid. Blend on high until thick and smooth.

title: caramel corn
directions: Pop popcorn.
Boil the butter, brown sugar and Karo for 5 minutes; do not stir.
Stir soda and vanilla together.
Put all in a greased pan.
Bake at 300° for 1/2 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: carolina delights
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to a boil at medium heat.
After it comes to a boil, let it boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Take off burner.
Mix the oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla with the hot cocoa mixture.
Stir real good, then drop from spoon onto wax paper.
Let set up.

title: pork roast
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Trim off excess fat.
Combine all ingredients together.
Rub roast with mixture.
Place meat in a shallow roasting pan, fat side up.
Roast, uncovered, in oven for 2 1/4 to 2 3/4 hours or until the meat thermometer registers 170°.

title: peach salad
directions: Mix jello, both boxes of pudding and boiling water together, let set until cool.
Add cool whip and cubed peaches.
Refrigerate.

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: Cook all the ingredients together until thick.
Then add 1/4 cup oleo and 1 tablespoon vanilla.
Pour into baked pie crust.

title: salmon spread
directions: Drain and flake salmon, removing skin and bones.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill.
Serve with crackers or bagels.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into baking dish.

title: cornflake peanut butter cookies
directions: Melt sugar and Karo in a large pot.
Bring almost to a boil and add peanut butter and melt.
Turn off fire.
Pour in cornflakes and stir good.
Lay cookies in wax paper or tin foil.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix soup and cream cheese over low heat until creamy. Add gelatine.
Place in freezer about 15 minutes or until it gels. Remove and mix remaining ingredients.
Serve with chips. Delicious!

title: cinnamon-raisin bars
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Add oats and 1 tablespoon of water.
Mix until crumbly; firmly pat half into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread with Raisin Filling.
Mix remaining crumbs with 1 tablespoon of water; spoon over filling.
Pat smooth.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Cool.
Drizzle with Cinnamon Icing.

title: log cabin pudding
directions: Mash crackers fine.
Cut dates in 2 or 3 pieces.
Cut marshmallows up, but if you use miniature ones it will take more cream.
Put in cream.
Work into loaf.
Mix it all cold.
Wrap loaf in wax paper and refrigerate overnight.
Slice and serve.

title: t v a refrigerator rolls
directions: Put hot potatoes in large mixing bowl. Mash. Add shortening, sugar, salt and eggs, beating well. Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water. Add to lukewarm milk; add this to potato mixture. Sift flour in to make a soft dough; turn out on floured board and knead well. When fairly smooth, place in large, greased bowl. Cover and let rise until doubled. Punch down. Brush top of dough with melted butter. Cover and refrigerate until ready to use. Dough keeps well for several days.

title: zippy italian dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of an electric blender; blend well.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour.

title: 10 minute chili
directions: Using a skillet, brown the ground beef then add the beans and soup.
Fill the soup can 3/4 full of water and add also.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until heated through.
Can eat immediately or simmer longer if desired.
Can also experiment with adding different seasonings to suit your taste buds, such as chili powder, Tabasco sauce, Mexican seasoning, etc. or simply eat as it is.

title: egg rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients,
except
egg
and
egg roll skins. Chill for 1/2 hour.
On an egg roll skin, place the amount the size
of your
thumb
and roll it like a burrito.
In a bowl, with
a fork,
mix the egg.
Use your finger and dip into egg and
seal the
egg roll seam ends.
Fry in oil on medium heat until
golden brown.
You
want
to
cook
the inside without burning
the
egg roll skin.
Serve with a plum sauce or sweet and sour sauce.

title: tofu cheese cake
directions: Heat milk; dissolve gelatin in it.
Add sugar and eggs.
Beat in cheese and tofu.
Add vanilla.
Pour into dessert pie shell and refrigerate.

title: raspberry sherbet
directions: Combine fruit, yogurt and sugar. Freeze to slushy consistency. In a chilled bowl, beat egg whites until light and fluffy, forming soft peaks. Add vanilla and continue to beat another 30 seconds.

title: apricot cake
directions: With fork, mix together until smooth.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Bake in 10-inch angel food pan for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Mix rhubarb, pineapple, sugar and salt in a kettle.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal or cool and cover with Parawax.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Mix cocoa and boiling water together, mix well.
Let cool. Cream Crisco and sugar, add eggs.
Add sour milk, flour, baking soda, vanilla and salt.
Add cocoa and water mixture.
Mix well. Drop by tablespoons full on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool on wax paper.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Slice carrots in 1-inch sections and cook until slightly tender, about 15 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients in bowl. Drain carrots and turn into bowl while hot.
Refrigerate in covered dish or in jars.
Will keep for several weeks.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into a ring.
Place into microwave-safe dish and cook on High 15 to 19 minutes.
Make sure your dish is deep enough to catch the grease.

title: crab and cheese appetizer
directions: Bring all ingredients to room temperature and mix together. Spread on party rolls.
Broil until cheese melts and is brown.

title: aunt ethel's country steak
directions: Put steak in pan or baking dish. Cover with mushroom soup. Sprinkle with onion soup. Cover and bake at 275° to 300° for 2 to 3 hours.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine. Press equal portions onto bottom of 24 lightly greased or paper cup lined muffin cups.
In large mixing bowl, beat cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Spoon equal amounts of mixture (about 3 tablespoons) into prepared cups.
Bake 20 minutes or until set. Cool.
Chill and top with filling.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: five fruit salad with peanut butter dressing
directions: For dressing, in blender container or food processor bowl place pineapple juice concentrate and peanut butter.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Keeping blender running at high speed, gradually add oil through hole in lid or with lid ajar until mixture is well blended.
Turn into storage container; cover. Store dressing in refrigerator until serving time:
stir before using.
Line a large platter with lettuce. Arrange fruit atop. Pass dressing with salad.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix first five ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Mix cornstarch with enough water to form a paste.
Add to pineapple mixture and cook until thickened.
Cool and pour into pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Add onion and celery (optional). Add soup.
Stir and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Add tomato paste plus 4 cans of water, garlic, Italian seasoning, basil, lemon pepper, salt and wine.
Simmer 2 to 3 hours, covered.
Water may be added while simmering.
Cook lasagne noodles.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and an 11 x 7 1/2-inch baking dish.
Place in dishes in the following order:

noodles, meat sauce, cheeses, ending with noodles on top. Cover with foil and bake at 350° about 45 minutes. Freezes nicely, but don't cook before freezing and allow longer baking time for frozen lasagne.

title: apple pudding
directions: Pour sugar, oil and eggs over chopped apples.
Mix and stir in dry ingredients, nuts and raisins.
Pour into a well-oiled 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tested done.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: grandma's tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and milk.
Sift enough flour (self-rising) to make a stiff dough.
Roll out and bake on cookie sheet at 450° until brown.

title: strawberry-banana salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; stir in fruit.
Pour half of jello mixture into an 8-inch pan and refrigerate until firm. Store remaining jello mixture at room temperature.

title: easy lemonade pie
directions: Use frozen limeade for lime pie.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Beat lemonade and milk.
Add Cool Whip and pour into a graham cracker pie crust.
Chill.
Great with fish suppers.

title: breakfast potatoes
directions: Toss potatoes in oil and seasonings.
Cook on medium heat in large skillet until tender.

title: chicken salad with fruit
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients, except dressing. Mix thoroughly. Add enough of the Miracle Whip or mayonnaise to properly moisten salad. May need more or less than 1 cup.

title: pickled salmon
directions: Put salmon pieces in a crock (I used my big Pyrex mixing bowl) with layers of 3/4 cup salt and 1 pound brown sugar, skin side up. Carefully cut bones off of meat.
This takes an hour or more. Leave at least 3 days in crock.

title: orange julius
directions: In blender, combine all ingredients.
Blend for 1/2 minute or until ice cubes are crushed (stir setting).
Makes 4 servings.

title: barbecues
directions: Stir meat in small amount of shortening; add remaining ingredients except buns.
Simmer 4 to 6 hours.
Grill bun if wanted.
Serves 40 people.

title: mamie eisenhower's never fail fudge
directions: Combine butter, sugar and milk.
Stir constantly; scrape sides of pan and continue stirring until boiling starts.
Stop stirring and boil for 8 minutes.
Remove from heat and add chocolate, marshmallow and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add nuts.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool until firm, then cut.
Makes about 5 pounds. Will keep well for several months if stored in refrigerator in tight container.

title: coffee cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, put the sugar, margarine and salt.
Pour the scalded milk over and let cool.
Put 2 teaspoons sugar in warm water.
Add yeast and let it get foamy.
Add eggs to the milk mixture.
Stir; add yeast, then flour and beat with enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Turn out onto floured surface and knead until smooth.
Grease bowl.
Put in dough and turn to grease top. Let rise until double.
Take out about 1/3 of the dough to floured surface and roll into a rectangle about 9 x 12-inch.
Spread with melted margarine; sprinkle well with brown sugar and cinnamon. Roll and flatten a little.
Place on well-greased cookie sheet or on pizza pan and bring ends together to form a circle.
Cut in 1/2-inch slices nearly to the center and turn cut sides up.
Let rise until nice and light.
Bake in 375° oven until brown and done.
Frost with powdered sugar glaze.

title: "everything nice" pecans
directions: Combine stiffly beaten egg whites and vanilla. Combine sugar, brown sugar and cinnamon and mix well.
Add to the egg whites and mix.
Add pecan halves and gently stir in to coat each pecan half. Using a fork, individually remove pecan halves from egg white mixture and place on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 250 degrees for about 20 minutes.
Cool completely.
Store in airtight container.

title: sliced ham with pineapple
directions: Place ham in an 8 x 8-inch casserole.
Add whole cloves in ham.
Mix together the maple syrup, vinegar and pineapple juice. Also add cinnamon; mix well.
Pour over ham.
Decorate with pineapple slices; cook for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix salt and cinnamon with flour.
Mix all in order, then add grated carrots.
Pour into well-greased tube pan.
Bake 2 hours at 300°.
As soon as you remove cake from oven, add icing to cake in pan, then turn out onto plate and ice rest of cake.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar, along with vanilla.
Add potato chips, pecans and flour.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chicken on sunday
directions: Line long oblong pan with tinfoil.
Pour rice evenly on bottom of foil.
Mix all other ingredients except chicken in bowl.
Put skinned chicken on uncooked regular rice.
Pour all ingredients from bowl over chicken and rice.
Cover with another piece of foil and join with the bottom layer of foil to make airtight.
Cook at 350° for about 3 hours.
This is great to put in oven, come home from church, it is all done.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and peanut butter until smooth, then add milk.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip and whip until no lumps.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Store in freezer, take out 1/2 hour before serving.

title: wedding salad
directions: Cook the sugar, salt, juices from fruit, flour, egg and lemon juice and bring to a boil. Add to drained acini. Refrigerate overnight. In the morning, add fruits and Cool Whip. Mix well and chill.

title: old time bread pudding
directions: Place buttered bread in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with raisins. Combine 4 teaspoons sugar, salt, milk, water and vanilla. Pour over bread and let stand 10 minutes. Sprinkle with cinnamon and remaining sugar. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: cream cheese-raisin sandwich spread
directions: Mix cream cheese, walnuts, raisins, pineapple and red pepper sauce.
Spread on whole wheat bread.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips with margarine in the microwave. Stir in peanut butter. Pour over cereal. Pour the powdered sugar into a large paper bag. Add cereal mixture and shake until pieces are covered.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Boil pineapple and sugar; remove from heat and stir in Jell-O. Add softened cream cheese and mix until smooth. Stir in celery and nuts. Whip evaporated milk and fold in. Refrigerate to congeal.

title: cream cheese potatoes
directions: Peel and boil potatoes.
Mash and add milk (and butter, if desired) and cream cheese until desired consistency is reached. Place mixture into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over top and cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes. Remove foil last ten minutes.
Serve warm.

title: microwave citrus marmalade
directions: Score outer peel of fruit into quarters.
Remove thin layer of peel a quarter at a time.
Discard white membrane from peel and fruit.
Cut peel into very thin strips.
In 2-quart microwave-safe bowl, combine peel, water and soda.
Cover; microwave on High for 5 to 8 minutes or until mixture comes to a full rolling boil; continue to boil for 10 minutes, stirring once halfway through cooking.

title: chicken in white wine and yogurt sauce
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons of the margarine in a shallow baking dish. Place chicken breasts in pan and bake at 350°, uncovered, for about 30 minutes.

title: balsamic green beans
directions: Clean green beans.
Place in saucepan with water.
Boil for approximately 3 to 4 minutes.
(Green beans should be crisp.) Drain water.
With beans in the pan, add 2 tablespoons butter or margarine and 1/4 to 1/2 cup balsamic vinegar.
Place lid on saucepan and shake until butter is melted and mixture is combined.

title: strawberries
directions: Dye toothpicks green beforehand.

title: oatmeal waffles
directions: In bowl, mix eggs and buttermilk.
Add oats and mix.
Stir in molasses and oil.
Combine flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Stir into egg mixture.
If too thick, add a little milk. Bake on preheated waffle iron.

title: 6 week bran muffins
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and add oil, eggs and white sugar that has been mixed well.
To both mixtures, add bran, raisins and flour.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes in greased muffin tins.
Place remainder in a glass bowl that has extra room and can be covered as the mixture will raise somewhat.
This will last 6 weeks.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Mix marinade thoroughly and set aside.
Put chicken wings in large Ziploc bag in pan to fit.
Pour marinade over all in bag. Press out air and seal bag.
Marinate in fridge 24 hours, turning bag every so often.

title: sugar-free banana muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Divide among 12 cup muffin pan. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. They should spring back when touched and are slightly brown on top.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Split Twinkies and place (filling side up) into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix pudding mix and milk together.
Put pudding on top of Twinkies.
Slice bananas on top of pudding.
Drain pineapple and put over bananas.
Cover with Cool Whip. Refrigerate overnight.

title: pumpkin-pecan bread
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt and spices.
Add sugar.
Stir thoroughly.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients and add all other ingredients.
Mix well and add nuts or raisins.
Pour batter into 4 (8 x 4-inch) loaf pans (greased and floured), filling 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 4 loaves.

title: alma todd's homemade bread
directions: Grease two 8 x 4-inch or 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.	Lightly spoon flour into	measuring
cup; level off.
In a large bowl, combine 2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast; blend well.
In a small pan heat water and oil until very warm.
Add warm liquid to flour mixture.
Blend at low speed until moistened.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Stir
in
additional 2 1/2 to 3 cups flour, until dough
pulls cleanly away from sides of bowl.
On floured surface, knead
dough
about 10 minutes or until dough is smooth and elastic with blisters under the surface.
Place dough in greased bowl;
cover
loosely
with plastic wrap and cloth towel.
Let rise
in warm place until light and doubled in size, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy tomato soup
directions: Combine juice and soda; bring to a boil. Add cold milk, butter and sugar. Bring to boil again. Add seasonings to taste.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Preheat oven
to
In large bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Add
flour,
sugar
and
brown sugar;
beat until well blended. Blend in melted butter/margarine.
Stir in chocolate chips and walnuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Remove about 1/4 cup of liquid from pie.
Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: reception salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Add pineapple, celery and nuts. Mash cream cheese and pimiento.
Add to mixture. Add pinch of salt to cream cheese. Set in refrigerator.
When the mixture begins to jell, fold in whipped cream. Set in refrigerator until completely jelled.

title: zucchini parmesan
directions: Mix small amount of flour, salt and pepper.
Roll zucchini slices in flour mixture.
Brown lightly on one side.
Turn and brown the other side.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: caramel icing
directions: Place 2 cups sugar in pan. Add milk and melted butter. Into another small skillet, put 1/2 cup sugar and melt over very slow heat. At the same time, have first vessel heating slowly. When both mixtures are at boiling point, slowly add melted sugar to first mixture, beating constantly as added. Allow to boil up for about 1 minute (by the clock) or until soft-ball. Remove and add 1 teaspoon vanilla. Beat until consistency to spread.

title: date nut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of a 9-inch square baking pan.
Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Remove from heat. Stir in remaining ingredients in order listed.
Mix well.
Spread in prepared pan.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Cut into 24 bars.
Sift confectioners sugar over bars, if desired.

title: apple pie
directions: Cook apples in about 1/2 cup of water until soft.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Top with dots of butter, then sprinkle with cinnamon as desired.
Add woven lattice top crust.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes until golden brown.

title: meat marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Marinate meat overnight. This is good for beef, chicken or pork.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Brown sausage and onion; drain.
Place in a crock-pot with smoked sausage and 5 cans Van Camp's New Orleans style beans. Cook at least two hours.
Serve over saffron rice.

title: florentine stuffed shells
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, stir cornstarch, milk, salt and hot pepper sauce until smooth.
Bring to boil over medium heat; boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add Parmesan cheese and ketchup, stirring until smooth.
Remove 1/4 cup sauce; reserve.
In large skillet, heat corn oil over medium heat.
Add turkey and garlic; saute 3 minutes.
Stir in spinach, Ricotta and reserved 1/4 cup sauce.
Spoon about 2 tablespoons mixture into each shell.
Place shells in an 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish; top with remaining sauce.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes, or until heated through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pie crust
directions: Combine flour and salt in medium bowl and cut in shortening with blender to form pea-size chunks.
Add your egg and water, a little at a time, until dough forms a ball.
Roll dough on a floured pastry cloth.
You divide dough up to make 2 (8-inch) pies with top crust for one pie.
You can freeze the pies until you need to fill them.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until creamy. Beat egg into creamed mixture.

title: enchilada ole
directions: Mix together in bowl; sour cream, enchilada sauce, green chilies and onion soup mix. Layer; beginning with flour tortillas that are quartered. Then add half of cooked ground beef, half of sour cream mixture and top with cheese. Repeat once. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Dredge chicken with flour and salt.
Heat oil in skillet. Simmer, covered, 45 minutes.

title: quick italian cream cake
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients at medium speed for 2 minutes. Stir in coconut and pecans. Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans. Bake at 350° for 15 to 17 minutes or until a wooden pick comes out clean. Cool in pans for 10 minutes. Remove from pans and cool on wire racks. Sprinkle layers with rum, if desired. Let stand for 10 minutes. Spread frosting between layers and on top and sides of cake. Chill 2 hours before slicing.

title: bloody marys
directions: In a pitcher, stir together tomato juice, vodka, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, celery salt and hot pepper sauce.
Serve over ice.
Garnish each glass with a celery stalk or pickle spear, if desired.
Makes 10 (about 4 ounce) servings.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Let stand until partially thickened.
Put cucumber through food chopper.
Add to gelatin with remaining ingredients.
Put into lightly oiled mold.

title: easy refrigerator rolls
directions: Measure into mixing bowl the water; add yeast, stirring to dissolve yeast.
Stir in sugar, salt, shortening and egg.
Mix flour in with hand until dough is easy to handle.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover with wax paper.
Place in refrigerator or if you're in a hurry for them, place in warm place and let rise. After rolls rise to top of bowl, work on floured surface.
Make into rolls.
Let rise until doubled, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Bake in 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Place rice in water with salt and butter.
Simmer down until stiff, about 1/2 hour, after it comes to a boil.
While rice is boiling, beat eggs, sugar and vanilla together.
After rice is stiff, add cream and milk and boil 20 minutes, mixing continually. Add egg/sugar mixture to rice.
Bring to boil; take off stove and cool.
Sprinkle with cinnamon if desired.

title: chocolate chip coffee cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in mixing bowl; beat until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Remove 1 cup crumb mixture; set aside.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla to remaining crumb mixture.
Mix until blended.
Pour batter into a greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch pan; sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Top with reserved 1 cup crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool slightly; dust top with powdered sugar.
Yields 1 coffee cake.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix wafers, sugar and orange juice together.
Add butter and pecans; form bite sized balls.
Roll in coconut and refrigerate until firm.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill for 2 hours.
Serve with sliced vegetables.

title: texas red chili
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients with 4 cups water in a large saucepan.
Simmer for several minutes.
Cook ground beef in a skillet until brown and crumbled.
Add to bean mixture.
Cook over low heat for 1 hour.

title: banana muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg.
Mix well.
Add bananas, sour cream and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and baking soda.
Mix.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pat's hot eggs
directions: Put oil in frying pan until hot.
Add beaten eggs and stir. Add onions and peppers.
Keep stirring until eggs are completely cooked.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: old-fashioned vinegar pie
directions: Mix vinegar, water and eggs.
Add flour and sugar, which has been mixed together.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Add butter.
Mix and pour into baked pie shell.
Beat 2 egg whites for meringue.
Add 6 tablespoons of sugar.
Cover filling and bake in oven until topping is brown.

title: eclairs
directions: Boil water.
Add shortening and stir until melted.
Add flour and stir until it leaves the sides of the pan.
Take off stove and cool slightly.
Add beaten eggs, one at a time, stirring well. Spoon along side each other on cookie sheet.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Brown hamburger and drain.
Add soups, pepper and macaroni.
Place 1/2 mixture in and cover with half cheese and onions.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Place in greased casserole dish.
Top with potato chips and bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Stir together margarine, sugar and milk in heavy 5-quart pan; bring to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in chips until melted.
Add remaining ingredients; mix until well blended.
Pour into 3 greased 9-inch or 2 greased 13 x 9-inch baking pans.
Cool at room temperature. Cut into squares.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: frosted sugar cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream butter and sugar; add juice, egg and orange rind.
Add flour mixture, a third at a time, stirring well.
Shape into a ball.
Wrap in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate several hours.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll dough on lightly floured board.
Cut with cookie cutters and place on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: orange bread
directions: Cut the peel from 3 large oranges and cook in salt water until tender.
Drain.
Add 1 cup sugar to peel while still hot. Simmer until clear.
Cut peel into small pieces.
Mix remaining ingredients. Add orange mixture. Pour into 2 medium and 1 small bread pan. Bake at 350° about 35 to 45 minutes. Check for doneness with toothpick.

title: sauce for ham
directions: Mix together.
Stir and heat contents on stove.
Add more cornstarch if desired for consistency.

title: white chip orange dream cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking soda and salt in a bowl.
Beat butter, granulated sugar and brown sugar in a mixer bowl until creamy. Beat in egg and orange peel.
Gradually beat in flour mixture. Stir in morsels.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes about 3 1/4 dozen cookies.

title: cheesy burger soup
directions: Cook ground beef in Dutch oven or large sauce pan over medium heat for 8 to 10 minutes or until thoroughly cooked, stirring frequently.
Drain.

title: dutch "boterkoek" (butter cake)
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add egg white, baking powder and salt. Add flour and mix well. Divide batter and spread into 2 pie plates. Spread egg yolk over top and decorate with cross hatching marks with the tine of a fork.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except Ritz crackers and pour in casserole dish.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Put on top last 15 minutes the crushed Ritz crackers, mixed with melted stick of butter.
Can be made ahead and frozen.

title: quick spanish rice
directions: Bring V-8 just to boiling.
Add picante sauce and rice.
Cover and cook 20 minutes.
Serve 4 to 6.

title: steak lo mein
directions: Slice steak into 1/4-inch strips.
Combine bouillon, water, soy sauce and cornstarch.
Set aside.
In a wok or large skillet, heat oil; add meat and garlic.
Stir-fry until meat is no longer pink.
Remove meat.
Add cabbage, carrots, onion, mushrooms, celery and green onions.
Cook for about 3 minutes.
Add pea pods and water chestnuts.
Cook about 2 minutes.
Add meat.
Stir bouillon mixture and pour over veggies.
Cook until sauce is thick.
Gently toss in spaghetti and heat for about 1 minute.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces; brown in hot oil. Remove chicken and saute onion in oil. Add remaining ingredients and simmer 30 minutes. Place chicken in sauce and bake, uncovered, in 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: hermits
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool in pan, cut while hot.

title: sea island salad
directions: Chill cooked macaroni.
Stir in mayonnaise or salad dressing, blended with sour cream and seasonings.
Gently stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill thoroughly.

title: crazy crust pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into a 9-inch pie plate.
Pour filling of your choice (apple is good) in center.
Bake at 425° for 50 minutes.

title: butterscotch bars
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine marshmallow cream, water and corn syrup.
Heat and stir over low heat until mixture just comes to a boil.
Remove from heat. Add butterscotch chips. Stir until thoroughly blended. Combine Rice Krispies and peanuts in a bowl. Pour marshmallow mixture over.
Toss until cereal is well coated. Press into well buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill until firm. Cut into squares.

title: hush puppies
directions: Heat oil (1-inch) to 375°.
Mix corn meal, salt, onions and baking soda. Stir in buttermilk. Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil. Fry until brown, about 20 minutes.
Makes about 2 dozen Hush Puppies.

title: raisin bread pudding
directions: Soak bread in milk two hours.
Beat sugar and eggs together. Add milk, butter, salt and raisins.
Pour into Pyrex dish. Sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Bake at 325° for 1/2 hour.

title: oyster chowder
directions: Prepare potatoes, onion and celery. Add vegetables and seasonings (but NOT the nutmeg) to chicken broth and simmer until fork tender, about 30 minutes and then remove bay leaf. Chop oysters into bite size pieces; add liquor and oysters to pot of vegetables and simmer 3 or 4 minutes before adding milk (or half & half) to pot. Mix cornstarch with small amount of water, add to pot, gently cook and stir until chowder thickens. Mix in a few dashes of Tabasco Sauce and serve with the fresh nutmeg on top.

title: shrimp turnovers
directions: Grind shrimp.
Combine all ingredients except pastry stick and cream; blend into a paste.
Prepare pastry stick as directed.
Roll very thin and cut into 2-inch circles.
Place 1 teaspoon of filling in center of each circle.
Moisten edges with cold water; fold over and press edges together with fork.
Prick tops and brush with cream.
Bake in a hot oven, 475°, for approximately 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about 48 turnovers.

title: mexican black bean soup
directions: Melt cheese (or just put in crock-pot and allow to melt) and mix in other ingredients.
Heat thoroughly in crock-pot (I cooked mine on low for about 2 hours).
Serve over tortilla chips.
You can also serve this with some chalupas (from Taco Bell) and you have a wonderful Mexican meal.

title: grandmama's chow chow
directions: Mix tomatoes, onions, peppers, cabbage, and salt together and let stand overnight.
Next day, drain out all possible juice.
Mix the sugar, vinegar and spices (put spices in a small cloth bag). Pour over tomato mixture.
Cook until well done, about 30 to 45 minutes or until thick.
Put in jars and seal.

title: chinese egg rolls
directions: Heat the sesame oil in a large skillet.
Quickly cook the bean sprouts over high heat stirring constantly.
Add mushrooms, water chestnuts, bamboo shoots and cook approximately 2 minutes. Add meat, shrimp, green onion, salt & pepper, soy sauce, sugar. Remove from heat and set aside to cool.

title: brownie dessert
directions: Bake brownies as directed on box.
When cooled, break up brownie mix and layer portion in bottom of bowl (should have 2 or 3 layers).
Spread with layer of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with layer of crushed Heath bars.
Do this at least twice, ending with Cool Whip and crushed Heath bars.

title: strawberry meringue puffs
directions: Beat
egg
whites
and	vanilla
until soft peaks form. Gradually
add sugar, beating to stiff peaks.
Spread meringue on top
and sides of each sponge cake.
Place on baking sheet. Bake in	very
hot
oven
(450°) for 5 minutes or until golden brown. Remove from oven; fill center of each cup with a scoop of ice cream.
Spoon
berries
over ice cream.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Saute diced onion.
Add diced Velveeta cheese, milk, cream of chicken soup and whole diced chicken. Mix until
melted.
Cook lasagna noodles. Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan 3 noodles, 1/3 cheese mix, 1/3 cottage cheese and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Repeat twice.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes covered, then 15 minutes uncovered at 350°.

title: summer torte
directions: Line two baking sheets with parchment paper.
Trace a 10 inch circle on both sheets.
Preheat oven to 300 degrees.
For meringues, in a large bowl, combine egg whites, cream of tartar, and 1/2 tsp. vanilla.
Beat with a mixer until soft peaks form. Add 1 1/2 c. of sugar, one Tbsp. at a time, beating on high speed until very stiff peaks form and sugar is almost dissolved.
Spread onto circles on parchment paper, building up sides slightly.
Bake for 1 hour.
Carefully remove to wire racks.
Remove paper and cool.
Increase oven temperature to 350 degrees.
Spread almonds on baking sheet.
Toast 7 to 8 minutes or until light brown.
Cool and chop coarsely.
Slice strawberries into thirds.
Sprinkle with 2 Tbsp. of sugar and toss gently.
Whip cream on high speed with 2 Tbsp. sugar and 1/2 tsp. vanilla.
Mix powdered sugar, milk, coffee crystals, and 1/4 tsp. vanilla.
To assemble, place one meringue on a large plate.
Place half of strawberries on top.
Drizzle with powdered sugar mixture.
Place another meringue on top of strawberries.
Spread whipped cream on top.
Sprinkle with almonds. Place remaining strawberries on top and around cake.

title: lemon bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, mix 1 1/2 cups flour and
confectioners
sugar;
cut
in butter or margarine until crumbly.
Press
into
lightly
greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake 15 minutes.
In a large bowl, mix eggs, granulated sugar, baking powder,
lemon juice and 3 tablespoons flour.
Mix well and pour over
crust.
Bake
to
30 minutes (until golden brown).
Cool and
cut.
Sprinkle
with
confectioners sugar. Store, covered, in refrigerator.
Makes 24 to 36 bars.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer all items in order listed.
Best made a day ahead.

title: old-fashioned peach cobbler
directions: In heavy saucepan over low heat, combine butter, milk, peach syrup and beaten egg.
In a separate bowl, combine dry ingredients and blend well.
Gradually add dry ingredients to the liquid mixture.
Stir constantly over medium heat until all dry ingredients are blended into the liquid.
Pour the cobbler batter into a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Scatter sliced peaches in the batter.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
To serve, top with whipped cream and sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, sugar, eggs, salt, 1/4 cup margarine, milk and vanilla.
Spoon into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Combine brown sugar, flour, nuts and 3 tablespoons margarine and spread over sweet potato mixture. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: double corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease 9 x 9-inch pan.
Blend all ingredients except corn.
Beat vigorously one minute.
Add corn. Mix well.
Pour into pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cut fruit in small pieces.
Combine flour, fruit and pecans. Beat egg whites stiff but not dry, then beat sugar in.
Add rest and mix well.
Drop by teaspoons and press.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: pear butter
directions: Wash pears and peel.
Cut into squares.
Boil them until they fall apart.
Press through colander to remove seeds and stems. Measure pulp and add 1 cup sugar to each quart of pulp.
Also add 1/2 teaspoon lemon juice to give a pleasing flavor (optional). Add spices to suit your taste.

title: crisp stuffed jalapenos
directions: Slit down 1 side of each pepper; remove seeds.
Do not remove top and stem of pepper.
Stuff jalapenos with 1 shrimp or 1 almond and some cheese.
You may do them entirely with cheese; coat with flour.
Beat egg whites to soft peaks.
In another bowl, beat yolks and add 1 tablespoon flour, salt and pepper to season.
Fold in egg whites.
Gently combine in heavy skillet; heat 1 inch oil to 350°.
Holding jalapenos by stem, coat in batter.
Drop into hot oil to fry, turning once, to golden brown.
Drain on paper towel; serve hot.
Appetizers for 4 to 6.

title: baked vidalia onions
directions: With a sharp knife, cut out a 1 x 3/4-inch cavity in the top of each onion, saving scraps.
Sprinkle each with salt and pepper. Mix butter, Worcestershire sauce, cumin and brown sugar.
Divide among cavities of the onions.
Arrange onions in baking dish. Add broth, wine and reserved scraps.
Bake in center of preheated 425° oven, basting occasionally, for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until onions are tender and
golden.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook rice in water for 7 minutes.
Add milk slowly and stir. Add butter.
Cover and cook on low for 1 hour.
Mix together eggs, sugar, raisins and vanilla.
Pour slowly into rice mixture and blend.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon and sugar.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat well and pour ingredients into pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: broccoli ham casserole
directions: Saute
chopped onion in butter	until
tender.	Add
to soup, cheese, broccoli, cooked rice
and	pimiento.
Mix	well and place in 10-inch greased baking
dish.
Cover
and let set in refrigerator about 8 hours or overnight.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple juice in saucepan; set aside.
Mix nuts, pineapple and marshmallows together, then set aside.
Mix butter, pineapple juice, sugar and cornstarch.
Heat on low, always stirring, until mixture thickens and turns a clear color.
Remove from heat.
Beat eggs, then mix into your sauce.
Let cool, then add 2 marshmallows.

title: lo-cal cabbage dish
directions: Chop cabbage into small pieces; steam for about 5 minutes. Drain and put into a large baking dish.
Brown meat.
Add onions, rice, tomato soup and water.
Bring to a boil; pour over cabbage. Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: sawdust cookies
directions: Roll in balls.
Smash with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: christmas fruit ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the 3 ounce box of gelatin.
Let stand overnight.
The next day, roll into 1-inch balls.
Pour the small box of dry gelatin into plate and roll balls until coated.

title: crimson crab cheese dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese, horseradish, mayonnaise and onion. Let set overnight.
Shape mixture on serving plate.

title: sausage chowder
directions: Cook sausage and onion together and drain.
Add potatoes, salt, marjoram, pepper and water.
Bring to boil and cook until potatoes are done, about 15 minutes.
Add creamed corn and whole kernel corn and milk.
Bring almost to boil again, but don't let boil.

title: punch
directions: Mix and freeze all ingredients.
About 2 hours before serving, remove from freezer.
Then add 3 quarts ginger ale.

title: corn casserole - texas style
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in a greased 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Crumble bacon on the top with a few extra cracker crumbs the last 15 minutes.

title: kansas dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies in food processor.
Put 1/2 of the crumbs in a clean flowerpot.
Mix cream cheese and butter until smooth with an electric mixer.
Mix in the powdered sugar.
Fold in the Cool Whip.

title: gazpacho(cold soup)
directions: Peel and chop (finely) all vegetables.
Combine with other ingredients and chill overnight.
Serve cold with a dollop of sour cream on top of each serving.
Serve with croutons.

title: western lima bean bake
directions: Soak beans overnight; drain.
Cover with boiling salted water and boil slowly 1 to 2 hours until tender.
Drain, reserving bean water.
Lightly brown meat and onion in oil, stirring to break into bits.
Add tomato sauce, bean water, salt, sugar and poultry seasoning.
Place beans in casserole.
Cover with sauce.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 20 to 35 minutes.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water.
Add oil to this.
Pour into flour and mix well.
Store at least 2 hours before baking. Bake at 450° until done.
Dough will keep in refrigerator for 4 to 5 days.

title: white chocolate chunk cookies
directions: Cream butter and shortening; gradually add sugars, beating well at medium speed. Add egg and beat well. In a separate bowl, combine flour, soda and salt; add to butter mixture, mixing well. Stir in vanilla, white chocolate and nuts. Chill for 1 hour.

Drop dough by spoonful 3-inches apart onto lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. (Cookies will be soft.) Cool slightly on cookie sheet; remove to wire rack to cool completely. Yield: 3 dozen.

title: tomato marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour over tomatoes; chill for several hours.
Overnight is even better.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Blend beans until smooth.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Add beans.
Pour into pie shells. Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: ham and cheese biscuits
directions: Combine ham, flour, cheese and baking powder.
Add milk.
Drop batter by heaping tablespoonfuls onto a baking sheet coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 400° for 22 minutes.

title: bubbles
directions: Mix. Wait two hours before using.

title: quiche lorraine a la crab
directions: Spread cheese in bottom of pie shell.
Spread crabmeat on top of cheese.
Sprinkle onion over crabmeat.
Beat eggs, cream, salt and pepper together until yolks are broken.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Cool and slice.
Serve warm, but not hot.
Test for doneness as you would a custard.

title: peaches n' cream pie
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt, pie filling, butter, egg and milk with a mixer until well blended.
Pour in a 10-inch greased pie pan.
Place peaches over batter.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and 3 tablespoons juice.
Beat two minutes and spoon to within one inch of edge of batter.
Mix 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon together.
Sift on top of cheese filling.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: marigold cake
directions: Cream butter with sugar and add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour with baking powder and fold into creamed mixture.
Add grated rinds and marigold petals.
Spoon into prepared 2-pound loaf pan or 2 (1 pound) loaf pans.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 1 hour for 2-pound tin; about 40 minutes for 1-pound. Sprinkle with granulated sugar about halfway through if desired. Cool 5 minutes.
Remove from tin.
Serve just when cool.
Keeps well and can be frozen.

title: fish fillets in sauce piperade
directions: Cook in small skillet vegetable oil, onion and garlic over low heat; until onions are transparent but not brown.
Add green pepper to onions and cook for 2 minutes.
Lay tomatoes over onions and cook until juices have evaporated.
Arrange fish on top of Piperade sauce and sprinkle with basil, pepper and lemon juice.
Bring to simmer, cover and simmer 8 to 12 minutes just until fish flakes. Yields 2 servings.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Cream the butter and vanilla. Sift together dry ingredients and add to butter.
Put in greased 8 x 8-inch pan. Score dough with fork to make a
crisscross design.
Bake until lightly browned.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix dry pudding into pineapple.
Fold in marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill and top with cherries, if desired.
Serve as salad.

title: barbecued brisket
directions: Mix all ingredients except sugar and catsup.
Marinate brisket overnight (double-wrapped in foil).
Put in oven at 200° to 250° for 10 to 12 hours.
Remove from oven and pour liquid into saucepan.
Add catsup and sugar.
Simmer on low heat for 15 minutes.
Serve over brisket.
Enjoy!

title: ribbon salad
directions: Dissolve lime Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water; add 2 cups cold water.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and chill until partially set. Dissolve lemon Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
When dissolved, add marshmallows and stir until they melt down.
Add 1 cup pineapple juice and cream cheese.
Beat until well blended.
Then add pineapple.
Cool and then fold in whipped cream and mayonnaise. Chill until thickened; spoon in a layer over lime Jell-O.
Chill until almost set.
Dissolve raspberry Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water; add 2 cups cold water.
Chill until it starts to thicken; spoon over lemon layer.
Chill overnight.
Do not let the layers set hard before adding the next layer or they will not adhere.

title: lemon-lime jello salad
directions: Combine lime and lemon jello.
Add boiling water.
Let cool a little.
Add cottage cheese, pineapple, salad dressing and nuts. Mix. Let jello set overnight.

title: spanish rice
directions: This is also very good with meat.
If you want to, add 1 pound cooked hamburger to the dish.

title: tuna-salmon casserole
directions: In ovenproof dish layer tuna; mash down with fork.
Add salmon, peas and cream of mushroom soup.
Top with potato chips. Bake in 350° oven until hot (do not dilute soup).

title: pineapple pie
directions: Stir all together and pour into crusts.
This can either be served frozen or chilled!

title: traditional turkey
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Place rack in the lowest position of the oven.
Remove the turkey neck and giblets, rinse turkey and pat dry with paper towels.
Place the turkey breast side up, on a rack in the roasting pan.
Loosely fill the body cavity with stuffing.
Rub the skin with the butter and season with salt and pepper.
Position aluminum foil over the turkey.
Place turkey in the oven and pour 2 cups turkey stock into the bottom of the roasting pan.
Baste all over every 30 minutes with the juices on the bottom of the pan.
Whenever the drippings evaporate, add stock to moisten them, about 1 to 2 cups at a time.
Remove aluminum foil after 2 1/2 hours.
Roast until a meat thermometer inserted in the meaty part of the thigh reads 180 degrees, about 4 hours.
Let it stand for at least 20 minutes before carving.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat in heavy skillet.
Add salt, garlic and pepper. Cook slowly, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce and spaghetti sauce mix.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes. Meanwhile, cook lasagne as directed.
Drain and rinse.

title: grandmother's oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine eggs, raisins and vanilla and let stand one hour. Cream shortening and sugars.
Sift flour, salt, soda and cinnamon into sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Blend in egg mixture, oatmeal and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown.

title: potato chowder(vegetarian)
directions: In a large soup pot, saute vegetables.
Add water, potatoes and seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add tomato puree.
Cover and simmer 15 more minutes.

title: honey bunn cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sugar, eggs, oil and buttermilk and pour into rectangle cake pan.
Mix brown sugar, cinnamon and crushed pecans and swirl into cake batter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: cookie bars
directions: Mix the cake mix, butter, egg and nuts together and spread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix powdered sugar, eggs and cream cheese together.
Pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: pizza di pasqua(easter bread)
directions: Beat eggs well in lg. mixing bowl.
Add milk, salt and pepper.
Melt butter, margarine and oil in small pan on top of stove until warm.
Cool.
In small bowl, dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Mix well. Add yeast to butter mixture, add grated cheese and add all to egg mixture.
Mix well with an electric mixer to blend.
Add flour one cup at a time, using up to 4 cups of flour.
Shut off electric mixer.
Remove bowl and add 1/4 cup of Crisco, using your hands to mix.
Keep adding the remainder of flour using a wooden spoon to mix.

title: marinated beans
directions: Heat oil, vinegar and sugar until sugar dissolves.
Marinate for several hours or overnight.
Serves 4.

title: bacon cheese puffs(may be frozen unbaked)
directions: Trim crusts and cut each slice of bread into 4 squares. Butter lightly if you wish.
Cut bacon slices in two (each 3-inch long). Lay one piece of bread in the center of each piece of bacon. Sprinkle amply with cheese.
Roll up and secure with a toothpick.
Place on rack in a shallow pan.
Scatter on remaining cheese.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 minutes until lightly browned. Serve immediately.

title: cloud biscuits
directions: Mix flour, sugar and shortening until pea-sized crumbs.
Then mix egg and milk.
Combine mixtures.
Knead 3 to 4 times on a floured board.
Cut with 2 1/2-inch cutter, 1/2 inch thick.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Brush top with butter after baking.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix rice with soup in baking pan.
Place chicken breast on top.
Pour rest of soup over chicken.
Bake, covered, at 275° for 2 1/4 hours minimum.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Grease a large casserole dish.
Layer cooked macaroni, shredded Mozzarella cheese, grated Parmesan cheese, mushrooms and pepperoni. Pour spaghetti sauce over mixture and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Spread in pan.
Bake until brown, about 25 minutes. Cut into squares.
Makes about 3 dozen appetizers.

title: pirok(or russian pie)
directions: Line pie pan with pastry.
When steaming rice, add the chopped onion.
When rice is done, mix with canned salmon, including the juice from the canned salmon.
Mix well.
Pat 1/2 rice and fish mixture in unbaked pie shell.
Press quartered hard-boiled eggs in crust; seal edges well.
Cut steam vents in top crust.
Bake 1/2 hour for canned salmon.
Bake 1 hour for the fresh salmon, or until well browned.
Serve as a main dish.

title: spaghetti squash
directions: Boil squash 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove from pan and cut in half. Take out seeds and let cool.
Scoop out spaghetti.
Brown hamburg, onions, salt, pepper, garlic salt, chili powder and sugar.
Drain. Add tomato sauce and simmer for 1 hour.
In large casserole dish, arrange layers of spaghetti, meat and cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: german cole slaw
directions: Bring first five ingredients to a boil and pour over cabbage, pepper, onion and carrot.

title: eggplant dressing
directions: Brown meat in oil; add onion; cook slightly.
Mix all other ingredients with meat.
Put in baking dish.
Grate cheese over and bake 25 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: crab dip
directions: Soften cream cheese in microwave on medium heat for 30 to 50 seconds (depending on firmness of cheese).
Add crab meat; stir. Add mayonnaise to desired creaminess.
Chill.
Serve with Triscuits or crackers of choice.

title: turkey tomorrow
directions: Combine
all
ingredients,
except
potato
chips.
Mix lightly, then
put 2 cups potato chips in mixture and the rest on top.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 375°. Serves 16 to 20.

title: cream cheese spritz cookies
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar.
Beat in egg yolks, vanilla, salt and cinnamon.
Blend in sifted flour (add a little more flour if batter is too wet).
Use cookie press.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Watch carefully.

title: beef stew
directions: Cut beef into inch cubes; roll in flour and fry in shortening, browning both sides.
Put meat in saucepan; add boiling water to half cover meat.
Add bay leaf and seasonings; cover and simmer slowly for 2 hours until meat is tender.
Add vegetables; cook until done.
More seasonings or other vegetables may be added.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Use a pizza pan.
Place refried beans on bottom.
Combine sour cream and taco mix.
Put on top of beans.
Guacamole dip goes on next.
Layer cheese, olives, tomatoes and onions until they are used up.

title: my italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook onion, green pepper, garlic and celery in butter and oil until tender.
Add the other ingredients and cook for 2 to 3 hours on low heat.
This is enough sauce for 1 to 1 1/2 pounds of pasta. After spaghetti is cooked, drain.
Pour sauce over and sprinkle with grated cheese.
This can be doubled and tripled.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Clean potatoes and cut into thin slices to make about 4 cups. Cook and stir onion in margarine in 2-quart saucepan until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is bubbly.
Remove from heat. Stir in milk and 2 1/2 cups cheese.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir for 1 minute.
Place potatoes in ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour cheese sauce on potatoes. Bake, uncovered, in 375° oven for 1 hour.
Mix remaining cheese and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over potatoes.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake until top is brown and bubbly, 15 to 20 minutes longer. Makes 6 servings.

title: yummy oven stew
directions: Cut meat and veggies into desired pieces.
Put in large roasting pan.
Pour in canned veggies and juices.
Put stew mix, salt and pepper in and stir, add water until meat and veggies are covered.
Stir again.
Cover and cook at 350° in oven for 3 to 3 1/2 hours.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crackers, 1/4 stick butter and sugar and line pie plate. Cream together powdered sugar, vanilla, 3/4 stick butter and salt until smooth.
Place creamed mixture on top of graham cracker crust.
Layer bananas.
Drain large can of pineapple and spread on bananas.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: marinated broccoli
directions: Blanch broccoli and cool.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over broccoli.
Refrigerate overnight.
Shake well before serving.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain grease.
Add taco seasoning.
In a large pan, combine chili, corn, tomato sauce, mushroom soup, nacho cheese soup, cream of chicken soup, mushrooms and Ro-Tel; warm. Crush Doritos.
In a large baking dish, sprinkle a few Doritos (enough to cover bottom).
Cover with soup mixture.
Layer with cheese.
Repeat steps until dish is full.
Warm in oven until cheese melts.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, molasses and margarine in saucepan. Bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add soda. Pour mixture over popcorn and peanuts. Mix well. Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Store in airtight container.

title: belly stickers
directions: Thaw bread loaves and make little round balls.
Place into pans and let rise.
Mix the evaporated milk, margarine and sugar together, then pour over top of bread dough.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Chop stems and combine with crabmeat, butter, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Stuff mushroom caps with crabmeat mixture.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Sprinkle lightly with Old Bay seasoning.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Layer in order given in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°, then spread or sprinkle on a layer at a time in the pan. Bake 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: tahitian chicken
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet.
Flour chicken and brown in hot oil.
Meanwhile, mix remaining ingredients together in small bowl. Place chicken, when browned, in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan in a single layer.
Pour soy mixture over chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: eye of the round roast
directions: Salt and pepper eye of round roast.
Preheat oven to 500°. Place roast in preheated oven and bake 5 minutes per pound.
Turn oven off and do not open oven door for 2 hours.

title: custard pie
directions: Heat milk; let cool.
Mix next 4 ingredients.
Add milk slowly and mix well.
Pour into pie shell and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: easy party punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar and water.
Add juice.
Chill or have ingredients chilled before mixing.
Pour over ice in punch bowl. Right before serving, add ginger ale and sherbet.
Serve at once. Makes 50 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: almond tea
directions: Mix tea and cold water.
Mix all ingredients in a large container.

title: banana split salad
directions: Combine Cool Whip and condensed milk in a bowl, beating well. Fold in remaining ingredients as you wish and mix slightly. Chill.
Simple to prepare and very tasty.

title: spinach crescents
directions: Mix all cheeses, spinach and spices well.
Open crescent rolls and spread mixture evenly onto dough and roll into crescents as directed.
Bake about 20 minutes or follow directions on crescent package.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and peanut butter until smooth.
Add 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Stir well.
Blend in confectioners sugar; then add rest of Cool Whip.
Mix until smooth.
Pour into crust and chill overnight.

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve over ice.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Wash zucchini and cut in half lengthwise.
Place in boiling salted water and boil until tender.
Remove from water and scrape out pulp.
Drain well.
Remove sausage from casing and fry until no longer pink.
Combine pulp, sausage, bread crumbs and beaten egg.
Mix gently.
Fill squash lengths with mixture and sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Place in a lightly oiled baking pan. Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: tuna pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain pasta.
Toss pasta and tuna together.
Mix in mayo, cucumber and onion.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Onion salt can be substituted for onion and salt.

title: caramel poke cake
directions: Cook cake.
Poke holes in cake.
Melt caramel squares in 1/2 cup Pet milk.
Pour on cake, then pour Eagle Brand milk on cake. Let cake cool.
Add Cool Whip for topping.
Put in refrigerator.

title: cracker mince pie
directions: Cream sugar and syrup.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into pie shell(s).
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: potato and sour cream casserole
directions: Mix together first 8 ingredients.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix corn flakes and melted margarine and sprinkle on top of potato mixture.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine vegetables, tossing lightly.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour over vegetables and toss lightly. Cover and chill overnight.
Drain well before serving.
Yields 8 servings.

title: coffee cream punch
directions: Stir sugar in coffee.
Chill.
Before serving, mix with whipped cream and vanilla ice cream, cut in pieces, about 2 to 3-inches.
Serves 60 if 1 quart of ice cream is added later.

title: white punch
directions: Mix together.
Add 1 bottle ginger ale at serving time. Serves 25.

title: crazy beans
directions: Mix together and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Can also be cooked in crock-pot for 5 to 6 hours.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt chocolate and shortening together. Mix sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix sugar mixture with melted chocolate.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: ham cheddar biscuits
directions: In a bowl, combine the biscuit mix and milk just until moistened. Stir in the cheese and ham. Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto greased baking sheets. Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown. Yield: 20 biscuits.

title: southern beef ring
directions: Combine everything but the hamburger and mix well.
Add hamburger and mix thoroughly.
Form into a ring in shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until well browned.
Slide ring onto serving platter and fill center with rice.
Serve with gravy.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Shape in loaf or in loaf pan.
Top with bacon strips, and bake for about one hour at 350°.
Let stand five minutes before slicing.

title: prune whip
directions: Cook prunes; remove stones and mash.
Beat egg whites with salt until stiff, but not dry.
Add sugar gradually, beating into whites.
Add lemon juice to prune pulp and gradually beat into egg whites.
Continue to beat until mixture is fluffy.
Pile lightly into individual serving bowls and chill or pour into a greased baking dish set in a pan of water and bake at 300° for 25 minutes. Serve with whipped cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: meat pie
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a bowl, then pat the meat mixture gently into the bottom and side of a 9-inch pie pan.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together and chill.
Serve with a variety of fresh, raw vegetable tidbits.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients except dressing mix, then add 1/2 package of the mix.
Pour into greased casserole dish and top with remaining mix.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat shortening until creamy.
Add sugar and beat until creamy.
Add eggs and dry ingredients.
Fold in strawberries.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: gourmet roast
directions: Let meat stand at room temperature for 1 hour before cooking. Preheat oven to 375°.
Rub meat with seasoning and place, fat side up, in a shallow roasting pan.
Do not cover; do not add water. Cook 1 hour and turn off the heat.
Do not open oven until serving time regardless of length of time the meat is in the oven.
Turn oven on again 30 to 40 minutes before serving time, but reset temperature to 375°.
The roast is now ready to serve.

title: my daughter-in-law's chicken fricassee
directions: Mix 1 cup flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Coat chicken pieces.
Heat a thin layer of shortening or vegetable oil in skillet and cook chicken until brown.
Drain fat.
Reserve.
Add water, onion and lemon juice or herbs (i.e., thyme and rosemary). Cover and cook over low heat, adding water as necessary, 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Remove chicken and keep warm.
Heat 3 tablespoons reserved fat, blend in 3 tablespoons flour.
Cook until smooth and bubbly. Add milk to liquid to make it about 3 cups.
Boil 1 minute.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix kraut, onion, celery, bell pepper and pimento together. Mix sugar, vinegar and oil for dressing; pour over vegetables. Stir well and cover tightly.
Refrigerate.
(Keeps indefinitely.)

title: pasta with shrimp
directions: Cook spaghetti and set aside.
In heavy 3-quart saucepan melt butter.
Cook onions and peppers for a few minutes before adding the shrimp and remaining spices.
After cooked, toss over the spaghetti and sprinkle with grated cheese.

title: christmas rainbow cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on cake box, baking in 2 (8 or 9-inch) pans.
Cool.
Place layers, top side up, in 2 clean layer pans.
Prick each cake with utility fork at 1/2-inch intervals. Dissolve each gelatin separately in 1 cup boiling water; carefully spoon each over one of the cake layers.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Dip one cake pan in warm water for 10 seconds.
Turn onto serving plate.
Top with 1/2 cup of the whipped cream.
Unmold second layer; place carefully on top of first layer.
Frost top and sides with remaining cream; chill.
Garnish with flattened gumdrops, cut to resemble holly leaves, if desired.

title: bacon and blackeyed salad
directions: Cook peas. Combine peas and next three ingredients and stir well. Cover and chill for 3 hrs. Cook bacon until crisp. Crumble bacon. Cook cauliflower until crispy tender. Drain peas and add cauliflower, celery, onions and bacon. Combine 2 tablespoons of bacon drippings, brown sugar, two tablespoons of vinegar and salt in a saucepan. Cook on low until hot. Pour over veggies. Toss gently.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add frozen strawberries.
Let set until slightly set.
Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: chinese ravioli
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Fry sausage until done; remove from pan and drain on absorbent paper.
Drain fat, reserving 1 tablespoon in pan.
Saute onions and celery in fat until tender.
Add water, bouillon cube and snow peas.
Cook for 4 minutes.
Add beef ravioli and stir gently.
Pour into a two-quart baking dish.
Top with sausages and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Garnish with Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Serves six.

title: spinach-tofu lasagne
directions: Cook noodles according package.
Wash and cut spinach. Crumble tofu (drained first) into bowl.
Put in Parmesan cheese and mix.
Set aside.
Cook spinach and mushrooms in skillet until just turning soft.

title: stove top lasagna
directions: Brown hamburg, seasoned with salts, pepper and onions.
Mix 1/4 cup spaghetti sauce and 1/4 cup water with meat.
Spread in bottom of electric fry pan.
Layer cottage cheese and noodles evenly over meat.
Mix the rest of sauce with 1/4 cup water; pour over noodles.
Cook on simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over top of mixture.
Turn off heat and cover 5 to 10 minutes; serve.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Mix cooked meat with the remaining ingredients until hot. Yields approximately 40 to 50 sandwiches.

title: peanut butter delights
directions: In medium pot, cook on medium heat, sugar, cocoa powder, evaporated milk and butter; stir and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat; let cool 1 minute.
Add vanilla, salt, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Stir well and drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Let cool. Makes approximately 50 pieces.

title: grated sweet potato pudding
directions: Beat the eggs.
Add the sugar, mixed with the flour.
Add flavorings and other ingredients.
Bake in 8-inch square buttered pan in a moderate oven until set, about 30 minutes.

title: frozen cocktail salad
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sour cream.
Add sugar and mix well.
Mix in remaining ingredients and put in 9 or 10-inch loaf pan.
Freeze.
Thaw slightly before serving.
Slice and serve.

title: henny penny(hot chicken salad)
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and potato chips.
Place in buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top; add crushed potato chips.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 or 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on and let cool.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Heat ingredients and pour over sliced boiled potatoes.
Bake for 30 minutes at

title: lemon sweet potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Transfer to a buttered casserole dish.
Brush with butter.
Top with lemon slices.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients; stir over medium heat for 3 minutes, or until mixture clings to spoon.
Store in airtight container overnight.
Mix and knead in enough water to make dough stiff. Store in plastic bag in refrigerator.

title: mom's breakfast fritters
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix corn and egg. Add to dry ingredients, stirring lightly.
Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Drop batter by tablespoon into hot oil, one layer at a time.
Fry about 2 minutes each side or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: cherry salad
directions: Boil pineapple and sugar 1 minute and add jello.
Let jell. Add cream cheese (mashed), cream, cherries and walnuts. Refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.

title: grandma's unbaked cookies
directions: Heat butter and milk.
Add sugar and cocoa.
Boil 5 minutes. Add peanut butter, vanilla and uncooked oats.
Stir until blended. Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let set 30 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Let hash browns thaw about 30 minutes.
Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine all ingredients, including melted margarine; salt and pepper to taste.
Spread in pan.
Sprinkle top with corn flakes, old bread crumbs or stale potato chips, crushed.
Bake.

title: no crust pumpkin pie
directions: Grease pie plate. Beat all ingredients; pour into pie plate. Bake in 300° oven for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: sweet potato custard
directions: Melt oleo and marshmallows in Pet milk.
Add mashed potatoes, sugar, eggs, vanilla and flavoring.
Pour in 2 unbaked pie shells. Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 325° to 350°.

title: waverly crunch
directions: Line pan with Waverly wafers (do not crush).
Melt butter and add brown sugar.
Stir and boil for 3 minutes.
Add chopped pecans.
Pour and smooth out over wafers.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Let sit for 10 minutes.
Cut into squares and leave in pan.

title: sesame oil dressing
directions: Shake well; serve at room temperature over fruit salad (apples, bananas and melons).

title: mandie's eggs ole
directions: Beat eggs in bowl.
Add flour, baking powder, cottage cheese, butter, chilies and shredded cheese; mix well.
Spoon into buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Serves 8.

title: broccoli and cheese quiche
directions: For Filling:
Beat eggs and cream; add broccoli and cheese (Cheddar).
Pour into pie shell (prebaked.
Bake pie shell for about 8 minutes before adding filling.)
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until lightly browned and set.

title: stroganoff loaf
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; all beef and mix.
Place half in loaf shape in shallow baking pan.
Make a well in center.
Brown mushrooms and onion in butter or margarine.
Stir in sour cream and remaining salt; spoon into well.
Top with remaining meat; seal.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour; let stand for 5 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: fudge cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Cream butter and sugar; add each egg separately and beat thoroughly.
Stir in flour, chocolate syrup and vanilla.
Bake approximately 50 to 60 minutes at 325°.

title: kamameshi(seasoned rice in an iron pot)
directions: Wash rice well.
Soak in water for 30 minutes, then drain and put in a container for another 30 minutes.
Thinly slice gobo (1-inch long) and put them in water.
Slice the carrots thin. Boil and cut the string beans short.
Cut the aburage in 1-inch squares.
Soak the shiitake in water for 20 to 30 minutes and squeeze them to drain.
Cut the stems off.
Take shimeji out of the bag, separate and wash with salt water.
Mix these ingredients together and cook in a saucepan with 1 tablespoon soy sauce, 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/2 cup soup stock.
Season the eggs with sugar and salt.
Cook in a frying pan and make thin omelets.
Cut in 1-inch pieces.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and set aside.
Heat last three ingredients until melted. Pour this over first mixture. Coat completely and press into a greased tube pan.
Let set, then turn out on a plate and serve.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and dry milk into a bowl.
Cut in peanut butter with two knives until a fine corn meal. Add orange rind.
Combine egg and water; add all at once into flour mixture.
Stir just until mixed.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: baked chicken reuben
directions: Place chicken in baking pan; salt and pepper.
Place kraut over chicken.
Top with Swiss cheese.
Pour dressing evenly over cheese, cover with foil and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Sprinkle parsley, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter crunches
directions: Blend butterscotch chips and peanut butter and stir in cereal. Drop by small teaspoonfuls on wax paper and let set until firm.

title: sweet potato pie
