directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Add margarine and mix with fork until mixture is like cornmeal.
Sprinkle in ice water a little at a time and mix with fork until pastry holds together.
Roll into a ball and cut in half.
Roll out onto an 11-inch circle between 2 sheets of wax paper.
Remove top sheet and turn the piece with the pastry over the pie pan.
Remove paper and mold into place.
Crimp edges and pierce generously with a fork.
Place in refrigerator until filling is ready.
This recipe makes two crusts.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix and pour remaining ingredients into melted margarine.
Bake at 375° until brown, about 25 to 35 minutes.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and white and brown sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Combine flour, oatmeal, soda and baking powder and fold into mixture.
Add vanilla, chocolate chips, raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli following directions on box.
Combine soup, mayo, cheese and onion in a bowl.
Place broccoli in a greased casserole dish.
Pour other ingredients over broccoli.
Mix bread crumbs with 1/4 cup butter.
Spread over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix dried beef with mayonnaise, sour cream, onions, parsley, dill and Beau Monde.
Refrigerate.
Serve inside scooped out rye bread.
Don't cut bread until ready to serve.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper; drain. Add salsa, corn and seasonings. Layer 1/2 meat sauce, 1/2 of the tortillas and 1/2 of the cottage cheese in a 13 x 9 baking dish. Repeat layers, ending with meat sauce. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon pudding
directions: Heat milk. Add bread crumbs.
When cool, add beaten egg yolks and 1/2 cup sugar.
Bake about 1/2 hour at 375°.
Beat egg whites until stiff and add 1/2 cup sugar and the juice of 1 lemon.
Put meringue on top and brown.

title: fried corn
directions: Cook the fatback until fried brown. Take meat from pan of grease.
Add corn, cooking until done, stirring occasionally.
If this is too thin and watery, mix 2 tablespoons flour with enough water that when it is added to corn mixture, it will thicken up some.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Press hamburger into 2 qt. baking dish. Add salt, pepper and chopped onion. Pour celery soup over hamburger. Add peas. Place single layer of tater tots over peas. Bake at 350 degrees for 35-40 minutes.

title: asparagus and pea casserole(second prize)
directions: Put the asparagus in a greased casserole.
Mix the peas
with the soup and pour over the asparagus.
Add a layer of water chestnuts.
Top with cheese. Soak the bread strips in melted butter and put on top of the casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: slow poke cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions of package.
Pour 1/2 of batter into a greased & floured 9x13 in. pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes.
In a sauce pan, melt caramel with butter & milk. Pour over the baked 1/2 and top with chocolate chips & pecans. Pour balance of cake batter over chocolate chips & pecans.
Bake until done, approximately 15-20 minutes.
Cool & serve.

title: carrot and fig salad c.j.s.
directions: Prepare carrots by washing, peeling and cutting into 3-inch long pieces.
Shred carrots in food processor.
Remove shredded carrots; add to salad bowl.
Roughly chop dried figs in food processor until the size of raisins.
Add chopped figs to carrots. Sprinkle brown sugar over salad.
Add vinegar; stir.
Taste for desired balance of sweet and tart.
Let set for 15 minutes prior to serving.

title: italian cake
directions: Cream together oil, sugar, oleo and egg yolks, then add remaining ingredients.
Beat 5 egg whites until stiff, then fold into mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: dill pickle pot roast
directions: Brown meat well.
Add all ingredients to pan.
Bake for 3 1/2 hours at 250°.
Add 1 cup sour cream to make gravy; cook another 1/2 hour.
Can also be done in crock-pot; brown first.
Serve with noodles.

title: navajo tacos
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add green chilies and onion, if desired. Cook pinto beans or use canned.
Prepare the lettuce, tomatoes and cheese as you would for regular tacos and set aside.

title: non-alcoholic margarita punch
directions: In a 4 qt container combine lemonade concentrate, limeade concentrate, powder sugar, egg whites and crushed ice. Mix well. Cover and freeze at least 30 minutes before serving. Spoon 2 cups slush mixture into blender. Add 1 cup of carbonated water. Blend until frothy. To serve, rub rim of glass with lime slice, dip in salt and fill glass.

title: wyoming bean casserole
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or on top of stove for 30 minutes.

title: italian bean soup
directions: About 45 minutes before serving:
Cut ham into 1/2-inch pieces; dice celery, thinly slice carrots, chop onion and dice zucchini. Remove 1 1/2 cups white kidney beans to medium bowl.
With potato masher or fork, mash beans until smooth.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Clean and wash beans.
Soak overnight.
Drain water.
In a heavy pot, heat the bacon fat.
Saute onions until wilted.
Add beans, tomato sauce, salt, pepper, vinegar, Tabasco sauce, red pepper and thyme.
Add enough water to cover beans.
Simmer until beans are semi-cooked, about 30 minutes.
Remove 1 cup of beans, drain and mash or blend.
Return to pot along with ham hocks and cover/cook on low for 2 hours.

title: english muffin loaf
directions: Set aside 1 cup flour.
In large bowl, combine remaining flour, sugar, salt, soda and yeast.
Heat liquids until very warm (125° to 130°).
Add to dry mixture; beat well.
Stir in reserved flour to make stiff batter.
Spoon into 2 (8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch or 9 x 5-inch) loaf pans that have been greased and sprinkled with cornmeal.
Sprinkle tops with cornmeal.
Let rise in warm place for 30 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove from pans and let cool.
To serve, slice and toast.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: salmon pie
directions: Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.
Serve with egg sauce or cheese sauce.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: creamed chicken
directions: Melt oleo.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat until blended.
Turn heat up some and stir in chicken broth and milk.
Bring to a boil and stir constantly until thick (about 1 minute).
Stir in chicken.
Serve over hot biscuits or hot corn bread.
(May boil chicken breast with skin on for the broth and chicken.)

title: triple chocolate sour cream treats
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Use 2 insulated cookie sheets to protect bottoms of cookies.

title: mccormack's choice casserole
directions: Cook noodles for 8 minutes; drain.
Cook broccoli; drain.
Mix cottage cheese with egg.
Prepare chickens in 6 cups water with celery, carrot, onion and 1 teaspoon salt.
Remove meat; save broth.
For gravy mix oleo and flour.
Cook to smooth paste.
Add 1 1/2 teaspoons salt, basil and pepper.
Cook 1 minute.
Slowly add 3 cups chicken broth, stirring until it comes to a boil.
Add other ingredients.

title: black-eyed pea dip
directions: Saute onions on low heat in small amount of butter until tender.
Add garlic and cook a little longer, being careful not to scorch the garlic.
Add cooked black-eyed peas, jalapenos and seasonings.
Blend this mixture in a food processor or blender until smooth.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat with mixer until frothy. Pour into freezer can.
Add condensed milk.
Fill freezer can to the line with whole milk.

title: seafood newburg
directions: Saute first ingredients in frying pan for 15 minutes.
Cook second ingredients in double boiler until thick.
Mix together and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve over rice or pasta.

title: lois' sorghum cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar; beat in eggs.
Add molasses and lemon juice, then blend well.
Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add boiling water and mix well.
Chill thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoons on a greased cookie sheet. Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in a moderate 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen small cookies.
For large cookies, drop by tablespoon and bake 10 to 15 minutes.
It will make 2 dozen large cookies.

title: toadstools
directions: Brown together sausage and onion.
Add soup, milk, olives and mushrooms.
Season with salt and pepper to taste and add a sprinkle of garlic powder.
Flatten bread slices, cut circles out and toast for 5 to 8 minutes.
Place meat mixture into bread cups. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and place in broiler or microwave until heated.

title: ono salad dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender and mix.
Yield: approximately 2 1/2 cups.

title: apple pancakes
directions: Mix all together.
Fry on hot oil on both sides.
Serve with sour cream and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch pan.
Oven temperature is 350°.

title: fruit and cabbage salad
directions: Place oranges, apples, cabbage and grapes in bowl. Beat whipping cream in chilled bowl until stiff. Fold whipped cream, sugar, lemon juice and salt into mayonnaise. Stir into fruit mixture.

title: amish pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil and egg substitute together.
Add pumpkin.
Add dry ingredients, then add apple juice, stirring until just mixed. Pour batter into two greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until it tests done.
The second loaf can be wrapped in foil and kept in freezer for a few weeks.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix well and bake in 3 layers (8-inch pan) in preheated 350° oven about 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: zucchini corn bread
directions: Melt margarine and cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° until light brown.

title: pancake syrup
directions: Bring to a boil.
Cook slowly until syrupy.

title: broiled ranch mushrooms
directions: Place mushrooms in a gallon size ziplock bag. Whisk together oil, water, vinegar and Ranch mix. Pour over mushrooms; seal bag and marinate in refrigerate for 30 minutes or longer.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and butter.
Then add eggs, pecans, salt and vanilla.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes (until center is set).

title: orange taffy
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine first four ingredients.
Cook and stir over medium heat until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to a rapid boil and cook until a candy thermometer reads 245° (firm ball stage).
Add cream and butter, heat and stir until mixture reaches 245° again.

title: frankfurter casserole
directions: Cook bacon, if used, and remove from pan.
Saute onion in bacon drippings or else in a tablespoon of margarine.
Stir in cream of mushroom soup and milk with salt and pepper.
Add boiled potatoes, sliced frankfurters and beans or peas.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes and top before serving with crumbled bacon if desired.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: cookie christmas ornaments
directions: Combine ingredients in a bowl; knead until the mixture is smooth and well blended.
To form shapes, you can roll out the dough to 1/4-inch thick or you can mold the shapes by hand.
Do not make shape thicker than 1/2-inch.
Make hole in top of ornament for string or wire loop.
Place ornaments on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 225° for 2 hours or more, until dry.
Paint with acrylic paints.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: In top of double boiler, place the cup of brown sugar.
Butter the 3 slices of bread with the 2 tablespoons of butter and dice into small pieces.
Sprinkle on top of sugar.
Do not stir.
Add 1 cup raisins; don't stir!
Beat 3 eggs with the 2 cups milk, 1/8 teaspoon salt and the vanilla.
Pour over bread.
Do not stir! Place over simmering water and cook for one hour.
The brown sugar will form a sauce.
Serve hot or cold.

title: party potatoes
directions: Mix together in large bowl; spread into 13 x 9 pan.

title: miniature ham and cheese rolls
directions: Slice rolls lengthwise through center of entire package. Do not break apart. Layer ham and cheese between layers of rolls. Place top section on top. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over roll. Leave uncovered until margarine sets, then cover. Bake, covered, for 15 minutes at 350°. Rolls can be refrigerated 24 hours or frozen until ready for baking.

title: garden chicken and stuffing
directions: In 3-quart saucepan over medium heat, cook celery, onion and carrots in butter until tender.
Add flour; cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually stir in broth and milk.
Cook until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly.
Add stuffing and chicken; toss to coat.
Spoon into 2-quart oblong baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake 5 minutes more to melt cheese.
Garnish with carrot curls and celery leaves.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into baking dish (greased). Cover with 2 cups cracker crumbs and 1/2 stick melted oleo. Cover.
Bake at 450° for 45 minutes.

title: mary redmiles best sugar cookie you ever snitched
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add next 4 ingredients after measuring flour and sifting with other dry ingredients.
Dough will be soft.
Roll into balls about the size of a walnut.
Roll balls in sugar.
Place on cookie sheet.
Mash down with glass dipped in sugar.
Allow room to spread.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix altogether.
Shape into balls.
Add a little extra stuffing if it's too loose.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Can freeze or heat in microwave.

title: homemade hot rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients and let it rise until doubled in size. Work down.
Put in greased pans and let rise until double in size again.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: hot!! deviled eggs
directions: Boil egg with 1 teaspoon salt; when done, put in cold water to cool quickly.
Peel eggs and cut in half.
Remove yolks and place whites on a serving tray, arranged the way you like.

title: corn muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl (with a wire whisk).
Add the liquids; mix quickly with a whisk or fork.
Lightly grease 12 muffin cups; distribute the batter evenly into them.
Bake in a 350° oven until golden brown.
Best served warm.

title: chicken casserole supreme
directions: Preheat oven
to
Shred chipped beef into bottom of a 10 x 12-inch shallow, greased casserole.
Wrap a slice of bacon around
each
half	of chicken breast.
Place chicken on top of beef,
add	pepper.
Blend	soup
with
sour
cream and button mushrooms and
pour over the chicken.
Cover and bake 3 hours on 275° (no salt).

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix all together and pour 1 cup Italian salad dressing on salad.
Mix well.
Stir again before serving.
Best if made the night before.
Serves 12.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix well 1/3 cup soup, beef, bread crumbs, egg, salt and pepper.
Shape into 6 oval patties; brown.
Pour off excess fat. Add remaining soup, ketchup, Worcestershire sauce and mustard. Gradually blend water into flour
until smooth.
Stir into soup mixture.
Pour over patties; cover and cook on low 20 minutes.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: In a small bowl, mix cocoa (level off), plain flour and sugar. Use enough milk to mix dry ingredients.
Put remainder of milk in saucepan and add mixture.
Cook on medium heat.
Stir constantly to keep from burning until thick!
Add vanilla, butter and salt. Great over biscuits or by itself!

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown sausage in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain. Unroll crescent roll dough.
Separate into 8 triangles.
Arrange over bottom and up side of 12-inch pizza pan; seal edges.
Spoon sausage over crust.
Sprinkle with potatoes and cheese.

title: frozen salad
directions: Stir it all up and put it in a 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze. Take it out 15 minutes before serving time.

title: stuffed acorn squash
directions: Halve squash lengthwise, remove seeds and membranes.
Place cut sides down in shallow 15 x 10-inch pan. Add water.
Bake in 350° oven until tender (approximately 1 hour).
Drain water from pan.
Carefully scoop pulp from squash, leaving sturdy shells. Mash pulp and mix well with meat, cheese, celery, margarine, onion, brown sugar, salt, mustard and pepper.
Fill shells. Sprinkle with crumb mixture and bake in same pan at 350° until hot and crumbs are lightly browned, about 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix an shape into balls. Refrigerate 1 hour. Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix the rest of the cake mix with 1 stick margarine (melted) and 1 egg with a fork until well mixed.
Spread in greased pan. Set aside.

title: tater tot dinner
directions: Brown meat.
Drain.
Spread meat in casserole dish; spread mushroom soup over top of hamburger.
Place Tater Tots on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with shredded cheese for the last 5 minutes.

title: pork chops supreme
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Trim excess fat from pork chops.
Place chops in baking pan or dish; salt well.
Top each chop with lemon slice and thin onion slice.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Pour catsup over the chops.
Cover and bake 1 hour; uncover and bake 30 minutes longer, basting occasionally. Makes two servings.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions. Combine all ingredients. Pour in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fruit stuffed pork roast
directions: *Have your butcher debone pork loin roast for you, or debone yourself (directions to follow).

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Blend meal and margarine with a fork until crumbly, add beaten eggs, mix well; add other ingredients.
Bake in a well-greased and floured pan that won't stick.
Bake 45 minutes at 400°.
(I use Teflon cake pan , 10-inch, sprayed with Pam and cook at 375° for 30 minutes.
Just watch
and test for doneness.)

title: wilted lettuce salad
directions: Wash, dry and tear lettuce into bowl. Add sliced eggs and onions.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon from pan and reserve drippings.
Add vinegar, water, sugar, salt and pepper to drippings.
Heat to boiling.
Pour over lettuce and toss. Add bacon. Serve at once.

title: quick fix pickle beans
directions: String and break beans.
Wash and cook until they change their color.
Drain off water and rinse in cold water.
Pack into quart jars, leaving space at top.
Then preheat 8 cups water, 1 cup vinegar and the salt.
Boil and pour over beans.
Seal jars.
Set aside for 10 to 20 days and they are ready to eat.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat until creamy.
Add flour and mace or vanilla.
Put into a greased tube or Bundt pan. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Start in a cold oven.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Heat beans and pour off excess liquid.
Mash with fork. Measure 1/2 cup mashed beans.
Mix butter and sugar well.
Add vanilla, beans, eggs and coconut.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Let stand until cool.

title: cheesy baked hash browns
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients except potato chips.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle with chips. Bake 50 to 60 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: chicken and dumplin's
directions: Make chicken stock by cooking chicken, onion, bouillon cubes and margarine in about 3 quarts water.
Take out chicken and shred it up.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix eggs, cinnamon, oil, sugar, vanilla, baking soda and baking powder. Gradually add flour.
Mix well. Add pineapple, zucchini and nuts.
Mix again.
Pour batter into loaf pans.
Bake 2 loaf pans for 50 minutes.

title: creamy lasagne
directions: Brown meat in a large skillet; drain.
Add onions; cook until tender.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, water, garlic and seasonings.
Cover; simmer 30 minutes.
Combine cream cheese and milk in a saucepan; stir over low heat until smooth.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, layer half of noodles, meat mixture, cream cheese mixture, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese; repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli and next 3 ingredients.
Combine salad dressing with sugar and vinegar.
Toss with broccoli mixture about one hour before serving.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture is clear (about 10 minutes).
Remove from heat; add lemon juice, rind and butter.
Blend well.

title: gayle's soda pop cake
directions: Bake cake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix 1 1/2 cups boiling water and Jell-O.
Chill until syrupy.
While the cake is warm, poke holes in it with handle of wooden spoon.
Pour Jell-O over cake, then pour soda over cake.
Cool.
Frost with pudding, then Cool Whip.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: pumpkin cake squares
directions: Set aside 1 cup cake mix for topping recipe.
Mix together remaining cake mix, 1 egg and oleo.
Press into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pumpkin, 3 eggs, milk, brown sugar and cinnamon together.
Pour over cake mixture.
For topping, mix reserved cake mix, sugar, butter and nuts with a pastry blender.
Sprinkle over top of pumpkin mixture.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour a loaf pan. Mix the flour, brown sugar, baking powder and salt in a large bowl. Add the egg, milk and butter; stir until well blended. Add the nuts. Spoon into pan and bake for 45 minutes. Remove from pan and cool on rack.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix together the ingredients and put in ice cream freezer. Pour regular milk into container until it reaches the fill line. Makes 1 gallon.
Fresh fruit is also good to add.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Set aside 1 cup crushed Fritos.
Combine remaining Fritos with 1 1/2 cups cheese, chili, sauce and onion.
Pour into an 11 x 7-inch or 12 x 8-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Spread sour cream over top, then cheese. Spread remaining corn chips around edges of pan only.
Bake 10 minutes more.

title: microwave chocolate fudge
directions: In a large bowl, mix sugar and cocoa.
Add milk and butter (do not stir).
Set power select at High; heat 4 1/2 to 6 minutes or until butter is melted.
Add nuts and vanilla, stirring until smooth.
Spread into well-greased square baking dish.
Chill until firm; cut into squares to serve.

title: arizona skillet dinner
directions: In a large skillet, heat corn oil over medium-high heat.
Add onion, green pepper, garlic, chili powder, salt and cumin.
Saute 4 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in tomatoes, breaking with a spoon.
Add kidney beans and corn.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Toss with elbows.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 8 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to first mixture.
Fold in grated carrots and nuts.
Put in 3 (9-inch) greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Cut pumpkin into 1-inch strips. Pare off rind and cut in 2-inch lengths. Cook in deep kettle with an old pie plate turned upside down in bottom. (This will keep the pumpkin pieces from sticking.) Add enough water to cover first layer of pumpkin. Bring to a boil and then cook slow about 4 or 5 hours. Place in colander and press pulp through. Measure 1 1/2 cups pumpkin for each pie. Add butter, milk, sugar, egg yolk, salt, ginger, nutmeg and cinnamon. Stir and mix well. Beat the egg whites until stiff and fold in mixture. Add a little bread or cracker crumbs to absorb water. Bake in pie shell(s) at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes. Then raise temperature to 425° until brown spots appear and crust turns brown.

title: scrambles
directions: Place all ingredients in large baking pan.
Mix in oil and salts.
Roast 2 hours in 250° oven.
Stir 4 or 5 times.
I sometimes add a little Tabasco sauce or Worcestershire to the oil.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix all ingredients. Chill a couple of hours.

title: crumb cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients; mix in shortening like fine crumbs.
Set aside 3/4 cup crumbs.
Add eggs and milk; beat until smooth.
Put in 2-greased layer tins or oblong pan.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs over top.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes or until done.
A good breakfast cake.

title: carameled sweet potatoes
directions: Cook and drain potatoes until tender, drain and cool.
Cut in half lengthwise and place in greased baking dish.
Mix salt, sugar and flour and pour over potatoes.
Dot with butter.
Add marshmallows and pour cream over everything.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in microwave and drain.
Cook onion and oleo on medium heat until onion is tender, then add broccoli, soup, cheese and rice.
Mix well.
Pour into a buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: easter eggs
directions: Cream the butter and confectioners sugar. Add milk, salt and vanilla.
Add more milk, if needed.
Add walnuts (optional).
Make into egg
shape.
Melt chocolates together.
Cool a little.
Put in egg. Roll it around until covered.
Cool on wax paper.

title: crock pot stroganoff
directions: Cook the first five ingredients on low all day.
I add the sour cream about 20 minutes prior to serving.
Serve over rice, noodles, or toast as desired.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Saute shrimp in butter until pink. Cut up asparagus and mushrooms and boil 5 minutes.

title: whole wheat not so sweet dough
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine yeast, powdered milk, salt and cereal.
Add 2 cups warm water and stir until yeast and milk dissolve.
Add shortening, molasses, eggs, remaining 1 1/2 cups warm water and wheat flour.
Beat well.
Stir in 4 cups all-purpose flour.
Use remaining 1 1/2 cups flour to add dough while kneading until dough is smooth.
Shape dough into ball.
Cover with damp towel.
Allow to rest on lightly floured board for 15 minutes. Divide dough into equal 4 parts.
To bake just do what each recipe tells you to do.

title: cheesy hash browns
directions: Mix together.
Bake until hash browns are done, about 1 hour, in a 350° oven.

title: hobo dinners
directions: Pat ground beef into 4 large patties.
Put each one on aluminum foil twice as large as the patty.
Slice vegetables.
Put potatoes, onion, carrots and celery on top of patty.
Sprinkle salt, pepper and dash of Worcestershire sauce.
Wrap in the aluminum foil; put on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.
Very tasty.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Rinse and drain sauerkraut.
Mix in the chopped vegetables, then add sugar, vinegar and oil.
Mix together and let stand overnight.

title: chocolate delight(two layers)
directions: Mix with hands in a 9 x 12-inch pan and pat flat.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Top with crushed potato chips or bread crumbs. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: shipwreck
directions: Layer sliced potatoes, onion and beef in baking dish.
Season with salt and pepper and chili powder after each layer.
Lightly stir in pork and beans.
Pour tomato sauce over top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.

title: yeast bread
directions: Stir together the first 3 ingredients and set aside.
In big bowl, beat egg, sugar, butter, salt and milk.
Mix well and add first mixture to the second.
Beat.
Add flour and stir with a wooden spoon.
Add enough flour so the dough won't stick to your hands.
Turn out on floured surface and knead well, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Put in buttered bowl and let rise.
Put in pans and let rise again.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 minutes, then turn oven down to 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 18 rolls or 2 (16 ounce) loaves.

title: chicken crunch
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Bake in a greased casserole dish at 325° for 40 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: granola
directions: Mix dry ingredients thoroughly.
Mix oil, water and flavorings.
Sprinkle gradually over dry ingredients.
Mix well. Spread out on 2 large pans and bake in slow (275° to 300°) oven approximately 1 hour or until golden brown.
Stir often for even browning.
Store in tight containers.
Freezes well.
Yields 6 quarts.

title: indian turkey roll-ups
directions: Warm tortillas for 5 minutes in a 300° oven. Spread each tortilla with 1 tablespoon chutney. Top each tortilla with 2 ounces turkey and roll up. Secure with a toothpick.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Gradually add well beaten egg yolks. Measure flour and sift three times with baking powder.
Add flour and milk gradually.
Add flavoring and add stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in layers at 350°.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix and press in bowl the crushed pretzels, 1/2 cup sugar and melted butter.
Mix and spread on pretzels 1/2 cup sugar, Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Combine 1/4 cup sugar and crushed pineapple; cook with cornstarch.
Mix in pineapple and spread on top.

title: blue cheese pate
directions: Advance preparation:
Cook bacon until crisp; drain.
Crumble; set aside.
In small mixing bowl, beat together cream cheese, liver spread, Blue cheese and sherry until fluffy.
Stir in water chestnuts, onion, olives and bacon.
Turn into small bowl or mold; chill until firm.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Heat margarine over low heat until melted.
Blend flour, dry mustard, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat; stir constantly until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat; stir in milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir one minute.
Stir in sharp cheese.
When blended, add Velveeta to get the right color.
Cook and stir over low heat until melted thoroughly.
Great over vegetables!

title: honeymoon cake
directions: Whip the cream and fold in the dates, marshmallows, nuts, crackers, and cherries.
Put in a 12 x 7-inch pan; refrigerate until molded.

title: basil chicken medley
directions: Heat oil in a skillet; saute garlic.
Add chicken and cook until no longer pink; remove and keep warm.
Combine zucchini, tomato, basil and vinegar; toss to coat vegetables well.
Add to skillet and stir-fry about 3 to 5 minutes.
Return chicken to skillet and heat through. Serve immediately over rice or pasta.

title: evelyn chamberlain's christmas cookies
directions: To well beaten egg whites, add sugar and vanilla.
Combine rest of ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in slow oven (250°) for 30 to 40 minutes or until lightly brown.
Do not overbake.

title: beef biscuit casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and pepper in a large frying pan. Drain. Stir in tomato sauce, chili powder and garlic salt. Simmer. Separate biscuits into ten.
Pull biscuits apart into 2 layers. Press 10 over bottom of a 2-quart casserole dish.
Combine 1/2 cup of the cheese (keep remaining cheese for top) with sour cream and egg.
Mix well.

Remove meat from heat. Stir in sour cream mix. Spoon over dough. Arrange remaining biscuits over top. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until biscuits are golden brown.

title: stewed tomatoes and okra
directions: Remove tip and stem ends from okra; cut okra into 1/4-inch slices and set aside.
Coat a medium saucepan with vegetable cooking spray and place over medium heat until hot.
Add onion and bell pepper; cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add okra, tomato and remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over medium-low heat 15 minutes or until okra is tender, stirring occasionally.

title: cheese hearts
directions: Let butter soften with cheese.
Add other ingredients.
Mix and knead it well.
Roll thin and cut with a small heart cutter.
This is good for a wedding reception.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil spaghetti.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Rinse vegetables in cold water for 2 minutes.
Do not cook.
Mix all ingredients together. Chill overnight.

title: german sour cream potatoes
directions: Chop warm potatoes into bowl.
Add eggs and onion.
Fry bacon crisp and crumble over potatoes.
Retain grease and add salt, pepper, vinegar, sugar and sour cream.
Bring to a boil, stirring to combine ingredients.
Pour over potatoes.
Serve warm or cold. Yields 8 servings.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, salt and celery seed and pour over cucumbers.
Add bell pepper and onions.
Stir every 10 minutes until there is enough liquid to cover.
Put in bags and freeze. May be eaten fresh as a salad.

title: aunt liz's pickles(very crunchy)
directions: Peel and cut out seeds from the cucumbers.
Rinse and soak in lime and 2 gallons of water for 24 hours.
Rinse and soak in alum and enough cool water to cover for 6 hours.
Rinse and soak in cool water for 6 more hours.

title: irresistable peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine peanut butter, shortening, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat until well blended. Add egg and beat just until blended.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix just until blended. Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten slightly in crisscross pattern with tines of fork. Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes or until set and just beginning to brown.
Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet before removing.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt butter and stir in stuffing.
Put half mixture into baking dish.
Mix squash, pepper, carrot, onion, soup, and sour cream. Pour into dish and cover with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: make ahead meatballs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients and shape into 1-inch balls.
Place in pans and bake about 10 minutes or until done. Cool in pans for 5 minutes.
Pack in freezer containers after about 15 minutes and freeze.
Use as needed.
Makes about 3 dozen. I like to double the recipe using 1 pound of chuck and 1 pound of turkey.
Enjoy!

title: crisco pound cake
directions: Beat Crisco, then sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Add cake flour and milk; beat.
Blend in flavoring.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well.
Gradually add milk, baking powder and flour, beating well. Pour into tube pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: talarena
directions: Mix together beef, onion, garlic, pepper, corn, olives, chili powder (minus 1 tablespoon) and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Put in a 9 x 11 x 2-inch pan.
In a separate bowl, mix together Jiffy mix according to directions with egg and milk.
Add 1/2 cup cheese and 1 tablespoon chili powder.
Pour on top of meat mix.
Bake by package directions for corn bread on Jiffy box.

title: fudge
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients for 7 minutes.
Remove from stove. Add peanut butter and marshmallow.
Whip.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet.
Add nuts, if desired.

title: ribar's hungarian supreme
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain off grease.
Add tomato sauce, salt, pepper and garlic salt to taste.
Add paprika.
Set aside.
Mix softened cream cheese, sour cream and chopped onion.
Add water, if needed, to make spreadable.
Set aside.
Cook noodles (not quite done) with salt and oil in water.
Drain.
Rinse with cold water.
Butter oblong dish.
Layer noodles, cream mixture and meat sauce.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle top with grated cheese. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: pepper pot roast(serve with noodles)
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven.
Add meat and brown well. Add onions and saute.
Return meat to Dutch oven; add pepper strips, tomatoes, tomato sauce, celery, bay leaves, salt, thyme and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and bake at 350° about two hours or until tender, basting occasionally with sauce.

title: pizzelles
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, then add oleo and Crisco.
Measure flour, salt and baking powder together.
Mix slowly everything together and drop by teaspoon on waffle iron until light brown.

title: curry vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together and let sit for several hours.
Use as dip for vegetables.

title: shrimp and rice salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix the shrimp, rice, green peppers, onion, celery and pimento together.
In another bowl, combine rest of ingredients and blend together well.
Pour this over the shrimp mixture and toss well.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg together.
Dissolve soda in applesauce and add to mixture.
Add salt and spices and part of flour.
Stir.
Add enough flour to make fairly stiff.
One cup of raisins may be added.
Bake in 350° oven 50 to 60 minutes.

title: angels omelet
directions: Saute bananas in butter until light and golden on low heat. Add a good teaspoon of honey; stir lightly.
Add eggs gently.
Fold over when done.
Serve on platter with a topping of sliced strawberries and powdered sugar.
Serve with muffins and coffee. Don't overcook omelet.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Empty brownie mix and chocolate flavor packet into a bowl.
Add cinnamon, water and egg.
Stir until well mixed.
Stir in nuts and oats.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 4 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Add sugars, oil and vanilla.
Beat until lemon colored.
Add zucchini and dry ingredients.
Add 1 cup chopped nuts gradually.
Raisins may be added, but make sure
you mix them with flour or they will go to the bottom.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Pour into greased muffin tins. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
These are very good rolls for a spur of the moment bread!!

title: oriental pasta salad
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Meanwhile, in saucepan, stir red pepper and oils over medium heat for 2 minutes.
Add honey, soy sauce and salt.
Stir to combine and mix well with cooked spaghetti.
Cover and refrigerate for four hours or overnight. When ready to serve, add chopped cilantro, peanuts and green onions to noodles.
Toss together and place in serving bowl.
Sprinkle with sesame seed and cilantro leaves for garnish.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour pie filling into bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Add pineapple. Sprinkle cake mix over pineapple. Pour margarine over cake mix. Add coconut and sprinkle pecans over top of entire cake. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: apple-marmalade pudding
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Butter a shallow baking dish about 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Peel and core apples.
Slice very thin and spread in prepared baking dish.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Put dish in hot oven while making topping.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour over chicken.
Marinate at least 4 to 5 hours (best if overnight).

title: italian chicken
directions: You will need 1 oven cooking bag, large size (14 x 20-inch).

title: snickers salad
directions: Mix in a big bowl and refrigerate at least 1/2 an hour.

title: brownies
directions: Mix dry ingredients; blend well with melted butter.
Add eggs and nuts.
Bake for 30 minutes at 300° in a greased pan large enough for the batter to be 1/2-inch deep.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: diabetic orange date bread
directions: Cream margarine and add eggs, orange juice, water and Sucaryl solution.
Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture, mixing until blended.
Pour into two greased loaf pans and let stand 20 minutes before baking.
Bake in a 350° oven for 55 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix everything, except dressing.
Put dressing on 1 hour before serving.

title: corn soup
directions: Clean corn and cut off in cream style.
Cut okra in small pieces.
Cut tomatoes in small pieces.
Put water, Crisco, okra and tomatoes in small pot and cook for about 10 minutes.
Add corn, salt and pepper if needed.
Add another 1/4 cup water.
Cook for another 10 minutes.

title: red cream cheese block
directions: Blend crushed fruit, lemon and orange juice.
Place cream cheese block on a serving dish.
Spoon fruit mixture over top. Sprinkle with nuts.
Provide a spreading knife.
Serve with crackers.

title: hot tamales
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll tamales about 1/2-inch thick and 4 to 6-inches long.
Wrap individually in foil, making sure it wraps around 3 times. Twist ends.
Place in boiling water. Cook for 30 minutes.

title: angel cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients in bowl.
Heat the oil in a skillet and cook at 400°.

title: microwave "baked" beans
directions: Microwave bacon; drain and crumble.
Put all ingredients in large bowl.
Microwave on High for 20 minutes; stir every 5 minutes.

title: spinach and linguine casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions; drain.
Combine next 8 ingredients; mix well.
Stir in spinach and linguine.
Turn into a 10 x 6-inch baking dish or 10-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 15 minutes. Uncover and bake 20 minutes more.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: rose fitzgerald's cheese cake
directions: Beat eggs; add cream cheese and 1 cup of sugar.
Beat until well blended.
Put in 9-inch pie plate (pie crust if used) and bake 50 minutes at 325°.
Remove and cool for 1/2 hour.

title: quick and easy sweet and sour chicken
directions: Makes a lot of sauce so there is enough to cover more than 2 pounds of chicken.

title: maple squares
directions: Beat eggs and sugar, then add oil and flour.
Add flavoring and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: salmon cheese ball
directions: Mix well.
Place in refrigerator until of consistency to form into a ball.
Roll in parsley.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, set aside;
Melt in the microwave sugar and vinegar.
Add mayonnaise and whip with whisk. Pour over broccoli just before serving.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and sugar.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture.
Fold in cranberries (cut across once) and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: rolled chicken breasts
directions: Roll each chicken breast half and wrap with a strip of bacon. Secure with a toothpick.
Shred beef and put on bottom of a baking dish.
Put chicken on top and cover with sauce made of mushroom soup and sour cream.
Bake at least 3 hours at 300°.

title: mom's banana bread(yield: 1 loaf or 12 small muffins)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: carolina fig special
directions: Wash and dry figs.
Trim stems and mash.
Combine figs, sugar and gelatin and let mixture stand for 30 minutes to blend flavors. Bring to slow boiling point.
Let cook and stir for 5 minutes. Pour into sterilized containers and seal.
Tastes like "old-fashioned strawberry preserves." Will keep a month in refrigerator without paraffin and up to a year if properly sealed and stored in cool, dry place.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: In a large pot, add meat and water. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer partially covered for about 1 hour or until meat is tender. Skim off any fat and scum that may form from boiling. Next, add all other ingredients, except potatoes and cook for about 1 to 2 hours. Season to taste. Add your potatoes; you can also add spaghetti (about 1/4 of the bag), broken in 3, at the same time as the potatoes.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix together potatoes, sour cream, chicken soup, shredded cheese, onion, 1/2 cup of the butter, salt and pepper.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients except the broccoli.
Fold in broccoli.
Place in greased casserole dish and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Place a ham and cheese slice on each piece of chicken.
Roll up and secure with toothpicks.
In a heavy skillet, brown chicken on all sides in hot oil.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and cover; simmer 10 minutes or until done.

title: chinese egg rolls
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients.
Place 1 heaping tablespoonful of mixture on egg roll and roll up, sealing ends with beaten egg yolk.
Fry in deep oil until golden brown.
Serve with the following sauce.

title: greek salad supper
directions: Mix potatoes, parsley, onion, cider vinegar, oil, salt and pepper.
Chill until ready to serve.
Put on a bed of lettuce.
Mound potato mixture in center.
Arrange around potatoes: tomato wedges, artichokes, cucumber spears, green onion rings, red onion, pitted black olives, diced Feta cheese, shrimp and radishes.
Serves 6.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes; mix all but last ingredient together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Crush potato chips; pour over top.
Bake another 15 minutes.

title: tuna macaroni casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and Cheddar as directed for oven method only use 2 1/4 cups water. Stir in tuna, green peppers and olives. Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Blend butter and garlic powder. Stir in croutons.
Sprinkle croutons on top. Bake, uncovered, for 5 more minutes.

title: steamed squash
directions: Melt oleo in heavy skillet and put in onion.
Cover and let steam until tender.
Cut squash in round thick slices and put in skillet with onion and let steam on low heat.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Use a little water if needed.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together cream cheese (soften) and confectioners sugar. Add peanut butter and mix.
Add milk and mix until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Place in graham cracker crust and refrigerate for 3 hours, until firm.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown beef in a skillet.
Add sauce and oregano.
Heat until bubbly.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Mix together and freeze.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Melt Crisco and let it cool.
Mix Crisco, sugar, molasses and egg.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill for one hour then make 1-inch balls.
Roll the 1-inch balls in sugar and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mustard sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring well.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Serve with fish or even hot dogs (14 or 15 calories per serving).
Good for people watching calories or high blood pressure or diabetic.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Brown ground meat in oleo. Drain. Add other ingredients in the order listed with potatoes added last. Bring to a boil, stirring frequently to keep from scorching. Lower heat and cover; simmer until potatoes are soft, 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chinese vegetable dip
directions: Place peas in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add remaining ingredients on top.
Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Cover with shoestring potatoes.
Bake at 350° for half hour.
Do not overcook; vegetables should be crispy.

title: garlic cheese grits
directions: Cook water, grits, and salt according to package directions. Add butter and 1 1/2 cup sharp cheese.
In measuring cup, beat eggs and milk to total 3/4 cup
Add garlic powder and Tabasco. Stir into grits.
Pour into well greased baking dish.
On top, sprinkle 1/2 cup cheese, then paprika.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: zucchini and peppers with lemon crumbs
directions: *Can be purchased in the herb and spice section of the grocery store.

title: carrot vichyssoise
directions: Peel and cut in several pieces the carrots and peel and cube potatoes.
Blend first 3 ingredients, then put in pan with chicken stock.
Boil gently for 1/2 hour.

title: cream of fresh pea soup with corn dumplings
directions: Combine peas, water, onion, parsley and salt.
Bring to a boil, simmer for 40 minutes.
Puree part or all in a blender.
Add wine, milk, butter and pepper.
Add dumplings, simmer 10 minutes.

title: goop
directions: Gradually add water to cornstarch.
Mix ingredients together with hands.
Goop is done when mass goes from lumpy to satiny texture.

title: buffalo wings
directions: *For hotter wings, use up to 3/4 cup (6 ounces), the amount used in Buffalo.

title: turkey divan
directions: Put about 1/4 of the soup mixture in buttered casserole.
Put the broccoli in, cover it with slices of turkey meat and pour on the rest of the sauce.
Sprinkle the Parmesan generously on the top and bake at 350°, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: winter warm-up beef simmer
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Place onions, bacon and beef in Dutch oven.
Cook over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally, until bacon and roast are browned (8 to 10 minutes).
Stir in vegetables.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover; continue baking (stir occasionally) for
2 to 2 1/2 hours or until beef is fork-tender.

title: french bread with cheese
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add poppy seed, salt, dry mustard, onion and lemon juice.
Cut bread lengthwise and then crosswise into slices but not quite all the way through. Pour butter mixture over cuts and add mushrooms and cheese in between the slices.
Wrap in foil and bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and drain.
Mix tomato sauce with dry spaghetti mix and add this to meat.
Place in casserole dish and cover with sour cream. Sprinkle grated cheese on top of sour cream.
Cover with crescent rolls.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly hot.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Put chicken pieces in pan.
Combine preserves, dressing and soup mix in saucepan.
Simmer over low heat 5 minutes.
Stir.
Pour over chicken pieces.
(Can do this night before.)
Bake uncovered 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburger pie casserole
directions: Cook hamburg and onion until done with salt and pepper.
Add drained beans and tomato soup.
Pour into greased 1 1/2 -quart casserole.
Add the mashed potatoes (which are made with milk and 1 beaten egg and whipped until light and fluffy).
Spoon mounds of potatoes on top of meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Put rice in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Spread onion soup mix over rice; put chicken pieces over soup mix.
Pour cream of chicken soup (combined with 1 1/2 to 2 cans of water) over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: moms apple pie
directions: Peel and core apples slices and cook in 1 cup water till tender.
Drain off juice and add 1 cup sugar, 1/4 cup cornstarch. Cook till thick and clear add back to apples, 1/2 tsp cinnamon, 1/4 tsp nutmeg.
Put in crust sprinkle with coconut and butter.
Bake at 400° till crusts are browned.

title: cheesy onion casserole
directions: In skillet, melt butter and saute onions until clear and slightly brown.
Layer onions and 2/3 of the cheese and pepper into a 2-quart casserole.
In saucepan, heat soup (undiluted) and milk and soy sauce.
Stir to blend.
Pour gently over onions and cheese.
Stir gently.
Top with buttered bread slices.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Take out of oven and push down bread slices into sauce.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and bake 15 minutes more.

title: peanut butter chocolate pretzels
directions: Use a medium glass bowl.
Combine peanut butter and chocolate. Microwave on Medium for 2 minutes.
Stir well.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes; stir well.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes or until mixture is melted and smooth when stirred.
Place 5 to 6 pretzels at a time in melted mixture and carefully turn to coat entire pretzel.
Remove pretzel with fork, tapping edge of bowl to remove excess chocolate.
Place pretzel on waxed paper and refrigerate for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chili con queso blanco
directions: Saute onion in butter; add melted cream cheese.
Add tomatoes, chilies and cream.
Heat slowly.
Do not boil!
Garnish with cilantro.
Serve in chafing dish with tortilla chips.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skins, cool, peel and shred.
In a saucepan over low heat, combine 1/4 cup butter and cheese until almost melted.
Remove from heat and blend in sour cream, onion, salt and pepper.
Fold gently into grated potatoes and turn into greased 2-quart casserole.
Dot with butter.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Cream shortening with sugar. Beat in egg and add yeast mixture; beat until well mixed.
Add salt and flour working in until smooth dough is formed.
Place in the refrigerator in 2 bowls covered with Saran Wrap until ready to use. Roll and form rolls. Let rise for 1 1/2 hours. Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: sicilian meat roll
directions: Combine eggs, bread crumbs, tomato juice, parsley, oregano, salt, pepper and garlic.
Stir in ground beef, mixing well.
On foil or waxed paper, pat meat to a 12 x 10-inch rectangle.
Arrange ham slices on top of meat, leaving a small margin around edge. Sprinkle shredded cheese over ham.
Starting from short end, carefully roll up meat, using foil to lift; seal edges and ends. Place roll, seam side down in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done (center of meat will be pink due to ham).
Place cheese wedges over top of roll; return to oven for 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: crunchy cheese ball
directions: Beat cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth.
Stir in next 5 ingredients.
Cover; chill several hours.
Form into ball; roll in nuts to coat.
Serve with assorted crackers and/or raw vegetables.

title: beef strips with green peppers
directions: Cut meat into 2-inch cubes, then slice very thin for quick cooking.
Place in bowl; add soy sauce, sherry, garlic, sugar and ginger root.
Then let stand for 30 minutes or longer.
Remove stems, seeds and membranes from peppers; cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.

title: asparagus spaghetti casserole
directions: Make cheese sauce with butter, flour, liquid and grated cheese (I prefer sharp cheese).
Add pimentos and diced green pepper. Grease casserole dish.
Put in a layer of spaghetti and layer of asparagus and pour part of cheese sauce over it.
Repeat the layers of spaghetti and asparagus and remainder of cheese sauce. Cook at 350° for about 45 minutes or so.

title: divinity
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients until it forms a long thread. Turn off fire and cool until all bubbles are gone.
Beat egg whites until firm, but not dry.
Add cool mixture to egg whites.
Add vanilla.
Beat until thick.
Add nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Work fast.

title: fudge brownie pie
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, stirring constantly, melt 1/2 cup margarine and chocolate squares.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 cup sugar, 1/3 cup syrup, 1/4 cup flour, vanilla and salt.
Blend well.
Add eggs (also add 1/2 cup chopped nuts, optional).
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: garlic grits casserole
directions: Cook boiling water, quick grits and salt by package directions.
To cooked grits, add 1 stick margarine and garlic cheese.
Beat until cheese and margarine are completely melted. Beat eggs in measuring cup and fill cup with milk.
Add to grits and mix well.

title: side boys
directions: Put each of the ingredients in separate bowls for guests to help themselves.

title: rotel salsa
directions: Mix all together and serve with chips.

title: tempura batter
directions: Beat oil smooth and frothy.
Used for meat, fish, chicken and veggies.

title: creamy tacos
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and serve over tortilla chips.

title: chili dip
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and chili powder.
Drain off grease. Melt Velveeta cheese in crock-pot and add soup, chilies and meat mixture.

title: shrimp party salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water, add iced water and tomato soup.
Stir in celery, green pepper and onion. Pour half into lightly-oiled ring mold or small individual molds.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Cut eggs in half.
Press eggs, cut side down, and shrimp into gelatin mold.
Pour balance of gelatin mixture over shrimp and eggs; chill until set.
To serve, unmold on crisp salad greens.
Makes 6 servings.

title: banana orange salad sherbet
directions: Mix together Jell-O, boiling water and sherbet.
When cool, add oranges, pineapple and bananas.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate until set.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan and cook until thickened.
When cool, pour over top of Jell-O. Refrigerate.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix onions, pepper and carrots.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour over carrots.
Refrigerate overnight.
Drain before serving.

title: minted jello
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup cold water.
Dissolve flavored gelatin and sugar in boiling water.
Add cold gelatin and extract. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and refrigerate.
Cut into squares (may use cookie cutters to cut out shapes).
May use other flavors of Jell-O (omit mint extract if other flavors of Jell-O are used).

title: jello salad with rice
directions: Mix together minute rice with 2 cups of hot water.
Add strawberry Jell-O.
Cool until mixture begins to set.
Add 1 cup of crushed pineapple and 5 ounces of Cool Whip topping.
Add chopped nuts, if desired.

title: pork barbecue
directions: Boil a good cut of pork in water to cover.
Season with onion, salt and pepper to taste.
When soft, shred.
Add enough broth to keep it very moist.

title: country herb roasted chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375° in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Arrange chicken.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients; brush on chicken.
Bake 45 minutes or until chicken is done.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: chocolate pistachio cake
directions: Get all items.
Need ready bowls, flour, egg, mixer and sugar. Remove Amy's doll and clothing from kitchen table.
Measure flour into bowl.
Answer the doorbell.
Wash flour off Amy's hands. Measure sugar into bowl.
Answer the telephone.
Sweep up the flour and sugar from floor and measure out more adding egg and shortening.
Answer the telephone.
Crash!
Clean up Amy.
Sweep up broken bowl and contents.
Give Amy a bath and put her in bed. Wash the floor.
Call the bakery.
Take an Excedrin and lie down.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Add marshmallows and stir until partially dissolved.
Add pineapple and orange sections that have been cut into bite-size pieces.
Cool mixture, then fold in Cool Whip and sherbet.
Congeal before serving.

title: fancy fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients. Chill before serving.

title: choco-dot pumpkin cake
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Add pumpkin, oil and bran.
Mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients, mixing only until combined.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread evenly in tube or Bundt pan, ungreased or lightly sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 10 minutes or until cake tests done with a toothpick inserted near center.
Cool completely before removing from pan.
Serves 16.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in an ungreased pan at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients but 2 cups cornflakes and 1/2 cup melted butter in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Combine cornflakes and 1/2 cup melted butter and spread over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yum!

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Make a day ahead.
Stir several times between making and serving.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook macaroni as package label directs. Drain.

title: chicken upside-down pie
directions: Reserve 2/3 cup gravy.
In a saucepan, combine remaining gravy with mushrooms, olives and pepper; stir in chicken.
Bring to boiling.
Turn into shallow 8 or 9-inch round baking dish.
Add sage to biscuit mix.
Prepare biscuit dough according to package directions, but use the 2/3 cup reserved gravy for liquid.

title: butterscotch supreme
directions: Mix flour, 1 cup pecans and melted butter.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: dream salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except blueberries and chill overnight. Add blueberries just before serving.
Serves 4.

title: scalloped potatoes in a hurry
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
In pan, add soup and 1/2 can milk. Heat until smooth.
Place potatoes in casserole alternately with onion.
Add soup and cover.
Bake at 350° in oven for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Remove cover last 20 minutes.
(May substitute cream of mushroom soup.)

title: strawberry yogurt mold
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Press in 9 x 13-inch (glass) pan; save a little to sprinkle on top.
In saucepan, heat sugar, water and gelatine just until dissolved.
Mix in sour cream, yogurt and vanilla.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in Cool Whip and fruit.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with graham cracker crumbs if desired.
Top with whole berries. (You may use peaches or blueberry yogurt.)

title: margaritas
directions: Mix lime crystals and water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight.
Makes just over 2 quarts.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix ingredients except paprika together.
Lay chicken pieces on top.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika and bake uncovered at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.
Remove from oven and cool 5 minutes.

title: pasta and olive cocktails
directions: Drain jar of olives and set-aside.
Place pastrami on top of ham and slice into 1/4 inch strips.
Roll meat slices one at a time and then take a toothpick and alternate meat, olive and pasta.
Place all toothpick cocktails in a zip lock bag and drizzle Italian dressing over them.
Refrigerate 1 hour or until ready to serve.

title: peach custard pie
directions: Place
peaches,
round	side
up, in pie shell. Mix the sugar, butter
and eggs.	Pour this mixture over the peaches. Sprinkle with
cinnamon
and
nuts.	Bake 15 minutes in a hot oven of 425°. Reduce the heat to 325° and continue baking for another 45 minutes until the custard is done.

title: confetti beans and rice salad(serves 8)
directions: Using package directions, cook enough brown rice to make eight cups, then place in a shallow pan in the refrigerator to cool.

title: gingered ham slices
directions: Mix all together and pour over ham.
Let set at least 4 hours. Cook on grill or in oven.

title: fat-free carrot muffins
directions: In a medium bowl, combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt, baking soda, baking powder and ginger.
In a large bowl, mix shredded carrots, yogurt, egg substitute, applesauce, raisins, brown sugar and vanilla extract.
Stir until well-blended.
Stir flour mixture into carrot mixture just until flour is moistened.
Spoon batter into 6 ounce brioche pans or jumbo muffin pan cups that have been sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center of each muffin comes out clean.
Cool muffins in pans on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Remove muffins from pans.
Cool slightly on wire racks. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar, if desired. Makes 8 large muffins.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix all and allow to almost set.

title: strawberry dream pie
directions: Mix pudding, jello, water, lemon juice all together in a pan and bring to a boil.
Put mixture into a bowl and refrigerate to thicken.
Once thickened add the cool whip and sliced strawberries and mix together.
Pour into pie shell and chill 1 - 2 hours.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Combine all ingredients (except 1/2 of the cheese) in a large bowl and stir well.
Pour into casserole dish; cover with remaining cheese and bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, chill and serve with vegetable platters.

title: microwave peanut butter(makes 1 pound)
directions: Stir sugar and corn syrup in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Microwave on High for 4 minutes. Stir in peanuts or mixed nuts. Microwave on High 3 to 5 minutes until light brown.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Microwave on High 1 to 2 minutes. Add baking soda. Stir until foamy.
Pour onto a lightly greased cookie sheet. Cool, break and eat.

title: shamrock rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine potatoes, shortening, sugar, salt and hot milk.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast and egg. Stir in 2 cups of flour; beat well.
Stir in the remaining flour or enough to make a soft dough.
Knead on lightly floured surface until smooth and elastic (6 to 8 minutes).
Place in lightly greased bowl.
Cover, let double (about 1 hour) in warm place. Punch down.
Shape in ball.
Cover and let rest 10 minutes. Form rolls (clover are the best).
Let rolls rise until almost double. Bake 10 to 12 minutes in 400° oven.

title: peach crisp
directions: Sprinkle granulated sugar into an ungreased pie plate. Arrange peach slices over sugar.
Mix flour, brown sugar and cinnamon; cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse corn meal. Spread over peaches and bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until topping is browned.
Serves 4.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: pineapple millionaire piegroves, texas
directions: Cream powdered sugar and margarine.
Add egg, salt and vanilla.
Mix until light and fluffy.
Spoon mixture evenly into pie shells; cool.
Whip cream until stiff, blend with pineapple and nuts.
Spoon on top of egg mixture and chill thoroughly. Makes 2 pies.

title: molasses ginger cookies
directions: Cream the shortening with sugar, salt, cinnamon, cloves and ginger.
Add beaten egg and molasses.
Sift the flour with baking soda.
Mix well.
Form into balls (about 1 teaspoon) and roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and press to pan with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 300° for 8 to 10 minutes.
They rise up and then flatten out.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend milk and cream cheese until smooth.
Add other ingredients.
Freeze solid.

title: kool-aid play dough
directions: Mix ingredients.
Add 1 cup boiling water.
Stir together. Knead mixture until it forms soft dough.
Stores a long time in covered container.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box using whole eggs.
Bake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
While hot, prick all over with fork.
Mix Eagle Brand and cream of coconut.
Pour over cake while hot.
Let cool and put in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Spread with Cool Whip and sprinkle coconut over top.

title: orange-cranberry wreath
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and baking soda in large bowl.
Make a well in center.
Add eggs, orange juice and margarine, stirring just until blended.
Add cranberries.
Stir. Spread batter in greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.

title: crab in cheese sauce
directions: Saute
crab
meat in skillet with the butter.
In large saucepan
combine
Cheddar	cheese	soup, Cheez Whiz and milk. Stir over medium high heat until smooth.
Reduce heat; stir in crabmeat
and
let simmer about 10 minutes.
Serve over toast. Our family prefers rye pump bread or seedless rye.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar, cocoa and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time. Mix well.
Add flour, salt and vanilla.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 300° to 325°. When done, spread marshmallows on top.
Cool and spread frosting over marshmallows.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix onions and cucumbers and put in jar.
Mix remaining ingredients and heat until dissolved.
When cool, pour over pickles.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: easy egg custard
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar gradually, margarine, vanilla, milk, then flour.
Pour into cups or glass pie plate.
Put in cold oven at 325° until done, about 1 hour.

title: hidden valley pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: texas pecan cake
directions: Cream butter in a large mixing bowl; gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix first layer and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: stromboli
directions: Roll dough into a rectangle, put on sauce, sausage and other ingredients on rolled out dough.
Fold corners into middle of dough to enclose ingredients.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 45 minutes.

title: fillo dough dessert shells
directions: *Filling can be your favorite pudding, cooked apples, well drained peaches/cooked fruit of any kind.
Then you can top the filling with Cool Whip, whipped cream or a glaze.

title: buttermilk meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef and egg.
Add remaining ingredients, except flour, in order listed (buttermilk, ketchup, salt, pepper, onions, bread crumbs, mustard and poultry seasoning); mix well.
Form into loaf; place in baking pan.
Rub small amount of flour on top of loaf.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 45 minutes, or until done.

title: punch
directions: Mix all juices.
Cut up oranges and lemons.
Add to mixture. If you have a mold, freeze some in a ring to add to punch.
Can be made several weeks ahead of time and frozen.
Add Sprite or ginger ale when ready to serve.
If desired, add peach sherbet.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Place day
old,
room
temperature
eggs in pan of cold water, heavily
salted,
over
high heat for about 10 minutes. Turn down to
low,
barely
bubbling.
Heat for additional 10 minutes. Remove
from
heat.
Leave
eggs in hot water.
Take out 1 egg
at a time and crack shell.
Run under cold water to cool shell.
This method usually allows shell and top layer of egg to
come
loose easier and leave eggs whole.
Cut eggs in half.
Set
whites aside.
Place yolks, onion, mustard, salad cubes, mayonnaise
and seasonings into bowl; mix well.
If too dry, use
salad
cube vinegar
to thin.
Place in egg whites. Sprinkle with paprika and sliced olives.

title: delicious baked beans
directions: Brown meat, pepper and onion.
Drain excess grease.
Stir in beans, molasses, ketchup and mustard.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Add zucchini, flour, salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add nuts.
Bake in greased loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cranberry congealed salad
directions: Combine cranberries and sugar and set aside.
Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Add cold water, lemon juice, cinnamon and allspice.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in cranberries, nuts and orange.
Put in a mold.
Chill 4 hours.
To unmold, place in hot water for a few seconds.
Shake slightly.
Place on chilled platter.

title: healthy meat loaf
directions: Pre-heat oven to 350 degrees.
Coat two 8 1/2 X 4 1/2 loaf pans with non-stick cooking spray.
Mix ingredients in a large bowl, reserving 1/2 cup of the pasta sauce.
Form loaves in pans and brush with reserved sauce.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: sugar cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pie shell, in saucepan.
Cook over medium to high heat, stirring constantly, with wire whisk.
Cook until it thickens, about 1/2 minute.
After boiling, be careful not to let burn.
Pour into baked Pet-Ritz deep dish pie shell. Sprinkle lightly with cinnamon.
Let cool for 15 to 20 minutes, then refrigerate for at least 2 hours before serving to set.

title: rice sausage casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions on box.
Brown almonds in 1/2 stick butter.
Brown together sausage, onion and garlic.
Mix rice and sausage, while hot, with other ingredients, except crackers and 1 stick of butter.
Place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Crush Ritz crackers.
Toss with 1 stick melted butter. Sprinkle over top.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350° until bubbly and crackers are browned.

title: eggplant casserole(argentina)
directions: Peel eggplant; slice and put in pan with lid with oil, onion, crushed garlic, salt, pepper and sugar.
Cook over medium heat, covered, until all eggplant has changed color (20 to 25 minutes). Peel and chop tomatoes and set aside.
In casserole, put layer of eggplant, a layer of grated cheese and 1 tablespoon tomato.
Top last layer with catsup and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: karo pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding nuts last.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked crust and bake in 450° oven for 10 minutes. Reduce heat and continue baking at 350° until a knife blade inserted in center comes out clean.

title: six layer chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter, adding sugar until creamy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Fold in sifted dry ingredients, alternating with milk, beating until smooth.
Add vanilla and almond extract.
Bake in 9-inch pans at 325° for approximately 12 minutes.
Use approximately 6 heaping tablespoonfuls of batter to each pan; makes 6 thin layers.

title: lighter fresh tomato quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Use tomatoes held at room temperature until fully ripe; cut 1 tomato into 1/4-inch thick slices for garnish; set aside.

title: peanut butter roll
directions: Cook sugar, water, salt and syrup until it forms a hard ball in cold water.
Pour into 3 beaten egg whites and beat until creamy.
Add 1/2 tsp. vanilla.
Spread on buttered foil or dampened cloth. (I use buttered foil.)
Let set a few minutes, spread with peanut butter, roll up into a roll.
After it is cool, slice into desired thickness.
Refrigerate.

title: sausage-bean chowder
directions: Brown sausage in Dutch oven, stirring to crumble; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients; bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.
Remove bay leaf before serving.
Yield:
3 quarts.

title: bean soup
directions: Combine ingredients and cook over low heat for about 4 hours.

title: n. c. cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar and baking powder. Beat until mixed.
Chop crackers and nuts.
Pour in egg white mixture and mix.
Put in greased pie plate. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Set this aside.
Combine sugars and shortening, creaming well.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture and mix well.
Stir in oats and chocolate chips.
Add chopped nuts.
Bake for 12 to 14 minutes at 350°.

title: german apple cake
directions: Mix together by hand and pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: thanksgiving fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Keeps well for a week.

title: hanky pankies
directions: In large pan, brown the beef and sausage.
Drain the grease. Add oregano and red pepper; stir the ingredients in the pan well.

title: oyster stew
directions: Blend flour, seasonings and 2 tablespoons water in a 3-quart soup kettle.
Add undrained oysters and butter; simmer over very low heat for 3 to 4 minutes, until edges of oysters curl, stirring gently.
Add scalded or hot milk; remove from heat and cover.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Reheat briefly.
Top servings with pats of butter.
Serves 4 or 5.

title: skillet burgers
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and celery until meat is browned; drain off fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, water, pepper sauce, salt, monosodium glutamate and chili powder.
Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: icing for apricot jello salad
directions: Mix pineapple juice, flour, sugar and eggs in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Cook until thick.
Add cream cheese; let cool completely before adding whipped cream.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together and cook in an uncovered casserole at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: barbecue pork chops
directions: Brown chops on each side.
Mix Coca-Cola (must be Coke), ketchup and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over chops and simmer 30 to 35 minutes.
Sauces will thicken.
Double recipe for larger quantities.
Can use this sauce with spareribs and chicken.
Cook spareribs and chicken halfway through and then add sauce.

title: no bake oatmeal bars
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add wet ingredients and sugar until dissolved.
Add dry ingredients.
Spread mix in 9-inch baking pan coated with vegetable spray.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Cut into squares.

title: healthy potato skins
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Reconstitute the "butter" granules according to the directions on the package.
Cut each potato in half.
Scoop out the center, leaving about 1/4-inch of potato on the inside of each skin.
(Use leftover potato to make Shepherd's Pie.)
Cut skins into quarters.
Dab liquid butter substitute onto the white side of each potato skin.
Sprinkle with garlic powder and pepper, if desired.
Place prepared skins, skin side down, on a baking sheet.
Bake 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Turn skins over and bake another 5 minutes or until crisp.
Serve immediately.
Serves 12; 4 per serving.

title: bulhao pato clams
directions: Dispose clams in recipient.
Cover with cool water and salt (for 2 to 4 hours) to remove sand.
In a pan mix olive oil and crushed garlic.
Cook until lightly browned.
Remove from heat. Add clams previously washed with cool water.
Cover pan and let clams open.
Chopped parsley and slices of lemon for garnish.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix and refrigerate in bowl.
Unmold and surround with chips or crackers.

title: heavenly fruit
directions: Drain
peaches in colander.
Add dry instant pudding to peach juice.
Mix thoroughly using a wire whisk.	Pour liquid back over fruit.
Mix lightly.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: squash puppies
directions: Combine meal, flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Beat egg and milk together; combine with dry ingredients.
If mixture is too thick, add small amount of milk.
Stir in squash.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot, deep fat.
Drain on paper towels.
Serves 6.

title: my mothers spaghetti
directions: Melt butter in saucepan. Cut up onion and add to pan. Saute until tender. Add ground chuck. Add soup; add sauce; add rest of ingredients. Cook over low heat. Simmer until heated through. Sprinkle parmesan on top. Serve with cooked pasta of choice. Makes 2 large "restaurant style" servings.

title: corn relish
directions: In a large saucepan, combine celery, peppers, onion, sugar, vinegar, 2 cups water, salt and celery seed.
Bring to boiling; boil, uncovered, 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Blend flour, mustard and turmeric with 1/2 cup cold water; add with corn to boiling mixture.
Return to boiling, cook and stir 5 minutes.
Pack loosely while boiling hot into hot pint jars; leave 1/2 inch headspace.
Adjust lids.
Process in boiling water bath 15 minutes. (Start counting time when water boils.)
Makes 7 pints.

title: hawaiian drop cookies
directions: Mix all together, except pineapple and coconut.
Add pineapple and coconut.
Drop on cookie sheet, and bake at 350° for approximately 15 minutes or until slightly brown.

title: copper pennies
directions: Combine soup, vinegar, oil, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and salt until smooth.
Blend well.
Pour mixture over pepper, onions and carrots.
Toss lightly; chill overnight.
This will keep several days.
(The leftover sauce makes a great salad dressing.)

title: roast beef
