directions: Put the roast in a pan and stir it.
Then put it on a plate and eat it up with a spoon.
You eat some potatoes on a fork.

title: german slaw
directions: Shred in food processor. Pour sugar over this and let stand until dressing is made. Heat dressing ingredients to rolling boil. Pour over cabbage mixture. Cover and keep in refrigerator overnight. Keeps well.

title: chocolate butterscotch chip nut cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large mixing bowl, combine butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla extract; beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate and butterscotch chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded measuring tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 11 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: bob's fudge
directions: Put sugar, cocoa, milk, water and margarine in 2-quart kettle. Stir until thoroughly mixed.
Cook to 234° to 236°; remove.
Add vanilla.
Set in pan.
Do not stir until cooled.
Use cold water to cool rapidly.
When you can touch bottom of pan with hand, add chopped or whole nuts.
Beat until it first loses its gloss. Immediately pour onto wax paper and spread ad your pour, or you can pour it in greased pan.
For higher altitudes, the temperature must be adjusted.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Melt margarine and mix with stuffing.
Set aside.
Drain vegetables and chestnuts, reserving liquid.
Mix vegetables, chestnuts, onion, mayonnaise and cheese.
Add liquid as needed, approximately 1/2 cup.
Pour in a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish. Cover with stuffing.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 30 minutes.

title: old fashioned sandwich spread
directions: Chop up all vegetables very fine.
Place in a pot and add boiling water to cover.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Drain.
Add vinegar, brown sugar and salt.

title: chicken liver casserole
directions: Cut chicken livers into 1-inch pieces.
Melt butter in large skillet.
Dip chicken liver pieces in seasoned flour.
Fry in melted butter until brown.
Remove and drain on paper towel.
Saute onion in remaining butter.
Mix in large bowl, rice, soup and milk.
Add onion, chicken livers and parsley; mix well.
Pour into buttered casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cherry pineapple pie
directions: Bring to a boil the pie filling, pineapple, sugar, cornstarch and coloring.
Take off heat and add the jello.
Put in refrigerator to cool.
Dice the bananas and add them along with the nuts to the filling and fill the pie shells.
Add whipped topping or Cool Whip to the tops.
Sprinkle with a few more chopped pecans.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine and bring to a boil.
Pour on meat.
Will do two chickens.
Can be stored in refrigerator for several weeks.
Good on any meats!

title: hot sauce
directions: Cut up and mix together.
Cook for 2 hours and put in hot jars to seal.

title: chicken, red beans and rice chili
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven over medium high heat.
Add chicken; cook 5 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned, stirring frequently. Add onion.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes or until onion is crisp-tender. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium; cover and cook 20 to 40 minutes or until rice is tender and chicken is no longer pink.
Makes 9 (1 cup) servings.

title: congo squares
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Melt shortening.
Add brown sugar.
Mix well and add eggs (one at a time), beating well after each one.
Add dry ingredients, nuts and chocolate chips. Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; toss gently.

title: steak au poiure
directions: Crush peppercorns in pepper mill.
Press pepper into both sides of meat with your hands.
Cover with waxed paper or plastic wrap and let stand 1 to 3 hours refrigerated.
Put oil and butter into heavy skillet on medium-high heat until butter begins to sizzle.
Saute steak 3 to 4 minutes on a side until rare to medium-rare steaks.
Remove to heated platter and keep warm while you prepare sauce.

title: copy pop
directions: Combine butter, syrup and sugar; cook on high heat 9 to 15 minutes.
Stir every 3 minutes.
When done (hard crack stage), stir in vanilla.
Pour over popcorn in a thin stream; stir well.
Butter bowl before mixing.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Follow cake box directions.
Pour into three 9-inch greased and floured pans.
Bake; then cool.

title: dinner in a dish
directions: Brown hamburger meat in a skillet.
Slice onion over browned hamburger, then slice potatoes over that.
Add green beans, including liquid, on top.
Cook over low heat until potatoes are done.
Serve in skillet.

title: jan's "night at the races" chili
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain off grease.
In large pot, mix together Chili-O mix, tomato sauce and chili beans.
Strain whole tomatoes and add to pot.
Mix and stir while simmering 40 minutes (do not get too hot, will stick to bottom of pot).
Garnish each dish with cheese or condiments to be added as liked (onions, cheese, salsa or sour cream).

title: caramel apple cake
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar. Bake in tube pan at 350° (do not preheat) for 1 hour.

title: beef-vegetable-rice soup
directions: Brown beef in large saucepan.
Add water and bring to a boil. Lower heat; simmer 20
minutes
(covered) or until meat is almost tender.
Stir in
tomatoes with their liquid, breaking up chunks with spoon.
Add
bouillon,
pepper,
thyme
and marjoram.	Simmer 1 hour.
Add carrots, celery, onion and rice for the last 30 minutes of cooking.

title: crepes
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk, eggs and vanilla.
Mix or beat thoroughly.
Cook in melted butter.
Add a small amount of butter to pan.
Add some batter and roll around to spread evenly.
Turn once.
Serves 4.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel and slice potatoes thin and parboil with salt for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Add soup and milk.
Add grated onion.
Place potato mixture in greased baking dish.
Top with cheese and paprika.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla, eggs and chocolate.
Stir in flour slowly.
Add nuts.
Bake for 35 minutes.

title: fruit compote
directions: Combine all juices with dry pudding.
Add fruit and chill. Before serving, add sliced bananas and sprinkle with coconut and strawberries.

title: mimi's southern dump cake
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl and mix by hand.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes, longer if needed.

title: pecan log roll
directions: Combine Marshmallow Creme, sugar and vanilla. (Add sugar until mixture is stiff enough to shape into logs. May not need the whole pound.) Shape into 4 x 1-inch rolls. Chill for 2 to 3 hours. Combine caramels and water in double boiler and melt. Dip rolls into melted caramel and roll in pecans. Chill for 1 hour, then cut into slices.

title: glazed chicken breasts and rice
directions: Combine
teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper and flour. Dredge
chicken
breast
with flour mixture.
Brown on both sides in oil.
(Use Dutch oven.) Add consomme, cover and cook 15 to 20 minutes.

title: old fashion bread pudding
directions: Place bread crumbs in 1 1/2 quart baking dish.	Mix the remaining ingredients together and pour over the bread crumbs. Dot with
2 tablespoons more of butter.
Place baking dish in larger pan
and pour 1 to 1 1/2 inches of hot water in larger pan.
Bake at	350°
for
minutes	or
until silver knife inserted
comes out
clean.
Serve warm with sauce on whipped cream
(better
if milk is heated before adding other ingredients).

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: gingerbread cookie cut outs
directions: Mix well shortening, sugar and molasses.
In another bowl, mix remaining ingredients together well.
Pour flour mixture into molasses mixture.
Chill dough 2 to 3 hours.
Preheat oven to 370°.
Lightly grease baking sheet.
Divide dough into 3 parts. Put two parts back in refrigerator until ready to use.
Roll dough out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Use any cookie cutter; cut and place on baking sheet.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: barbecue shrimp
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
in large pot.
Add shrimp in shell and cook no more than 20 minutes.

title: pineapple lime ring
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add cold water and lemon juice.
Gradually add gelatin to cream cheese, mixing until blended.
Chill until thickened, but not set; fold in marshmallows, pineapple and nuts.
Pour into 6-cup ring mold; chill until firm.
Unmold onto serving plate.
Garnish with flaked coconut and Kraft Funmallows mini marshmallows, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fresh orange cake
directions: Mix softened butter and
cup
sugar in a bowl; add eggs and grated rind from
orange.
Mix well; add flour and baking powder.
Mix well and
add juice from 1 orange and pour into well-buttered 8-inch
pie
plate.
Place
in oven at 375° for 4 minutes;
reduce heat
and
bake
at
for 25 to 30 minutes longer.
As soon as
cake is baked, put it on a plate. While still warm, pour over
it the juice of the two remaining oranges, with 1/2 cup sugar that has been dissolved.

title: fudge icing
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients together until hot, then stir in the 2 cups of powdered sugar and vanilla.
Pour on cake rapidly and spread.

title: summer tea
directions: Place the tea bags in boiling water.
Let steep until water is cool.
Mix sugar, thawed orange juice, thawed lemonade and 10 cups cold water together.
Stir in tea.
Mix all well.
Refrigerate. Makes 1 gallon.

title: lemon icebox pie(club member: brandi cook)
directions: Mix 3 egg yolks with 1 can condensed milk. Squeeze the juice of the 3 lemons into the mixture slowly. Pour into pie crust.

title: refrigerator cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package; then pour batter into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at temperature and time as directed on package. Remove cake from oven and let cool.
With a meat fork, poke holes all over top of cake.
Mix Jell-O with 3/4 cup boiling water and 1/2 cup cold water.
Pour Jell-O mixture into holes on cake.
Cool cake in refrigerator. Beat instant pudding, Dream Whip, milk and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla until thickened.
Place topping on cool cake.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients well and add 1 can tomato soup (10 3/4 ounce) plus 1/2 can water.
Stir until smooth and add 1 cut up chicken.

title: crabmeat warfield
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake in a medium size casserole dish for about 40 minutes until golden brown.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in oleo.
Add all other ingredients and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Double this recipe to fill 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: orange honey glazed chicken
directions: In pie plate, place bread crumbs; coat chicken.
In large skillet, heat oil and brown chicken on both sides.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients, except onion; blend well.

title: potato soup
directions: In large pan, saute onion and celery in butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook on low heat until potatoes are cooked.
Stir frequently.

title: eggplant souffle
directions: Peel
eggplant
and
cut into 1/2 inch slices.
Cook in boiling
water 15 minutes, until tender.
Drain well and mash. Add eggs, cream, bread crumbs, onion, salt, pepper and cheese. Blend well.
Pour
into
greased
1 1/2 quart casserole dish. Combine butter
and
cracker
crumbs.
Sprinkle
over
top of casserole. Bake
at
350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Crumble Blue cheese into other ingredients.
Stir thoroughly and store in refrigerator.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix cooked macaroni and all other ingredients well.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hot dog sauce(coney island)
directions: Brown and drain ground round.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: cheese soup
directions: In covered saucepan, cook carrot, onion and celery in butter over low heat until tender.
Add broth; cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in half and half and cheese until cheese melts and soup is heated through.
Do not boil!

title: best carrot cake
directions: Line three 9-inch round cake pans with wax paper.
Grease and flour wax paper.
Set pans aside.
Stir together first 4 ingredients at medium speed with an electric mixer until smooth. Add flour mixture, beating at low speed until blended.
Fold in carrots and next 3 ingredients.
Pour batter into prepared cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in a center comes out clean.
Drizzle Buttermilk Glaze evenly over layers.
Cool in pans on wire racks for 15 minutes. Remove from pans and cool completely on wire racks.
Spread Cream Cheese Frosting between layers and on top and sides of cake.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Beat
egg
whites
and
set
aside.
Cream
shortening, sugar, margarine, soda, vanilla
and
egg
yolks.
Add rest of ingredients except egg whites.
Beat ingredients until smooth. Fold in egg whites.
Pour in 2
round pans or 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil and brown beef.
Stir in onion soup mix blended with 1 1/2 cups water.
Simmer, covered, stirring occasionally for 30 minutes.
Add green peppers and simmer, covered, for 10 minutes or until beef is tender.
Stir in cornstarch, blended with remaining water.
Bring to a boil; then simmer, stirring constantly, until sauce is thickened, about 5 minutes.
Serve over hot cooked rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients with mashed potatoes.
Add egg.
Mix again.
Add enough milk to make pancake consistency.
(Mix will be lumpy.)
Drop by tablespoon onto preheated pre-greased griddle. When served, may butter like regular pancakes.

title: chili sauce
directions: Peel, core, seed and coarsely chop tomatoes (about 13 cups). In a six to eight quart dutch oven combine all the above ingredients.

Bring to a boil then reduce heat. Boil gently, uncovered for 1 1/2 hours or until it is thick and reduced by half. Stir mixture occasionally. Immediately ladle chili sauce into hot sterilize half pint canning jars leaving a 1/2 inch head space. Wipe the jar rims and adjust lids. Process in a boiling water canner for 15 minutes. Start time when water begins to boil. Remove jars and cool on wire rack. Makes 7 half pints.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Cook rice and add to first mixture. Mix milk, Miracle Whip, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.

title: irene's pancakes
directions: Add 2 teaspoons of vinegar to the 2 cups of milk and let it set out until it reaches room temperature.
Add egg yolks and oil to milk.
Sift dry ingredients and mix all together.

title: bacon and egg casserole
directions: Arrange bread slices in greased 9 x 13 baking pan. In large bowl, beat together eggs, milk and sour cream. Add salt and meat. Mix. Pour over bread and sprinkle with cheese. Best if refrigerated overnight. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: al's steak and vegetables
directions: Brown meat in a large frying pan.
Add rest of ingredients and cook until meat and potatoes are done.
Serve over rice or wrap in flour tortillas.

title: homemade bread
directions: Mix yeast, sugar and warm water in 2-cup measuring cup.
Let this rise to top of cup.
Mix boiling water, Crisco, sugar and salt in large bowl; stir until Crisco melts.
Add yeast mixture.
Add beaten eggs.
Beat in flour.
Cover bowl and let rise until double. Punch bread down and turn out on floured wax paper.
Knead like biscuits.
Roll out and cut with small cutter.
Dip each piece in melted butter.

title: red hot ski tea
directions: Add 2 or more teaspoons of the mix to a mug of steaming hot water.

title: ham rolls
directions: Combine mustard, margarine, poppy seed and onion.
Cut rolls into halves without pulling apart.
Spread both sides with mustard mixture.
Cut ham and cheese into pieces and assemble on rolls. Put back into pans and cover with foil.
Bake at 300° for 10 to 15 minutes, until cheese melts.
Cut apart and serve.
Can be frozen.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients, then add soda and cream of tartar. Pour over popcorn.
Stir until coated well.
Pour into dish pan; put in oven for 1 hour at 250°.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Remove from oven; stir until cool.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Best if chilled overnight.

title: ham dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, ham (drained), celery and onions together.
Add Hidden Valley Ranch dressing.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix sugar, oil and vinegar together.
Add other ingredients to vinegar mixture.
Mix together and store in refrigerator.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in greased pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sherry's frosting
directions: With mixer, beat shortening, butter, sugar and vanilla. Slowly add warm milk.
Whip 7 minutes.

title: impossible bacon pie
directions: Grease (or Pam) 9-inch pie plate; sprinkle cooked bacon, cheese and onion in plate.
In blender beat remaining ingredients 15 seconds on high or minute with wire whisk or hand beater until smooth; pour into pie plate.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes, cut into wedges and serve.

title: pancakes
directions: Sift together the flour, soda, salt, baking powder and sugar. Add the buttermilk, egg and oil to the flour mixture.
Cook on hot griddle.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix these ingredients well.
Blend good.
Roll into rolls. Wrap in wax paper. Chill until firm.
Slice thin and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
You can freeze these cookies and slice and cook later.

title: gladys peterson's cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl in the order given. Drop by teaspoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° until brown.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix eggs, meat, milk and corn flakes together.
Put it in a loaf pan.
Put ketchup on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mike's great baked beans
directions: Drain all beans and place in ovenproof dish.
Crumble bacon and use 2 tablespoons of drippings to beans.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Garnish with green pepper, sliced.

title: fried chicken
directions: Mix milk, salt, pepper and eggs together.
Pour over chicken and let set for 2 or 3 hours.
Then roll in flour and fry about 30 minutes (15 minutes on each side).

title: hamburger goulash
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and spices.
Add macaroni; cook until macaroni is tender.

title: blueberry chills
directions: Mix crushed crackers, sugar and butter. Press mixture into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 10 minutes. Let cool.

title: easy coconut custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and blend well.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until crust is brown and custard is firm.

title: chocolate rich cake
directions: Bake chocolate cake as directed.
When still warm, poke holes and pour over fudge topping and caramel and Eagle Brand milk. Spread Cool Whip, crush up Butterfingers and sprinkle on top.

title: old fashioned beef stew
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper; roll beef cubes in mixture.
Shake off excess.
Melt shortening over high heat. Brown beef on all sides. Pour on 4 cups boiling water. Stir and add lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, onion, bay leaves and allspice.
Lower heat, cover and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours until meat is tender.
Add vegetables and cook 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: easy and delicious cherry cheese cake
directions: Soften cream cheese. Add powdered sugar and Cool Whip. Blend until well moistened. Pour into pie shell. Top with pie filling and chill.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain grease and add the rest of ingredients.
Heat through; serve with grated cheese, sour cream and Fritos.

title: cabbage-onion slaw
directions: Shred cabbage; slice onion.
In large mouth jar, place a layer of cabbage, then a layer of onion rings until all used up.
Pour 7/8 cup sugar over this.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix in sugar, flour and 1/2 of oleo.
Sprinkle more flour on waxed paper and knead.
Let rise. Pinch off dough, make into rolls and place in pans greased with remaining oleo.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: out of this world salad
directions: Put Jell-O and marshmallows in mixing bowl.
Add boiling water; stir until marshmallows are partly melted.
Add crushed pineapple and mix.
Refrigerate until partly jelled.
Remove from refrigerator.
Add nuts, cottage cheese and cherries that have been cut into small pieces.
Fold in the whipping cream that has been beaten stiff.
Return to refrigerator.

title: fudge
directions: Melt chocolate with butter in a saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients and beat thoroughly.
Pour into buttered pan and chill about 6 hours.
Cut into squares.

title: berry saucy meatballs
directions: Brown meatballs.
Put in pot with chili sauce and cranberry sauce that has been stirred.
Cook together for about 1/2 hour. Serve over rice.

title: creamy coconut pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar, milk and coconut in electric blender container.
Cover and blend at medium speed for 30 seconds.
Fold into whipped topping and add extract.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
Sprinkle with additional coconut, toasted, if desired.
Let stand at room temperature 5 minutes before cutting, if necessary, for creamier texture.
Store any leftover pie in freezer.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Top with fruit slices, lemons, strawberries or oranges.

title: louise's strawberry pizza
directions: Mix flour, butter and pecans and pat out in pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until brown.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread on crust.
Top with fresh strawberries sliced and mixed with strawberry glaze.

title: blacken cajun chicken breast
directions: Slightly dredge chicken breast into Cajun spices.
Shake excess.
In saute pan, heat oil until water droplets bubble. Carefully put spiced chicken in hot oil.
Brown both sides. Remove from hot oil and place in baking dish.
Bake until tender.

title: grandmother's lemon meringue pie(serves 6; do not freeze)
directions: Whisk egg yolks in top of double boiler.
Add lemon juice, rind, cornstarch and cold water and blend well.
Add sugar, boiling water and butter and put over heat, stirring until thick. Cover and cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add cream of tartar and confectioners sugar.
Beat in well.
Pour lemon mixture into cooked pie shell and cover with meringue mixture.
Bake at 225° until brown, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool on rack away from drafts.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix shortening and sugar together; cream them.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and pour into small lined bread pans.
Bake it at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corned beef hash casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Add all other ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale.
Add ginger ale when ready to serve.
Serves 25 people.
Can be doubled.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cover whole chicken in water; cook with onion, celery, salt, pepper and garlic powder until done in large saucepan.
Debone chicken and set aside.
Add 2 cans cream of chicken soup to juice from cooked chicken.
Put deboned chicken back into pot with first mixture.
Stir until thick.
When it bubbles, add Bisquick recipe for dumplings (on side of box).
Cover and simmer according to box recipe.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Drain blueberries and pineapples, saving liquid.
Add enough water to make 1 cup.
Add to Jell-O.
Stir in drained fruit.
Pour into a dish; place in refrigerator until firm.

title: cheesy broccoli bake
directions: Combine 1/4 cup butter, water and contents of stuffing mix seasoning packet in pan.
Stir and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add crumbs.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir mixture and spoon along both sides of a 2-quart baking dish.
Arrange broccoli down center.
Sprinkle with salt.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter and stir in flour.
Remove from heat, adding cream cheese.
Stir until smooth. Add milk and bouillon.
Return to heat and cook, stirring constantly.
Add green onions.
Spoon sauce over broccoli; sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes, until broccoli is tender.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: cajun candy
directions: Combine sugars, salt, milk, yams and corn syrup in heavy 4-quart saucepan.
Stir until all is mixed thoroughly.
Cook over medium heat until sugar is dissolved and it comes to boil.
Reduce heat and cook to 224° on candy thermometer or soft-ball stage. Remove from heat; add butter.
Do not stir.
Cool to 110°.
Chop 1/2 cup pecans.
Add vanilla to cooled mixture.
Beat until candy stiffens and loses gloss.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Spread candy on greased 9-inch pan.
Top with last 1/4 cup pecan halves.
Cut into squares.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Melt the butter.
Blend all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: frosted meat loaf
directions: Combine egg, salt, pepper, mustard, horseradish and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well.
Add chopped onion and tomatoes. Mix meat and blend crumbs; pour in egg mixture.
Press into a greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
After 1 hour, take out of loaf pan.
Spread catsup on top and sides.
Bake an additional 15 to 20 minutes.

title: raisin puffs
directions: Boil water and raisins until water is gone; cool.
Cream the shortening and sugar.
Sift flour, soda and salt and add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and cooled raisins; mix well.
Wet hands.
Form dough into balls and roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Yields 7 dozen.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Mix 1 egg, cake mix
and
margarine.
Press
into
x 13-inch buttered pan.
Combine
remaining ingredients and pour over batter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Serves 18.

title: pear honey
directions: Cook until real thick as for preserves, 2 to 3 hours.

title: seasoned salt
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a mixer and blend thoroughly. Package in airtight container.

title: chocolate cola cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and chocolate.
Add dry ingredients alternately with cola beverage.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in square pan.

title: mom sims' cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In 2-quart casserole, cream together butter and sugar until fluffy.
Stir sifted dry ingredients in alternately with milk.
Beat until smooth.
Spoon fruit over batter.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Pour fruit juice over top.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: all american potato salad
directions: Day before, prepare the dressing.
Combine the mayonnaise, onion, celery, mustard, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce. Cover and refrigerate overnight to allow flavors to develop.

title: baked country ham
directions: Saw off the hock end of the ham so that it will fit into a covered roasting pan.
Save
the
hock
to
use for seasoning vegetables.
Place the ham in
the
roasting pan and cover with water.
Bring to a boil.
Cover.
Remove
from the heat and let stand for several hours.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake in a sheet pan for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: cashew chicken casserole
directions: Boil or cook chicken breasts in microwave until done.
Saute onions and celery in margarine for 5 minutes.
Add chicken broth, soy sauce and soup.
Simmer 2 minutes.
Add chicken.
Place rice in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Put cashews on top.
Bake 5 minutes more.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake cake as directed on package, using 13 x 9-inch pan.
As soon as cake comes from oven, poke holes in cake with fork.
Pour Kahlua evenly over cake.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
In the morning, cut cake in half.
Crumble 1/2 into bottom of punch bowl and pack down.
Mix 2 boxes of mousse according to package and spread evenly over crumbled mixture. Spread 1 Cool Whip over mousse.
Crumble 3 Heath bars and sprinkle over mousse and Cool Whip.
Repeat with remaining ingredients for second layer.
Enjoy!

title: magic meatloaf
directions: Mix egg, milk, and salt.
Allow bread to soak.
Combine meat and vegetables.
Mix in bread.
Shape into loaf.
Put in pan and top with ketchup.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: miracle cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Put butter or margarine in a large casserole dish; place in oven.
When butter softens, spread over bottom and sides of dish.
Prepare a thin batter by sifting together all the dry ingredients and stirring in the milk.
Pour the batter into the buttered dish.
Spread the fruit over the batter.
Peaches, cherries, apricots or berries may be used.
Bake for 45 minutes.
The batter rises through the fruit and makes a brown crust.
Serve slightly warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: perfect tuna
directions: In 1-quart casserole, blend soup
and milk.
Stir in tuna, eggs and peas.
Top with chips.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: pizza dough
directions: Mix water and yeast together until dissolved.
Add sugar and oil; mix well.
Add salt and 2 1/2 cups flour.
Mix into a ball. Turn onto floured board.
Add remaining flour until a bread-type consistency.
Put in lightly greased bowl.
Cover and let rise until double.
Spread on 1 large pizza pan or 2 small.
Bake at 325° for 5 minutes.
Add favorite pizza toppings and sauce; bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: corn muffins
directions: Grease twelve 2 1/2-inch muffin cups.
Heat oven to 425°. Sift flour, baking powder, sugar and salt into a medium size mixing bowl.
Add corn meal; stir to mix well.
In a small bowl, beat eggs with a fork.
Add milk and oil.
Add all at once to dry ingredients; stir until moistened.
Batter will be lumpy.
Drop batter from a tablespoon into the prepared muffin cups, filling each cup half to two-thirds full.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes, or until golden brown.
Remove from pan and serve hot with butter.

title: spinach dip
directions: Let spinach thaw; squeeze out all water.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Let chill at least 2 hours or overnight. Serve with chips or crackers.

title: mama's cream pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients
well.
Pour in milk; add egg yolks and butter.
Cook
over
heat until it begins to thicken.
Add pineapple.	Pour in pie shell(s) and bake.

title: vegetable pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package instructions.
Drain and rinse with cold water.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Toss vegetables together.
Mix dressing of mayonnaise, cider vinegar and sugar.
Pour over vegetables.
Chill for at least two hours to let the flavors mix before serving.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix first six ingredients and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle box of yellow cake mix on top.
Pour melted butter over this.
Sprinkle pecans over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Check and cook longer if needed.

title: taffy bars
directions: Mix sugar, Nucoa and egg yolk.
Add flour, nuts and vanilla. Spread in jelly roll pan.
Beat egg white slightly and spread over batter.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 225°. Cut into squares while still warm.

title: sausage bread
directions: Crumble and brown sausage; set aside.
Mix hot roll mix as directed except don't let it rise.	Take a piece of foil a little longer than a cookie sheet; spray the foil and your hands with Pam.
Then knead the dough about 3 to 5 minutes.
Then press the dough out about the size of a cookie sheet.
Put crumbled sausage over dough, then crumble cheese over dough.
Roll and wrap with foil and bake at 375° for 20 minutes, then unwrap and bake for 10 more minutes or until brown.
Slice, serve and enjoy.

title: oyster dill snacks
directions: Mix
last five ingredients and pour over crackers.
Let sit about an hour and then store in Tupperware container.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve with favorite vegetables.

title: fried shrimp
directions: Devein and shell shrimp leaving fantail.
Mix eggs, milk, baking powder and vinegar.
Marinate shrimp at least 1 hour.
Add seasoning liberally to flour.
Dip shrimp in flour, batter and flour again.
Fry in oil until brown, turning once, about 2 to 3 minutes.

title: old fashioned peanut brittle
directions: Stir together sugar and corn syrup in a 2-quart bowl. Microwave for 4 minutes on High.
Add peanuts; stir well. Microwave for 4 minutes on High.
Add butter and vanilla; stir well.
Microwave for approximately 1 to 1 1/2 minutes on High. Watch carefully.
Add baking soda and stir until light and foamy. Pour at once onto buttered cookie sheet; spread as thin as possible.
Cool 30 to 60 minutes and break into pieces.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Boil macaroni in water until tender.
Place layer of macaroni, cheese, bread crumbs, green pepper and onion in baking dish, continuing until all is used.
Thoroughly beat eggs.
Add milk. Pour over macaroni.
Sprinkle with pepper and salt.
Dot with butter.
Bake in moderate oven 30 minutes.

title: strawberry jello mold
directions: Combine jello and cottage cheese.
Fold in berries and Cool Whip.
Let set.
Very good.

title: italian fruit salad
directions: Cook soupettes according to directions.
Rinse and cool.
In pan, bring to boil juices, sugar, flour, eggs, salt, cornstarch and lemon juice.
Make like gravy.
Mix in soupettes and refrigerate overnight.

title: banana pudding
directions: Whip egg yolks in pan; add milk and put on burner to get warm. Add flour, sugar and dash of salt in separate container.
After mixing, add to milk and egg mixture.
Stir continuously until thick.
Take off burner and add vanilla.
Set pan in cold water. Cool; then layer with vanilla wafers and bananas.
Top with meringue and brown in oven.

title: banana split cake
directions: Blend together 1 stick of butter and crushed graham crackers. Bake for 7 minutes at 375°.
Beat for at least 15 minutes, eggs, powdered sugar and 2 sticks butter.
Do not under beat.
Pour mixture on top of graham cracker crust.
Layer with bananas; then layer with drained crushed pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip on top of pineapple.
Top with cherries and chopped nuts.
For best results, refrigerate overnight.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute onions and celery in margarine.
Add cabbage, basil, bouillon cubes and water.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add Beefogetti and simmer 10 minutes more.
Serves four to six.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Mix good.
Drop on cookie sheet with teaspoon.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: non-cook finger paint
directions: Beat liquid starch with Ivory flakes.
Mix until soap is thoroughly dissolved. Add the desired color of tempra powder. Blend thoroughly.
Keep in tightly sealed jar.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown the meat until it changes color.
Add onion.
Salt to taste.
Add water and steam until done, 5 to 10 minutes.
Add soup and heat through.
Add sour cream and stir in.
(Do not boil the sour cream.)
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Wash and drain shrimp.
Mix with cream cheese and Worcestershire sauce.
Dip away!

title: hot dog or spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together including ground beef.
Cook over low heat unti done or as dry as you like.
Chili powder and garlic may be added, if desired.

title: chicken corn chowder
directions: In large saucepan, stir all ingredients until well blended. Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Ladle into bowls and sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: dill carrots
directions: Wash and cut carrots in 2-inch strips.
Place all ingredients in 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Cover.
Place in microwave on High power for 7 minutes.
Allow to stand, covered, for 5 minutes.

title: three layer cake
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients except egg whites.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour batter equally into 3 greased and floured cake pans. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Use your favorite icing to cover these layers.

title: georgia style salmon patties
directions: Boil potato until tender; drain.
Drain salmon and remove bones.
Cut up onion and add rest of ingredients.
Shape into patties and fry in oil on medium heat until done.

title: woodford pudding
directions: Cream butter until light, then gradually add both sugars. Beat until fluffy. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in the jam. Combine flour, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add milk and flour mixture alternately, beating well after each addition.
When mixture is smooth, pour into a greased and floured 10-inch square or similar capacity pan and bake in a preheated 350° oven 35 to 40 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve warm with Bourbon Sauce.

title: cinnamon squares
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy; add egg yolks and vanilla and blend; add flour and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Divide dough between two greased 15 x 10 x 1 inch jelly roll pans.
Flatten down with heels of hands in pans.
Lightly beat the egg white and brush over batter.
Mark batter into squares, place chocolate chips, nuts or coconut on top and bake 350° for 20 - 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix 1 can cream of mushroom soup with a little more than 1/2 pt. sour cream.
Bring to a boil.
Cook and chop broccoli spears; put in quart casserole, pour soup mixture over mix and let set in refrigerator overnight.
Melt butter and mix in stuffing crumbs until coated with butter.
Put on top of broccoli and bake at 325° to 350° for 45 minutes, or until brown, uncovered.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, add the following in order.
Melt butter; sprinkle over butter, graham cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle chocolate chips, then butterscotch chips and coconut.
Pour sweetened milk over other ingredients.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over all.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cool and cut into squares.
This is very rich and delicious.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Line the bottom of 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish with dried beef. Put chicken breast on top and sprinkle with pepper.
Mix sour cream and soup in a bowl.
Pour over the chicken and sprinkle with paprika.
Cover with Reynolds Wrap and bake at 300° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Combine vanilla, eggs, sugars and oil; mix until creamy and smooth.
Mix dry ingredients; add to sugar and oil mixture.
Stir in oats, corn flakes and coconut.
Drop by tablespoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 12 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Fry your pork chops and put aside.
Saute chopped onion and bell pepper.
Boil water and add bouillon cubes.
Stir this until well mixed.
Put your rice in the bottom of a casserole dish.
Then add your pork chops on top of rice.
Then put your onion and pepper in the water with bouillon cubes.
Pour this on top of pork chops. Put the lid on your dish and cook in oven about an hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sauerkraut - bohemian style
directions: Pour sauerkraut into 2-quart pan.
Add sugar, grated potato and diced onion.
Cook at least two hours, stirring every so often. Check because it will dry out and burn, but add more water as needed.
After about one hour, add the fennel seed.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together except eggs and Rice Krispies. Put one half of mixture in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan (lightly greased).
Place sliced eggs on top of mixture and then cover with remaining mixture.
Put crushed Rice Krispies on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Blend together in a Baggy. Cover top of Chicken Casserole. Bake 45 minutes at 425°.

title: mom's hawaiian banana nut bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until batter is moistened.
Spoon in two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans (sprayed with Pam).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes or until done.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Remove and cool completely.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Half way through baking, top with shredded cheese.
Return to oven for remaining time.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Butter buns.
Spread mixture on rolls.
Wrap buns individually with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: ham and cheese crescent snacks
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Unroll dough into 4 long rectangles. Firmly press the perforations to seal.
Place on side of ham on each rectangle.
Spread ham with mustard and sprinkle with cheese. Starting with the shortest side, roll up each rectangle.
Press edges to seal.
Cut each of the rolls into 5 slices.
You should end up with 20 slices in all.
Place each slice on an ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown. Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Serve warm.

title: grandmother's old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and shortening. Add eggs one at a time; add vanilla and remaining ingredients. Knead dough on floured board; chill dough. Roll out on floured board; cut with biscuit cutter. Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: beef burritos
directions: Cook and drain hamburger. Mix beans and cheese into the hamburger. Add red pepper, garlic and onion to mixture, according to your tastes. Warm tortilla shells for easier folding. Fill to your desired thickness; most usually 2 tablespoons will be enough. Microwave and eat.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease bottom and sides of slow cooker. Spread layers of pineapple, pie filling and dry cake mix. Be careful not to mix the layers. Sprinkle with cinnamon. Top with thin layers of butter chunks and nuts. Cover. Cook on high 2 to 3 hours.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix meat, seasonings, bread crumbs, water, onion and green pepper.
Form into balls.
Roll in flour; brown in hot fat or olive oil.

title: corn pudding
directions: Blend all ingredients until well mixed and pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
One of my favorite dishes.

title: chow mein soft noodles
directions: Fry noodles
in skillet with enough oil to cover bottom of skillet.
Lightly
brown,
flipping over to brown the other side. Place
on
platter.
Fry
pork
in dash of oil.
Season with
salt and
pepper.
When nearly done, add vegetables and water.	Season with sugar, vinegar, soy sauce and m.s.g.
Cook just
enough
to heat through the vegetables, do not overcook. Thicken
with diluted
cornstarch;
mix and pile mixture onto noodles.
Serves 4 generously!

title: pasta fagioli
directions: Heat olive oil in 2-quart saucepan to medium.
Saute garlic until opaque.
Add onion, celery and about 2 ounces of water.
When mixture boils, reduce heat to simmer.
Simmer 10 minutes until onion is soft.
Dissolve bouillon in water; add to pot.
Add additional 8 ounces boiling water.
Remove casing from precooked sausage and break into small pieces.
Add to mixture.
Add seasoning, tomato sauce and beans.
Bring to boil, then simmer about 25 minutes.
Cook pasta al dente.
Drain and place in large bowl.
Add sausage mixture and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Serves 6 to 8.

title: italian veal birds
directions: Chop the onion, carrots and celery in food processor.
Pound veal or chicken slices lightly until very thin.
Combine the ham, garlic, parsley and salt and pepper if needed.
Spoon a little of the mixture on top of the veal or chicken slices; roll and fasten with toothpicks.
Dredge in flour and brown on all sides in the butter and oil.
Add the wine and cook until it is almost completely reduced.
Add the chicken stock and simmer gently for 25 minutes.
Add the vegetables and rosemary and cook for 20 minutes longer.
Serve on top of rice.
Reduce what's left of the wine and chicken stock and serve on side.
Serves 6.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain off grease.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer at least 1 hour.

title: super salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl, except egg. Beat with mixer until ingredients are well blended.
Add egg and beat until it is well mixed with other ingredients.
Makes slightly more than one quart.
Keep refrigerated.
It will keep indefinitely.

title: pumpkin bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tea cake cookies
directions: Cream margarine.
Gradually add sugar; beating after each addition.
Add eggs, beating after each.
Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Stir well.
Sift soda, baking powder and 1 cup flour together and gradually add to butter mixture, blending well.
Add more flour, a little at a time, until dough is stiff enough to handle.
Cover dough and chill 2 hours.

title: french vanilla frosting
directions: Beat 1 cup Crisco and egg together well.
Bring water and sugar to a boil, until dissolved, to make syrup.
Gradually add confectioners sugar to Crisco/egg mix.
Add syrup to get consistency desired.
Add extract.

title: peach bread
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine next 5 ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with the peaches, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in orange juice and vanilla.
Pour batter into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican chicken manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti as directed on package; drain.
Combine chicken, carrots, cottage cheese, onion, cilantro and garlic; stuff manicotti shells with chicken mixture.
Arrange in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour Ro-Tel over manicotti, then sprinkle with cheese.
Cover with foil and bake 35 minutes or until hot in center in 325° oven.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Place cut up vegetables in bowl.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and garlic salt with vegetables.
Add peas last.
Mix well.
Let stand in refrigerator several hours.

title: chicken soup
directions: Bring water to a boil and then add onion salt, garlic salt and the chicken.
Let it cook until just about tender.
Add tomato sauce, cabbage, carrots and rice.
Cook until the rice is done. Serve in bowls with lemon and chile on the side.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar, eggs and milk.
Beat with fork. Add coconut and mix.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown on top.

title: ritz cracker chicken
directions: Dip chicken in butter.
Roll in Ritz cracker crumbs.
Place on a cookie sheet or oblong baking dish.
Cover tightly with foil. Bake at 225° for 2 hours.
This is ideal to bake while at church.

title: 5 minute chocolate chewies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together flour, cocoa, soda and salt.
Beat into sugar mixture, a little at a time.
Refrigerate cookie dough until it's very firm.
To bake, roll spoonfuls of dough into a ball.
Roll the balls in granulated sugar.
Mash on cookie sheet with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes.

title: cheese cake snack
directions: Combine cake mix, melted butter and 1 beaten egg in a large bowl and mix well. Spread into a greased 9 x 13-inch sheet cake pan, making a 1/4-inch side around the entire pan.
Next, mix well the cream cheese, powdered sugar and 2 beaten eggs, then pour batter over dough already in pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Allow cooling time and sprinkle top with powdered sugar.

title: the working girl's crock-pot beef mix
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot before work.
Turn on low. Simmer for 8 to 10 hours.
When you come home, you can decide whether to serve on hamburger buns, in taco shells or add other ingredients and make a casserole dish out of it.
Very versatile. Use your imagination!
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream brown sugar, shortening, eggs and pumpkin.
Sift flour, baking powder, ginger, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.
Add flour mixture to batter and mix well.
Fold in vanilla and lemon, then nuts and chopped dates.
Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: granny's potato bread
directions: Heat together milk and margarine to scalding; do not boil. Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl. Add cooled milk, salt and sugar.
Stir in potato flakes and enough flour to make a soft dough.
Knead on floured surface 8 to 10 minutes until smooth and satiny.
Cover; let rise in warm place until doubled in bulk, 45 to 60 minutes.
Punch down; divide in half.
Shape into 2 loaves.
Place, seam side down, in well-greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Let rise again 30 to 45 minutes.
Bake in a 375° oven for 45 to 50 minutes, until golden brown.

title: ham balls
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Mix meat, eggs and milk.
Blend in bread crumbs.
Shape into balls and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix brown sugar, vinegar, water and mustard.
Pour over balls and bake for 3 hours.
Baste occasionally.

title: hungry jack beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Stir in the next 6 ingredients. Heat until bubbly.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Cut biscuits in half to form 20 half circles.
Place cut side down around inside edge of casserole.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top of biscuits.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.
Refrigerate any leftovers. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix water, sugar, syrup and salt in a saucepan, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to a boil; boil for 3 minutes. Continue cooking until syrup takes on a rich caramel color at 320°.
Have peanuts spread out on a 12 x 12 x 19-inch buttered shallow enamel ware pan, a marble slab or an enamel kitchen top. When candy gets to 320° stir in butter and soda.
Stir well and quickly pour out on peanuts.
Let cool and break.

title: chicken and chiles casserole
directions: Sprinkle chicken breast evenly with salt and pepper.
Place in a lightly greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Combine cheese and next 3 ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with chiles.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Grind eggs, onions, pecans and cheese.
Mix in mayonnaise and juice.
Will keep in refrigerator a couple of weeks.

title: sausage hot roll
directions: Remove skin and crumble summer sausage.
Brown lightly in 1 tablespoon olive oil.
Drain and save it.

title: french blueberry glace pie
directions: Put blueberries in baked pie shell.
Cover with cooled Blueberry Sauce.
Refrigerate until firm, about 2 hours.
Serve with vanilla ice cream or whipped cream.

title: chicken with fennel
directions: In a large skillet, heat the olive oil and butter.
Saute the fennel, leeks and shallots until golden brown, about 10 minutes. Transfer to a platter.
Add the chicken to the skillet and cook until done.
Arrange over the vegetables.
Keep warm.
In the skillet, combine the broth, wine, mustard, salt and pepper; bring to a boil.
Stir in the half and half; simmer, stirring 1 minute. Pour the sauce over the chicken and vegetables.

title: raisin special pie
directions: Combine raisins, sugar, water, salt and butter.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Stir in 2 tablespoons cornstarch mixed with 3 tablespoons water.
Cook stirring 5 minutes.
Add 1 teaspoons lemon flavoring.
Use a 9-inch crust with lattice top.
Bake at 425° for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli first
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Place in oven at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Mix ingredients in the order given.
Mix when all ingredients are in the bowl, starting with the egg and ending with the boiling water.
Place in two 9-inch cake tins.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost when cool.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Make chocolate pudding according to package directions. Cool for about 5 minutes. Mix pudding with dry cake mix and pour into a greased 9 x 13 pan. Top pudding/cake mixture with brown sugar, nuts & chocolate chips. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender.
Drain.
Mix with other ingredients.
Put in a casserole dish.
Add bread crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until bubbly on top.

title: meat balls
directions: Beat egg whites; set aside. Soak bread crumbs in milk. Mix the rest of the ingredients together and make into small balls. Dip balls in egg whites. Roll in crushed corn flakes. Fry until brown. Place in baking dish.

title: sweet potato custard
directions: Mix all ingredients (except pie shell) and put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 25 minutes.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all together.
Store in tight container.
Mix 3 teaspoons to 1 cup hot water.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly. Save some bread crumbs for topping.
Add extra cheese on top, if desired.
Bake at 325° for approximately 40 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Combine the soups, onion, salt, parsley, thyme, pepper and celery flakes.
Add water to mixture; bring to boil.
Put 1 cup of mixture aside and to remaining mixture, add rice.
Mix well and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken on top and pour remaining mixture over.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: amazingly easy overnight cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine dry milk, warm water, sugar, shortening and yeast. Stir until yeast dissolves.
Beat egg with the salt and add to liquid.
Add flour one cup at a time, beating well after each addition.
Continue beating until dough is smooth.

title: chocolate frosty
directions: Let ice cream sit in refrigerator for 1 hour before preparation to soften.
Mix all ingredients in blender.
Blend until smooth. Makes 1 serving.

title: baked beans
directions: Blend all ingredients, except bacon.
Put in a casserole dish; add bacon on top.
Put in oven and cook at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, until bacon is done.

title: pecan pies
directions: Beat eggs real good and add everything together.
Pour into two 9-inch deep dish pie shells.
Cook at 250° for about 2 hours.

title: tuna pasta
directions: Heat oil in heavy medium skillet over medium-low heat.
Add onions and cook until translucent, stirring occasionally, about 5 minutes.
Add tuna, tomatoes, olives, basil, garlic, salt and pepper; cook until fish is opaque, stirring often, about 9 minutes.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer the first five ingredients in order listed in a 2 quart flat casserole. Mix the mayonnaise, yogurt, sugar, and salt. Spread over top and seal edges. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Garnish with crumbled bacon and cherry tomato halves.

title: "fourteen karat" cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together first 5 ingredients; in a separate bowl, beat next 3 ingredients until creamy.
Mix all ingredients together well.
Add carrots and nuts.
Pour into well-greased and floured 9-inch tube pan or two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Test after 50 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Tested should come out clean, but somewhat moist.

title: soft yummy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all the above ingredients. Make them the size you want, little or big. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Check at 10 minutes to check for desired chewy cookies.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Sift together the sugar, flour, cinnamon and baking powder. Add the cherries and nuts. Add the egg.
Add the shortening.
Mix well and pour into square pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bread and butter pudding(theresa shea)
directions: Line bottom of greased pudding dish with raisins.
Cut bread slices in 3 strips, crosswise.
Dip each in melted butter and arrange on top of raisins.
Beat remaining ingredients together and pour over bread.
Set dish in pan of hot water.
Bake in hot oven at 375° until bread is browned and a knife blade comes out clean (about 1 hour).
Serve plain or with cream.
Serves 6.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown and drain ground beef and sausage. Add next 7 ingredients and cook together until it looks like spaghetti sauce. In a 17x 9 inch pan, layer in this order, noodles, meat sauce, cottage cheese, mozzarella. Layer again the same way, but end with a layer of meat sauce on top. Cover with heavy foil and bake at 300 degrees for 1 hour. Remove foil and cook 1/2 hour. Let set 10-15 minutes before cutting.

title: shoo-fly pie(wet bottom)
directions: Beat egg yolk in a small bowl. Blend in the molasses. Add the boiling water with the baking soda dissolved in it. Set aside.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Mix all of the ingredients, except Doritos and 1/2 cup of cheese.
In casserole dish, alternate layers of Doritos and chicken.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: ritz peanut butter cookies
directions: Spread peanut butter on cracker and top with another cracker. Make about two rolls of peanut butter and crackers.
Melt almond bark in microwave according to package instructions.
Dip crackers using tongs into almond bark.
Place cookies on wax paper to dry.

title: lemon tart
directions: Hand mix nuts, flour and butter together.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Beat with an electric mixer the Cool Whip, powdered sugar and cream cheese. Pour over cooled crust.
Beat with electric mixer the pudding and milk.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Spread additional Cool Whip over pudding and top with chopped nuts.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Make cake as directed on box, adding vanilla and coconut, except for 1/2 cup.
Bake in greased, floured, 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.

title: mammy's tea cakes
directions: Combine Crisco and sugars in bowl and mix.
In separate bowl, combine soda, salt and flour and mix together with a spoon.
Add to Crisco, sugar mix and add flavoring and eggs.
Mix.
With a teaspoon, drop batter on cookie sheet.
Flatten cookies with tines of fork and sprinkle with sugar.

title: chicken cooked with vermouth and tomatoes(poulet chasseur)
directions: Peel and chop the shallots; peel the onions but leave them whole.
Melt the Crisco; add the oil and beat together for a moment.
Place the chicken in one layer in the pan; brown the pieces on both sides.
After adding the onions to flavor them a little and the shallots after 2 to 3 minutes so that the shallots melt but do not color.
Remove the pan from heat; add vermouth and when warm, ignite with a match.
Tip the pan until the flames die down.
Simmer for 5 minutes to reduce the liquid in half.
Drain tomatoes; roughly chop.
Add the juice to the pan and mix well. Cover and leave for 1 hour without lifting the lid.

title: pumpkin cranberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Combine flour, spices, baking soda and salt in a large bowl.
Combine sugar, pumpkin, eggs, vegetable oil and orange juice in a larger mixer bowl.
Beat until just blended.
Add pumpkin mixture to flour mixture.
Stir just until moistened. Fold in cranberries.

title: turkey frame soup
directions: Break turkey frame or cut in half with
kitchen shears; place in large Dutch oven with water, onion and
salt.
Bring to boiling;
reduce heat.
Cover;
simmer for 1
hours. Remove turkey frame; when cold enough to handle, cut
off meat and coarsely
chop.
Discard
bones.
Strain
broth;
discard solids. Return
broth
to
Dutch oven.
Stir in cut up turkey meat, undrained
tomatoes,
bouillon granules, oregano, thyme and pepper.
Stir
in
fresh
vegetables.
Bring
to
boiling; reduce heat.
Cover;
simmer for 45 minutes.
Stir in uncooked noodles; simmer,
uncovered,
8 to 10 minutes or until noodles are done. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Serves 10.

title: corn souffle casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Cover with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: maple-vanilla ice(low sodium, low-fat, low cholesterol and low calorie)
directions: Mix all ingredients until sugar is dissolved.
Pour into 1-quart ice cream freezer.
Freeze according to the manufacturer's directions (8 servings).

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Melt chocolate chips with 14 ounces almond bark in a large saucepan over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Remove from heat. Stir in marshmallows, cereal and peanuts.
Pour onto greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Top with cherries; sprinkle with coconut. Melt remaining 2 ounces almond bark and oil over low heat, stirring until smooth; drizzle over coconut.
Refrigerate until firm.
Store at room temperature.
Cut into wedges.
Makes about 12.

title: coconut cake
directions: Let cool in pan approximately 6 minutes then remove and cool rest of way. Put coconut into bowl. Boil 1 cup water and 1 cup sugar then pour over coconut. Drain, reserving liquid and spoon that liquid over cakes.

title: mother's chicken dressing
directions: Stuff bird with dressing.
Cook until light brown.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: On large plate, layer bean dip.
Mix together avocados, lemon juice, salt and pepper; spread over bean dip.
Mix taco seasoning, sour cream and mayonnaise together and spread over avocado mixture. Sprinkle green onions, tomatoes, olives and Cheddar cheese on top in that order.

title: hash brown-cheesy potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thaw hash browns 1 hour.
In large bowl, mix sour cream and soup; stir in hash browns, onion and cheese. Spoon into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Crush potato chips in bag with rolling pin.
Sprinkle top of casserole with potato chips. Pour melted butter all over chips.
Bake 1 hour.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: orange yogurt salad
directions: In medium bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Combine remaining ingredients and chill until set.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Great with raw veggies or chips.

title: joanne's mother's secret sugar cookie recipe
directions: Cream and beat shortening and sugar until light and fluffy. Cream and beat well eggs, milk and flavoring.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to other mixture.
Shape into mound. Wrap in wax paper.
Chill.
Roll on a board lightly floured with confectioners sugar and flour mixture.
Roll to approximately 1/4 inch thick.
Put cutter in confectioners sugar before cutting. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add taco seasoning, Cheddar cheese soup and water, then cook noodles.
Layer 1/2 noodles, 1/2 ground beef, 1/2 can cream of mushroom soup, 1/2 green chilies, 1/2 Cheddar cheese and 1/2 Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat for second layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coffee cake
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients.
Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to first mixture.
Mix together cinnamon and nuts.
Pour into Bundt pan 1/2 mixture and 1/3 cinnamon and nut mixture.
Add rest of mixture and sprinkle rest of cinnamon mixture over top of mixture.
Start in a cold oven. Turn on at 350°.
Bake for approximately 45 to 50 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all except walnuts and parsley.
Refrigerate for 2 hours. Roll mixture in walnuts and parsley; shape as desired.
Delicious served with crackers.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together.
Roll into small balls.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes about 100 balls. These also freeze well.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Mix together cake mix, margarine and 1 egg.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cream together cream cheese, powdered sugar and 3 eggs.
Pour over cake mix.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.
Do not overbake.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Season with salt and pepper.
Roll in corn meal or shake together in Ziploc bag.
Heat shortening in heavy skillet.
Fry tomatoes slowly until brown. Serve hot.

title: spinach dip
directions: Squeeze spinach dry.
Chop water chestnuts finely.
Mix with rest of ingredients and chill.

title: moussaka
directions: Pare eggplant and slice 1/2-inch thick.
Sprinkle with salt and set aside.
Brown meat with onions and drain off fat.
Add water, parsley, tomato paste, salt and pepper.
Simmer until liquid is nearly gone.
Cool and stir in half bread crumbs, 2 eggs, 1/4 cup cheese and cinnamon.

title: grandma's wine drop cookies
directions: Beat eggs, butter and sugar.
Add molasses, then sour milk with soda.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Drop by large teaspoonful onto baking sheet.
Bake approximately 10 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken (save broth).
Let chicken cool, then cut chicken up.
Mix stuffing with butter.
Put stuffing mix in the bottom of pan (save about 1 cup of stuffing to put on top).
Mix soup together with 1 can of chicken broth.
Put chicken over top of stuffing.
Pour the soup over chicken.
Sprinkle stuffing over soup.
Cook for 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.
Let soup bubble through stuffing.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion to taste.
Drain.
Line bottom of casserole
with 1/2 the stuffing mix.
Mix squash with remaining ingredients.
Top with remaining stuffing mix.
Melt oleo and drizzle
over
stuffing
mix.
Bake
at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: jambalaya
directions: Boil chicken in 6 cups water; dice.
Keep separate.
Dice sausage; pan-fry, drain and keep separate.

title: mock strawberry jam
directions: Combine all ingredients in a heavy saucepan. Bring to a boil and cook for 5 minutes.
Pour into hot sterilized jars and seal. Store in a dark cook place.

title: grits casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook grits in salted water until thick. Add butter, eggs, milk, cheese and sausage.
Stir thoroughly. Pour into well-greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed fish fillets
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onion in 3 tablespoons butter until tender; remove from pan.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in pan. Add flour; blend well.
Slowly add broth; stir until smooth and thick.
Add onion; season and remove from heat.
Combine 3 tablespoons of sauce with shrimp and 3 tablespoons with parsley, reserving some shrimp and parsley for garnish.
Spread 2 fillets with shrimp sauce and 2 with parsley sauce.
Roll up fillets; place in buttered custard cups.
Add 1 tablespoon wine to each cup.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Place fillets on warm spinach.
Top with remaining sauces and garnish.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Saute pork in a large Dutch oven until crisp; drain.
Add remaining ingredients except macaroni and cheese.
Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Add macaroni; simmer 10 minutes.
Sprinkle each serving with cheese.

title: prazhna(spinach souffle)
directions: Slightly beat eggs.
Add cottage cheese, spinach, cubed cheese, oleo and flour.
Put in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° until brown, approximately 1 hour.

title: san antonio salsa
directions: Chop vegetables in food processor.
Heat remaining ingredients until paste is diluted.
Combine with vegetables, chill and serve.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour over ice cubes.
Let stand for a few minutes.
Serve as an appetizer or quencher.
Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: white sauce
directions: Melt oleo; remove from heat.
Stir in dry milk, flour and salt.
Slowly add water, stirring constantly.
Return to heat; cook on medium heat, stirring until thick.
Yields 1/3 cup.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix beans, soup and sour cream with 1/2 can of fried onions, salt and pepper.
Pour in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Pour remaining onions over top of casserole and cook for 5 minutes more.

title: cherry cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and preserves.
Thoroughly stir together flour, soda and salt. Blend dry ingredients into creamed mixture, mixing until well blended.
Drop 1 teaspoon dough 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until lightly browned (8 to 10 minutes). Cool on cookie sheets 1 to 2 minutes.
Spoon a little additional cherry preserves atop each cookie.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Add together.
Place in greased casserole dish, dotted with butter.
Bake at 350° until brown.
May be refrigerated for 2 weeks.

title: honey oat bran bars
directions: Lightly grease a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In a large bowl toss together cereal, nuts and raisins; set aside.
In a 2-quart saucepan combine butter, honey and sugar.
Stirring constantly, bring to a full boil over medium heat and boil for 5 minutes. Pour over cereal mixture; toss to coat well.
Press evenly into prepared pan.
Let stand 1 hour.
Cut into 2 x 1 1/2-inch bars. Store in tightly covered container.
Makes 24 bars.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add milk and cooled, melted margarine. Combine nutmeg, flour and sugar; add to other ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: pickled cow heart or cow tongue
directions: Boil meat until just cooked through.
Drain and slice.
Mix everything together and pour over tongue or heart.
Make sure you have tongue and heart sliced the way you want it.
Put it in a good sized jar with lid, so it is all covered with liquid.

title: race day cake
directions: Combine boiling water and cocoa; cool.
Sift flour, sugar, soda and salt together into a bowl.
Make a well and add vegetable oil, egg yolks, vanilla and cooled cocoa mixture.
Beat until smooth with spoon, then measure egg whites and cream of tartar into large mixing bowl and beat until very stiff.
Pour egg yolk mixture in thin stream over entire surface of beaten egg whites, gently cutting and folding in with rubber spatula until completely blended.
Pour into ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 55 minutes at 325° and then at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until cake tests done.
Let hang over bottle neck until cold.
Ice with Fluffy White Frosting.

title: salmon biscuit roll
directions: Saute celery, pepper and onion in butter until tender; add olives.
Drain salmon; reserve liquid.
Add salmon with 1/4 cup of the chicken soup to vegetables; set aside.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Mix sugar and shortening together thoroughly.
Stir in egg and milk.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and stir in.
Fold in blueberries.
Spread batter in greased oblong pan.
Sprinkle with Streusel Mix.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion over bottom of lightly greased 9 inch pie plate. Place remaining ingredients in blender and blend at high speed for 1 minutes. Pour into pie plate. Bake at 350° 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in tube pan.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: crab meltaways
directions: Combine all ingredients. Spread mixture evenly over English muffin halves. Place on cookie sheet and cover with plastic wrap. Freeze. Remove to a sealed container and keep frozen until ready to bake. Bake at 500° until tops are lightly browned and bubbly. Cut into quarters and serve.

title: caramel sticks
directions: Melt sugar and margarine together.
Add other ingredients and stir in nuts.
Spread in an 8-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake approximately 30 minutes at 325°.
Cool before cutting.

title: cantaloupe and blueberries with yogurt dressing
directions: Rinse and dry cantaloupes.
Cut each melon in half; scoop out and discard seeds.
Drizzle melons with lemon juice; set aside. In a small mixing bowl, combine berries, yogurt and vanilla.
Fill melon halves with equal amounts of mixture.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Using the broth from the chicken, mix it with the bread. Saute onion, celery, and bell pepper in small amount of oil until tender.
Add to broth and bread.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put small pieces of chicken over the dressing, pressing it into the dressing.
Pour into long pie pan and bake at 400 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Finely crush the Oreos.
Set aside.
Mix milk, vanilla pudding and Cool Whip.
Set aside.
Mix butter, powdered sugar and cream cheese, then mix this with pudding mixture.
Layer in flowerpot or large bowl 1/3 cookies, 1/2 pudding mixture, 1/3 cookies, 1/2 pudding mixture and 1/3 cookies.

title: sugar-free strawberry pie
directions: Mix strawberry Jell-O, vanilla pudding, hot water and 2 packages sweetener.
Boil 5 minutes.
Mix sliced strawberries and 2 packages sweetener.
Add sweetened strawberries to filling and stir.
Pour into pie crust.
Add red food coloring for brighter color.

title: excellent london broil
directions: Marinate the London broil in the wine, oil, garlic, thyme, black pepper, basil and marjoram for 2 hours or overnight.
You may broil the steak on the grill, but I remove it from the marinade, wrap it tightly in foil and cook at 450° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until desired doneness.
Do not overcook or it will be tough.
Slice in very thin strips.

title: curry chicken
directions: Saute chicken in oil.
Place asparagus in baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients.
Drain chicken and mushrooms and put into baking dish.
Pour in other ingredients and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix soup and
beans
in casserole dish.
Top with onion rings. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cauliflower au gratin
directions: Wash cauliflower; break into flowerets.
Cook, covered, in a small amount of boiling water until tender, 10 to 15 minutes; drain well.
Place half the flowerets in a 2-quart casserole; season with salt and pepper.
Spread with 1 cup sour cream and 1 cup cheese; top with 1 teaspoon sesame seed and repeat layers. Bake in 350° oven until cheese melts and sour cream is heated through.

title: chocolate chip coffee cake
directions: Blend cake mix, dry pudding, eggs, oil and milk with mixer on high for 4 minutes. Batter will be thick. Spread half of batter in a greased 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle with half of cinnamon-sugar mixture and half of chocolate chips. Spread remaining batter in pan and sprinkle with remaining cinnamon-sugar mixture and other half of chocolate chips. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes. (If using glass pan, bake at 325°.)

title: icing for moist chocolate cake
directions: Combine milk and flour.
In a saucepan, cook until thick. Cover and refrigerate.
In a mixing bowl, beat butter, shortening, sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Add chilled milk and flour mixture and beat for 10 minutes.
Frost cooled cake.

title: copper pennies
directions: In saucepan, put last 6 ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
While still hot, add the other ingredients.
Let cool. Cover and keep in refrigerator overnight.

title: twenty-two minute chocolate cake
directions: Mix in a large bowl with a fork the flour and sugar.
In saucepan, mix oleo, water, oil and cocoa.
Bring to a boil and pour over dry mixture.
Mix eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla. Pour over batter and mix thoroughly with a spoon.
Pour into a 12 x 18-inch greased pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: soft peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix all ingredients together thoroughly in a bowl. Drop mixture by teaspoons onto a nonstick baking sheet and press each with a fork.
Bake for about 10 minutes. Cool before removing from baking sheet.

title: peas and cauliflower
directions: Measure water and salt into 2-quart saucepan.
Place cauliflower in pan with peas on top.
Cook as directed on package. Stir in butter.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: corn and zucchini medley(easy, fast and delicious)
directions: Cook bacon in large skillet over medium heat until crisp. Remove, crumble and drain on paper towel.
Reserve 2 tablespoons bacon drippings in skillet.
Add zucchini, corn and onions; cook and stir until tender and zucchini is still crisp (7 to 10 minutes); time varies.
Season with pepper; place in serving bowl. Sprinkle vegetables with cheese and crumbled bacon.
Makes 5 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: cheese toast
directions: Prepare eggs and milk as for French toast (but do not put sugar in).
Dip bread slices in mixture and brown.
When bread is all browned, use rest of milk and egg mixture and add grated Cheddar cheese to make a thick sauce, then serve it with sliced dill pickles over it.
This makes a good breakfast.

title: fruit and nut candy
directions: Cook syrup, sugar and cream to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Beat until it begins to thicken and change color.
Add vanilla and fruit and all of the chopped nuts.
Pack in a greased loaf pan.
Let stand 24 hours.
Cut into pieces.

title: cream cheese - tuna bake
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Soften cream cheese and blend with soup.
Stir in tuna, mustard, milk and macaroni.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart dish and sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Cook broccoli until thawed; drain and put into 9 x 13 casserole dish. While broccoli is warm, add cheese and 1/2 stick of oleo. Combine cracker crumbs and 1/2 stick of melted oleo and sprinkle on top of mixture. Bake 25 minutes.

title: strawberry layer salad
directions: Dissolve one package Jell-O in one cup hot water and fold in one half of fruit.
Pour into "snack-and-store" or "cold-cut-keeper" and let congeal in refrigerator.
Spread with sour cream and nuts.
Dissolve other package Jell-O in one cup hot water.
Fold in remaining fruit and spoon over the congealed salad.
Chill until firm.

title: seashell pasta salad
directions: Stir all ingredients together in a large bowl; cover and refrigerate for 1 hour before serving.

title: dill dip
directions: Cut off top of bread.
Scoop out the center and break bread into small pieces for dipping.
Mix other ingredients together for dip.
Chill.
Pour the dip into the bread loaf just before serving.

title: double chocolate chunk cookies
directions: Melt 1 square chocolate in small microwavable bowl on High for 1 to 2 minutes or until almost melted, stirring after each minute. Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Cut 3 squares chocolate into large chunks; set aside.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Line baking dish with pastry.
Fill crust with sliced green tomatoes.
Mix sugar, vinegar, cinnamon, ginger, margarine and a little water.
Pour mixture over tomatoes.
Cover with pastry crust.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Sort and wash cranberries; grind with food chopper, using fine knife.
Slice and remove seeds from orange, lemon and lime.
Put through food chopper; mix with sugar and cranberries.
Chill several hours before serving.
Makes 1 quart.

title: poppy's butter cookies(yields 6 dozen)
directions: Cream butter and sugar until blended.
Add egg and mix together.
Add flavoring and mix.
Add 1/3 of the flour and all of the salt.
Mix.
Add another 1/3 of flour and mix.
Then add the last of the flour and mix.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add bananas, eggs and dry ingredients sifted together.
Mix just enough to moisten flour; then pour into well-buttered loaf pan.
