Bake at 300° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until tester comes out clean.
Cool before slicing.

title: darrin's gingerbread
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs. Stir together dry ingredients and blend in. Beat until smooth. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 9 pan. Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes. Cut into squares. Serve hot with whipped cream or applesauce.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Debone the chicken and mix with onion, bell pepper, Ro-Tel, soup, salt and pepper.
Set aside.
In casserole dish, line bottom and sides with Doritos.
Pour chicken mixture in the middle and spread evenly.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: john torrey
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Spray skillet with a non-stick coating.
Add ground beef, green pepper and onion.
Saute until tender.
Add remaining ingredients including macaroni.
Pour into a casserole dish that has been sprayed with non-stick coating.
Bake, covered, for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 7 servings.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in 4 eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture, alternately with buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour 1/4 of batter into 2 greased and floured (9-inch) pans.
Stir nuts, raisins and spices into remaining batter; pour into 2 more prepared pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
When cake is done, put layers together with Japanese Fruit Cake Filling, alternating light and dark layers.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs slightly, then beat in sugar and flour. Add melted butter, milk, vanilla and spices.
Pour into pie crust and bake at 450 degrees for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 300 degrees and bake till filling is firm.

title: landon's favorite pudding chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine butter or oleo, sugars, vanilla and pudding mix.
Beat until smooth.
Add eggs and mix well.
Combine baking soda and flour and add to butter mixture.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Drop by tablespoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in a casserole; cover with bread crumbs and bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Grind vegetables.
Pour boiling water over ground vegetables. Let stand 20 minutes.
Drain.
Heat vinegar, sugar and salt. Pour over vegetable mixture.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Place in jars and seal.
Makes about 6 pints.

title: pumpkin jelly roll cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Beat eggs and sugar together for 5 minutes.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Fold in dry ingredients.
Grease and flour jelly roll pan.
Pour batter in pan; sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Cool slightly.
Sprinkle 10x sugar over towel; turn out cake on it.
Roll cake in towel from long side.

title: tuna or salmon dinner
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed. Stir in soup and milk. Gently stir in tuna or salmon and peas.
Heat to serving temperature.

title: eraser
directions: You will need wax paper (3 x 6-inch), stapler or tape, saucepan and potholder, rubber spatula and plastic wrap.

title: italian casserole
directions: Cook hamburger, broccoli and macaroni separately.
Mix together in baking dish.
Pour sauce over.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tea biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup hot water (with salt and sugar) in a medium sized glass bowl.
Cover and set aside in warm dark place for about 10 minutes.

title: orange snowballs
directions: Mix crumbs,
melted margarine, 1 c. sugar, nuts and orange juice;
Mix well.
Shape into balls.
Mix soft margarine and rest of sugar with enough milk to make it easy to spread.
Roll balls in sugar mix, then coconut.
Store in air tight container.
Better after they have set for 3 or 4 days.

title: shrimp patties
directions: Cut shrimp into 3 to 4 pieces.
Mix with onion, bell pepper and celery.
Stir in remaining ingredients except oil and mix well. Cover bowl and refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours.

title: sparkling pineapple drink
directions: Fill 6 glasses 2/3 full of pineapple juice; add club soda and ice cubes.
Garnish and serve.

title: chicken and broccoli bake
directions: Bake chicken in oven according to directions on Shake 'n Bake package.
Remove chicken from bones in small pieces.
Cook broccoli in boiling water until color changes.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Line bottom of baking pan with layers of broccoli, chicken, cream of chicken soup (straight from can) and bread crumbs.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Mix drained vegetables, soup, chicken and 1 cup of chicken stock reserved from cooking chicken.
Pour mixture into deep dish pie crust.
Invert remaining pie crust over this and remove pie pan.
Place pie on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Pour hot water over jello and stir well.
Add pineapple, cherries and nuts.
Pour in Coke and stir well.
Chill overnight. Especially good with beef.

title: boston clam chowder
directions: Wash clams and steam in a 12-quart heavy stockpot.
Reserve the broth.
Remove the clams from their shells and chop coarsely. Cover both items and set aside.
In the same pot, saute the garlic in the butter for about 3 minutes.
Add onion, celery, pepper, bay leaf and thyme.
Saute until onions are clear.
Add the flour to make a roux, stirring constantly.
Cook over low heat 5 minutes. Slowly add the clam nectar, stirring constantly to avoid lumps. Simmer for 10 minutes (soup will be thick, be careful that it does not burn).
Add potato and cook until tender.
Add cream and clams and bring back to boil.
Serves 10.

title: fish patties
directions: Cook fish for 10 minutes in water; drain.
Combine fish with potatoes and egg (if too soft, add potato flakes).
Roll in bread crumbs and fry.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Combine granulated and brown sugars and salt in a bowl.
Stir in beaten eggs and milk, mixing well.
Add oats, coconut and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: bohemian crescents
directions: Cream butter or margarine and blend in sugar, then vanilla. Add flour gradually, stirring until smooth after each addition. Stir in chopped nuts.
Dip fingers in flour, then shape small pieces of dough into crescents (about 1 1/2 to 2-inches).
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake in moderate oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
When still warm, sprinkle with confectioners sugar. Makes 5 dozen.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Stir; put in crock-pot on low all day.
Stir occasionally.

title: crab bread
directions: Combine ingredients in a large bowl and mix thoroughly.
Spread onto French bread that has been cut in half crosswise.
Put the halves onto a broiler pan and broil until cheese is melted and top is a light golden brown.
Cut into slices and serve warm.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook over medium heat the
flour, sugar, milk and butter until thick.
Add vanilla.
Place in baked pie shells.
Add strawberries.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Makes 2 pies.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix together.
Put in greased 11 x 13-inch pan.
Cook at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, shape into loaf.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour or until done.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes about 8 servings.
tags: Recipe Secrets beefy onion soup mix

title: chocolate oatmeal cake
directions: Mix oats and water; set aside.
Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a greased and floured pan at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: layered dessert
directions: Mix well and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Prick bottom dough all over with fork and bake in 425° (preheated) oven for 10 minutes.
Combine the eggs, milk, salt, nutmeg and pepper in a bowl and beat to mix thoroughly.
Mix in cooked spinach and the onion butter mixture.
Sprinkle the cheese over the partially baked pie shell.
Ladle the spinach custard mixture over the cheese.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: party squares
directions: Fry beef and sausage together; drain well.
Add garlic powder and cheese.
After all cheese has melted, leave on low heat. Spread on rye bread and place on cookie sheet to freeze.
After frozen, can be placed in 1 container.
Take out as many as needed and bake in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: never fail peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, Karo syrup and water until thread spins.
Add peanuts and stir constantly, cooking until it turns brownish gold. Take from heat.
Add butter, salt and baking soda; mix.
Pour immediately onto buttered cookie sheet to cool.

title: broccoli casserole or asparagus
directions: Mix together the bread, Longhorn cheese and melted butter. Pour half of the mixture in a casserole dish.
Layer broccoli or asparagus and cubed chicken.
Pour soup mixture over chicken and top with remaining bread crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: 9-day cole slaw
directions: Chop ingredients and set aside while preparing dressing.

title: sugarless apple cookies
directions: In large saucepan, combine dates, apples, raisins and water. Bring to boil and reduce heat and simmer 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool.

title: white ball cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix shortening, margarine, sugar, eggs and flavorings.
(The addition of a few drops of food coloring could be added at this point, if desired.)
Add flour and salt.
Roll dough (about a teaspoonful at a time) into small balls (1 to 1 1/2-inches in diameter) by hand.
Place on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake 5 to 6 minutes or until bottoms are just barely brown. Don't overbake.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: ranchero cornbake
directions: Combine muffin mix and dressing mix.
Stir in eggs, butter and sour cream until moistened.
Add everything else except cheese, stirring until combined.
Pour into a 9-inch dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: medley of vegetables
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in tightly covered 3-quart casserole.
Bake in 350° oven until tender, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Add beaten eggs, melted butter, buttermilk and flavoring.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: baked sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Wash and scrub sweet potatoes; pierce them with a small knife or fork.

title: creamy chocolate frosting
directions: Melt butter over low heat with the water.
Remove from heat and stir in cocoa.
Beat in sugar, one cup at a time, and add vanilla.
Beat to consistency (add a little water if too thick).

title: mexican style chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken and de-bone.
Cook spaghetti as per package directions.
In medium saucepan, saute pepper, onion and celery in butter.
Add soup, Ro-Tel tomatoes, mushrooms, salt, garlic powder, bouillon cubes and water.
Stir.
In large bowl, mix spaghetti, soup mixture and cheeses.
Place all in greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in a baking dish.
Mix together all remaining ingredients and brush over potatoes.
Bake for 45 minutes, brushing occasionally in a 375° oven.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and set aside.
Drain cherries and set aside.
Mix cherry juice with
baking soda, flour-cornstarch mixture, sugar and food coloring. Place cherries in pan, pour juice mixture on top then top with oatmeal topping.
Cook at 300 for 25 minutes.

title: farmhouse barbecue muffins
directions: Separate dough into 10 biscuits; flatten into 5-inch circles. Press each into the bottom and up the sides of a greased muffin cup; set aside.

title: strawberry butter
directions: Bring margarine or butter to room temperature and whip.
Let strawberries thaw.
Whip all ingredients together, including strawberry juice, with large mixer.
Vary amount of sugar to taste (increase when using frozen; decrease when using fresh).

title: orange chicken
directions: Combine 1/4 cup flour, salt, pepper and paprika in plastic bag without holes.
Shake contents, then place chicken breasts in bag and shake.
Take coated chicken breasts and brown in oil.
Remove chicken.
In same pan, mix juice, sherry, sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to boil and reduce heat.
Add combined water and cornstarch until thickened.
Place chicken in greased pan.
Place peppers and onions on top of chicken.
Pour orange juice mix over top.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy quiche
directions: Beat eggs until foamy, add soup and milk, mixing well. Sprinkle cheese, meat, and vegetable evenly over the pie crust (use the deep dish, 9 inch frozen).
Pour liquid mixture over all and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350 for 50 minutes or until center is set.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften and whip cream cheese. Drain and rinse shrimp.
Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate for 3 to 4 hours.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Batter for each cookie may be up to 1/4 cup or make regular size cookies.

title: to the moon chili
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in seasoning mix, water, tomatoes, beans and red hot sauce.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, 10 minutes.
Garnish with chopped red pepper, green onion and cheese, if desired.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Fix cornbread and let cool.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: multi-colored layer jello salad
directions: Use jellos in order as named.
Dissolve 1 package of jello in 1 cup of boiling water.
Take 1/2 cup of jello and 1/3 cup sour cream.
Blend well and pour into dish.

title: old-fashioned bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly spray bottom of 2 1/2-quart baking dish with Pam, etc.
Line bottom with bread cubes; scatter raisins over.
In large bowl, mix thoroughly egg whites, milk, extracts, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and liqueur.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until set.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Let stand 24 hours.

title: southwest chicken salad
directions: Stir together dressings and ground red pepper; reserve 1/2 cup.
Pour remaining dressing mixture over chicken.
Cover; marinate in refrigerator 2 to 3 hours.
Preheat electric broiler (not necessary to preheat gas broiler).
Remove chicken from marinade, reserving marinade.
Place chicken on greased rack of broiler pan so top is 4 to 5 inches from heat.
Broil 10 minutes on each side or until tender, brushing occasionally with reserved marinade.
Cut into strips.
Arrange chicken, avocado and red pepper over lettuce on large serving platter.
Sprinkle with cilantro.
Serve with reserved dressing mixture.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Batter will not be thick.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spicy barbecue sauce
directions: Bake garlic in a small baking pan at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool and peel.
Combine garlic and remaining ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Cool.
Pour into blender; process until smooth, stopping once to scrape down sides.
Yields 4 1/2 cups.

title: beets and pineapple
directions: Drain pineapple chunks and use pineapple juice, cornstarch, vinegar and salt; cook and add pineapple chunks and drained beets. Simmer about 20 minutes.

title: cranberry harvest relish
directions: Boil 1 cup water; remove from heat. Add jello and sugar and stir until dissolved. Add lemon juice and remaining water. Chill while preparing cranberries. In blender, chop cranberries and orange, a small amount at a time. Place in large bowl. Stir in apple, celery, nuts and jello mixture; chill until set.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter. Cook broccoli as label directs and drain.
Mix all ingredients, adding salt and pepper to taste. Serve in chafing dish.

title: evelyn collins' dietetic fruit cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until water is gone.
Add applesauce, eggs, sweetener and oil.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients and vanilla.
Pour into loaf pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems. Chop and saute in butter with onion.
Add other ingredients except mushroom caps.
Cool mixture.
Fill caps and cover with bread crumbs.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Vary by adding chopped ham, chicken, celery, cheese, etc.

title: combination punch(serves 50 to 60)
directions: Mix juices.
Let stand 1 to 2 hours for flavors to blend. Refrigerate until very cold.
Pour in ginger ale just before serving.
(Crushed ice or an ice ring may be used.)

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, combine butter and stuffing mix. Pat down on bottom of pan.
Boil chicken breasts in a large Dutch oven until tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Let cool.
Save the chicken stock.
Debone the meat and dice.
Combine soup, milk and chicken stock.
Layer the stuffing, chicken and soup mixture twice.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: kansas dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies. Put half in 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix cream cheese and butter until smooth. Mix in powdered sugar. Fold in whipped topping. Mix pudding, milk and vanilla. Fold 2 mixtures together and pour over crumb mix in pan. Top with remaining crumbs. May be chilled or frozen. Makes 12 servings.

title: pea casserole
directions: Brown mushrooms and pimentos in butter.
Toast almonds at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Layer peas, soup, almonds, pimentos and mushrooms.
Repeat.
Top with dots of butter or may use cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350°
until bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hot sweet mustard
directions: Mix mustard with a little water to make a paste.
Mix cornstarch, sugar, salt and water; cook over low heat 5 minutes until smooth.
Add vinegar.
Cool mixture; then add mustard.

title: fettucini
directions: Boil fettucini as directed.
Steam vegetables until tender. In a pan, melt butter and whipping cream; add Parmesan cheese. Mix everything together and serve.

title: seafood cocktail sauce
directions: Combine celery and green pepper into processing bowl in a food processor.
Grind until coarsely chopped.
Add remaining ingredients and grind until desired consistency is reached.
Makes 1 cup.

title: creamy holiday vegetable dip
directions: In bowl, beat cheese until fluffy; blend in chili sauce and next 4 ingredients.
Cover; chill.
Serve with vegetables or chips.
Makes about 1 2/3 cups.

title: may to september pasta
directions: Cook pasta, drain and rinse with hot water.
Cut tomatoes and Mozzarella cheese into bite-size pieces.
Chop basil leaves.
When pasta is ready, in large bowl toss pasta, tomatoes, Mozzarella and basil.
In measuring cup, mix olive oil and garlic.
Pour over pasta and toss.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
May be served hot or cold.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixer bowl, beat sweetened condensed milk, peanut butter, egg and vanilla until smooth.
Add biscuit mix.
Mix well.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Flatten with fork.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool. Store tightly covered at room temperature.

title: easiest peach cobbler ever
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter/margarine in baking dish (set aside).
Mix flour and sugar together; gradually add milk to the flour/sugar mixture.
Pour into the baking dish.
Spoon in peaches.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: rhubarb rumble
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, oatmeal and cinnamon in a bowl.
Add melted butter.
Press half of mixture in greased baking pan.
Put diced rhubarb on mixture.

title: cobbler
directions: Put into deep baking dish.
Cover with 2 cups fruit (may use drained can fruit or pie filling (cherry, peach, apple) Your choice........

title: oven fried steak
directions: Dip steaks into eggs.
Roll in corn flakes, salt and pepper as desired.
Brown in hot fat.
Then remove and place in greased baking dish and cover steaks with soup, diluted with 1 cup water. Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour.

title: pork in wine sauce
directions: Slice onion in thin rings and saute in olive oil until soft and beginning to brown slightly.
Remove and keep warm.
Season both sides or pork with black pepper and garlic powder.
Brown both sides of pork. Return onions to pan and add wine and soy sauce.
Cover and simmer for 35 to 40 minutes. Serves 2.

title: christmas wreath cookies
directions: Melt margarine and marshmallows in large bowl in microwave. Add color and extracts.
Stir in flakes until well coated.
Use about 1 tablespoon for each cookie.
Dip fingers in cold water (not butter) so it doesn't stick.
Shape into a wreath and decorate with candies while sticky.
Place on wax paper.
Allow to dry uncovered at room temperature for 8 hours.
Makes 12 to 18 wreaths.
Make only one batch at a time, don't try to double the recipe.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Bake cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool.
Frost cake with chocolate frosting.
Right before serving, spoon cherries over frosted cake.

title: potato casserole
directions: Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Place all ingredients in a 1 or 1 1/2-quart high sided casserole pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Stir; bake 15 minutes more at same temperature.
Serve warm with Doritos chips.

title: creamy stuffed potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes thoroughly and rub skins with oil.
Bake at 400° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until done.
Allow to cool to touch. Slice skin away from top of each potato.
Carefully scoop out pulp, leaving shells intact.
Mash pulp.
Cook bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Reserve 3 tablespoons of drippings in skillet. Saute onion in bacon drippings until tender.
Combine potato pulp, bacon, onion, cheese, sour cream, salt and pepper; mix well. Stuff shells with potato mixture.
Sprinkle each with 1/8 teaspoon of paprika.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until heated thoroughly.

title: rhubarb upside down cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan (bottom).
Mix first 4 items and put in bottom of pan.
Mix cake according to directions on box.
Pour over rhubarb mixture.
Bake 55 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: tuna (or chicken) souffle salad
directions: Blend Jell-O and hot water.
Add mayonnaise; fold in rest of ingredients.
Chill until set.
Serve.

title: aunt pam's hot mexican salad
directions: Fry hamburger; drain fat.
Add taco sauce, tomatoes, lettuce and onions.
Let simmer.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: pork chops and spanish rice
directions: Trim excess fat from chops.
Heat fat in skillet; when you have 2 tablespoons of melted fat, remove the trimmings.
Slowly brown chops in fat; drain.
Combine seasonings and sprinkle over meat.
Add rice, onion and green pepper.
Pour tomatoes over mix; cover.
Cook over low heat 30 to 35 minutes.
Add green pepper rings and cook 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: chili corn muffins
directions: Mix all together until moist (do not overmix).
In a greased pan, fill 2/3 full with mixture.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm.
Makes 18 to 20 muffins.

title: no bake chocolate peanut butter bars
directions: Mix ingredients together and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Melt 12 ounces semi-sweet chocolate chips and spread over top.
Refrigerate to set.

title: mexicali casserole
directions: Mix chili, drained corn and cut up tomatoes in a bowl. Combine muffin mix according to directions on the box.
In a baking dish, put ingredients in the center and put muffin mix completely around the outside of the ingredients (along the baking dish).
Bake according to the directions for the muffin mix.

title: hot rize biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Cut shortening into flour until particles are as fine as coarse crumbs.
Add milk; stir in with fork.
Turn dough out on slightly floured board or pastry cloth; knead just until smooth.
Roll out about 1/2 inch thick; cut with floured cutter.
Place biscuits on lightly greased baking sheet; bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix together.
Make into small meatballs.
Place on cookie sheet; brown at 350° for 10 minutes.
Place in crock-pot.
Add jelly and chili sauce.
Let cook for 4 hours on low.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: In double boiler, combine sugars with flour and add hot milk gradually.
Stir constantly to make smooth.
Add salt and cook for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally until thick.
Pour part of mixture slowly into egg yolks, stirring constantly.
Pour back into double boiler; mix well and cook 3 minutes.
Stir and add butter.
Cool and add vanilla.
Pour into pastry shell.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Combine cake mix, 2 eggs and margarine.
Mix well and spread in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1 cup pecans and chocolate chips.
Combine cream cheese, 3 eggs, sugar and 1/2 cup pecans and spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: gorton's crab soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Cook on low for 6 hours.
Stir once an hour.
Serves 4.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Fill baked pie shell with fresh strawberries sliced in half. Mix water and cornstarch together.
Cook mashed strawberries and sugar.
Slowly add the cornstarch mixture to mashed strawberries and cook until thick.
Add lemon juice.
While still hot, pour over strawberries in pie shell.
Chill and top with whipped cream.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Melt peanut butter and butter over hot water in double boiler. Mix sugar and cereal.
Pour peanut butter mixture on cereal and mix well.
Make finger shapes by squeezing in palm of hand.
After set, dip ends in or frost and stripe with melted chocolate.

title: "easy" ice cream pie(but tastes and looks gourmet.)
directions: Lightly grease a 9-inch pie plate.
In glass bowl or pie plate, melt butter.
Mix in cookie crumbs and sugar.
Press into pie plate.
Heat in microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Cool.

title: quick baked beans
directions: Empty beans into greased baking dish.
Pour next four ingredients over them.
Place bacon strips over top.
Bake at 300° until bacon is crisp and beans are thoroughly heated.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat eggs and oil in small bowl.
Combine flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt in a large bowl. Add egg mixture. Mix well.

title: special k bars
directions: Heat sugar and syrup until they boil.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter and vanilla; mix well.
Pour in cereal and stir.
Press into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips.
Spread on top.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring the butter, water, and cocoa to a boil.
Add flour, salt, sugar, and baking soda all at once.
Cream well.
Add eggs and sour cream.
Bake in greased and floured jelly roll pan (15 x 10-inch) for about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: bourbon balls
directions: In large bowl, mix all ingredients except granulated sugar. Shape into 1/2 inch balls.
Roll balls in granulated sugar.
Store in tightly covered container for at least 3 days before serving for flavors to mellow.
Keeps up to 2 weeks in tightly covered container.
Makes about 3-1/2 dozen balls.

title: jambalaya
directions: Heat oil in large pan.
Saute onion, green pepper and garlic until tender.
Add chicken, ham and sausage.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bring to boil.
Cover and reduce heat.
Cook approximately 20 minutes to 25 minutes or until rice is done and liquid is absorbed.
Serves 8.

title: spanish rice
directions: In a skillet, saute the onion and green pepper in oil until tender. Add the remaining ingredients and mix well. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed. Yield: 6 servings.

title: banana-nut bread(muffins)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend all ingredients except nuts in a large mixer bowl, then beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Stir in nuts.
Makes 1 big loaf or five 1 pound pans.
Bake 35 minutes. Test with toothpick.
Let cool 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: quickie chicken cacciatore
directions: Wash chicken and place in bottom of Pyrex dish sprayed with Pam.
Cut up tomatoes (use all juice in can, too) and mix with the dry spaghetti mix. Pour over chicken and bake, covered, 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Serve with rice.

title: party punch
directions: Make a syrup by combining sugar and water; bring to a boil and cook until sugar is dissolved.
Add the lemon Jell-O; allow to cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serves 100.

title: graham cracker crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: corn bread salad
directions: *Can use bacon, Polish or Italian sausage instead of regular sausage.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients
except bread crumbs and margarine, mixing well.
Pour	into
3 quart oblong casserole dish. Combine melted margarine and bread crumbs.	Sprinkle over top. Bake at 350° for 35 to
40	minutes
or
until bubbly and hot. Serves 12 to 15.

title: new orleans style gumbo
directions: Preparation:
Chop the onion and green pepper.
Mince the garlic.
Skin, bone and cut chicken into bite sized pieces.
Cut the sausage into 1/2-inch slices and quarter each slice.
Rinse, clean and halve the shrimp.

title: kool pops
directions: Dissolve jello, sugar and Kool-Aid in hot water, then add cold water.
Mix well and pour into molds or small glasses and freeze. Refreshing on a warm day.

title: crunchy frozen punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 9 cups of boiling water.
Combine the sugar and water; bring to a quick boil.
Add to Jell-O mixture.
Set aside to cool.
When cool, add lemon and pineapple juices.
Mix well and freeze.
(Use the large Tupperware cake carrier.)

title: grandma schmidt's poppy seed torte
directions: Soak the poppy seed at least 2 hours in the milk.

title: strawberry tiramisu torte
directions: With a sharp bread knife, slice angel food cake crosswise into 3 layers.
Sift 1 tablespoon unsweetened cocoa powder onto a 12 to 14-inch cake plate to within 1 inch of rim.
Place bottom layer of cake onto the cocoa.
Drizzle 1/3 of the Espresso (mixed with almond extract) over first layer of cake.
Cover the layer with 1/2 of the sliced strawberries.
Spread 1/2 of the cream cheese mixture (cream cheese, yogurt, powdered sugar and vanilla extract) over the strawberries.
Top with the second layer of the cake. Drizzle 1/3 of the Espresso mixture over the cake.
Cover with the remaining strawberries, then the cream cheese mixture.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except walnuts and raisins. Add them last and gently mix with spoon.
Divide into 3 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Can be wrapped in freezer paper and frozen until needed.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring sugar, butter, cocoa and milk to a boil.
Boil 2 minutes. Remove from stove and add coconut, nuts, oats and vanilla.
Stir and drop by spoon on wax paper.

title: clear bowl fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple juice and oranges, then mix oranges and pineapple with cherry pie filling.
Chill until ready to serve. Put thinly sliced bananas on top.

title: extra special rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 3 tablespoons of warm water in a large mixing bowl; let stand 5 minutes.
Add sugar, shortening, eggs, 1 cup warm water, salt and 2 cups flour.
Beat at low speed on an electric mixer for 1 minute.
Gradually stir in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface; knead 4 minutes or until smooth and elastic.
Shape dough into a ball; place in a well-greased bowl, turning to grease top. Cover; let rise in a warm place (85°), free from drafts, for 1 hour or until doubled in bulk.

title: chicken quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake pie shell 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and reduce to 350°.
In bowl toss cheese with flour and bouillon and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell and bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Mix all together.
Store in a tight container.
Mix 1 cup hot water to 1/4 cup of mix.
Makes about 30 cups.

title: homemade oven fries
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cut potatoes lengthwise into wedges. Place on greased cookie sheet.
Brush potato slices with vegetable oil.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and bake until done.

title: venison chablis
directions: Brown meat; drain off liquid.
Add all other ingredients. Cover and bake in the oven at 325° for 3 hours.
Stir well every 1/2 hour.
Serve over rice.

title: husband's delight
directions: Combine all the ingredients.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Sprinkle over top 3/4 cup chopped nuts mixed with 3/4 cup brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: jello mold
directions: Bring to a boil, pineapple and sugar, then add jello.
Let set to thicken.
Then add cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Mix together and let set in fridge.

title: mint-chocolate chip surprise
directions: Dip cookies
in
milk
(briefly
so
they won't get too soggy).
Layer the cookies
in 13 x 9-inch glass pan (any size pan does fine if you choose to make more).
After first layer, mix mint extract into Cool Whip (add more mint or less mint to your desired taste).
Layer Cool Whip on top of first layer of cookies. Continue
layering
cookies,
Cool Whip, cookies and Cool
Whip. Decorate
top
with
coconut, sprinkles, etc., if desired.

title: quicky pickled beets
directions: Drain beets reserving 3/4 cup liquid.
Combine beet liquid with vinegar and next 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to boil; pour over beets.
Refrigerate overnight in covered bowl.
Onion may be added just before serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham crackers and 1 stick melted margarine and press into a 9x13 inch pan.

title: velvet souffle
directions: Prepare a 5-inch souffle dish with a 2-inch paper collar. Whisk egg yolks and sugar in a bowl over a pan of hot water until thick and creamy.
Remove from heat; whisk while cooling.
Put the water into a small bowl; sprinkle the gelatin over it and leave to "sponge."
Melt the chocolate.
In a bowl over hot water, melt the gelatin.
Add the gelatin to the egg mixture; mix well.
Add the melted chocolate and brandy; mix again.
Whip cream lightly and fold into the mixture.
Whisk the egg whites until stiff and fold in carefully.
Pour the mixture into the souffle dish and refrigerate.
Decorate with whipped cream and chocolate.

title: cheese enchiladas
directions: Cook and stir onion, garlic and chili powder in 2 tablespoons oil until onion is tender.
Stir in cumin, salt, pepper and tomatoes, breaking up tomatoes.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, until thickened, about 30 minutes.
Mix cheeses. Heat 1/2 cup oil in skillet until hot.
Dip each tortilla lightly into oil to soften; drain on paper towels.
Dip each tortilla into tomato mixture to coat both sides.
Spoon about 2 tablespoons of cheese on each tortilla.
Roll tortilla and place seam side down in ungreased rectangular pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Pour tomato mixture on top of tortillas.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until cheese is melted.
Top with avocado slices, olives or sour cream.
Enjoy!
Makes 6 servings, 490 calories per serving.

title: green salsa
directions: Place tomatillos, 1 jalapeno pepper, onion, garlic and water in saucepan.
Cover.
Boil for 6 minutes.
Puree the vegetables together.
Cool.
Add salt, cilantro and another jalapeno pepper if you like it hot, and mix.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together well and serve with any fruit.

title: squash pie
directions: Beat egg whites, sugar and cream of tartar until stiff. Spread on pie.
Brown.

title: scampi-style shrimp
directions: Thaw shrimp if frozen.
Remove shells and devein.
Gently pat dry with paper toweling.
In a large skillet melt butter over medium heat.
Add onion, garlic, lemon peel, lemon juice, salt and pepper sauce.
Cook until boiling.
Add shrimp to the skillet and cook about 5 minutes or until shrimp turn pink.
Serve with rice; top with parsley and shredded lemon peel.

title: easy zucchini pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients (zucchini last). Pour into a greased pie dish until golden brown (about 40 to 45 minutes).
Good either hot or cold.
Great as a side dish or as a main course served with salad.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.

title: ground turkey soup
directions: Brown ground turkey in Dutch oven. Add onions, cooking until tender. Drain if necessary. Stir in remaining ingredients. Simmer until vegetables are almost done, then add noodles. Continue simmering until noodles are cooked. Add more water as needed or for desired thickness.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook chicken in water and remove from bones.
Add vegetables to broth and simmer, uncovered, until done. Add chicken and seasoning.

title: mexitalian lasagna
directions: In large bowl, combine chili, salsa, mushrooms, Parmesan cheese and Italian seasoning.
In small bowl, stir together cottage cheese and parsley flakes.
In a 9 x 9-inch pan sprayed with cooking spray, layer the noodles, cottage cheese, chili mixture and Mozzarella cheese until there are 3 layers.
After it has cooked, let stand 10 minutes.

title: barbecued popcorn
directions: In small saucepan, over low heat, combine margarine and spices.
Stir until margarine is melted.
Pour spice mixture over popcorn in a large bowl; mix thoroughly to coat.
Makes 4 (2-cup) servings.
